title: Aargau
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Core Worlds', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-10'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': 'Bank of Aargau'}}
paragraph: Aargau was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Core Worlds, in grid square L-10 on the Standard Galactic Grid, that was headquarters of the Bank of Aargau.

title: Aargonar
side_bar: {'Physical information': {'Points of interest': 'Aargonar Separatist base'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Confederacy of Independent Systems'}}
paragraph: Aargonar was a planet located in the galaxy. During the Clone Wars, the husband of Senator Mina Bonteri went there to set up a base for the Confederacy of Independent Systems, but was killed when Republic clone troopers attacked. It was the homeworld of Imperial stormtrooper TK-14057.

title: Abafar
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Sprizen sector', 'System': 'Abafar system'}, 'Physical information': {'Diameter': ['12 11 714'], 'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Climate': ['Hot', 'dry'], 'Primary terrain': 'Desert', 'Surface water': ['80 40 000'], 'Points of interest': ['Rhydonium mining installation', 'The Void'], 'Fauna': 'Void strider'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': ['Human', 'Sullustan'], 'Major cities': 'Pons Ora', 'Major exports': 'Rhydonium', 'Affiliation': 'Unallied '}}
paragraph: Abafar was a remote desert planet located within the Outer Rim Territories, and was host to massive amounts of rhydonium, a scarce and volatile fuel source. The large desert was known as the Void, and light was twisted in a way by the strange regolith that made it impossible to see tracks because there were no shadows. During the Clone Wars, the Confederacy of Independent Systems set up a mining installation in the settlement of Pons Ora. The planet wasn't very populated. During the reign of the Galactic Empire, the Hutt crime lord Jabba Desilijic Tiure had a drilling platform on Abafar to mine rhydonium. Following the Battle of Endor, the New Republic pilot Wedge Antilles visited Abafar whilst looking for Imperial forces that may have been hiding in the Outer Rim.

title: Abhean
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'R-7', 'Trade routes': 'Perlemian Trade Route'}}
paragraph: Abhean was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim. It was also located on the Perlemian Trade Route.

title: Abregado-rae
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Core Worlds', 'System': 'Abregado system', 'Suns': 'Anza', 'Grid coordinates': 'K-13', 'Trade routes': 'Rimma Trade Route'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': 'Unidentified aquarium'}}
paragraph: Abregado-rae, also known simply as Abregado and sometimes spelled Abregado-Rae, was a trade world located in the galaxy's Core Worlds. It was situated at the beginning of the Rimma Trade Route. Abregado-rae had the reputation to be a rather lawless world, and its main spaceport was as close to a safe dock for smugglers as could be found in the Core.

title: Adarlon
paragraph: Adarlon was a location whose population suffered a famine while under the control of the New Republic according to claims made in the news feeds of the First Order. The stormtrooper FN-2187 viewed such a news report during a moral session within his training on Starkiller Base, shortly before his deployment to the planet Jakku.

title: Aduba
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Bheriz sector', 'Grid coordinates': 'U-11'}}
paragraph: Aduba was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories way out on the edge of Wild Space, positioned at the coordinates U-11 of the Standard Galactic Grid. It was the homeworld of Cobalt Hammer pilot Finch Dallow. Dallow flew crop-dusters and spotter rigs on Aduba before qualifying for a post in the New Republic scout service.

title: Adumar
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Wild Space', 'System': 'Adumar system', 'Grid coordinates': 'J-6'}}
paragraph: Adumar was an astronomical object located in the Adumar system of the galaxy's Wild Space.

title: Aeneid
side_bar: {'General information': {'Location': ['Kessel sector', 'Outer Rim Territories']}}
paragraph: Aeneid was an astronomical object located in the Kessel sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Affa
side_bar: {'Physical information': {'Primary terrain': 'Terrestrial', 'Points of interest': 'Droid factories'}}
paragraph: Affa was a terrestrial planet that housed great droid factories. Arakyd Industries's RA-7 protocol droids, including DK-RA-43, were manufactured in the factories, while parts for Cybot Galactica's 3PO-series protocol droid were also manufactured on the planet.

title: Agamar
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'System': 'Agamar system', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-5'}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Climate': 'Cold', 'Primary terrain': 'Rocky', 'Points of interest': 'DH-Omni Support Vessel wreckage'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Human', 'Affiliation': 'Confederacy of Independent Systems'}}
paragraph: Agamar was a barren, rocky planet located in the Agamar system within the Outer Rim Territories of the galaxy in grid coordinates M-5. During the Clone Wars, Separatist General Kalani was ordered by Count Dooku to retreat from Onderon to Agamar following the Separatist defeat on Onderon. Later during the Galactic Civil War against the Galactic Empire, the rebel cell known as the Spectres confronted Kalani on Agamar, eventually teaming up to defeat the Empire, a mutual opponent.

title: Ahakista
side_bar: {'General information': {'Location': 'Ahakista system', 'Points of interest': 'Daystar Casino'}}
paragraph: Ahakista was a location in the Ahakista system where the Daystar Casino was built. The Dug gambler Gronson Takkaro, who at one point worked as operations manager of the casino, fell into large amounts of debt on Ahakista and fled to the planet Lothal. The bounty hunter Bossk tracked Takkaro down to Lothal in order to capture him and bring him back to Ahakista to claim a bounty placed on the Dug.

title: Ahch-To
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Unknown Regions', 'System': 'Ahch-To system', 'Suns': '2', 'Moons': '1'}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Primary terrain': ['Oceans', 'Rocky islands'], 'Surface water': 'Oceans', 'Points of interest': 'Temple island', 'Flora': ['Fern', 'Grass', 'Moss', 'Nightkelp', 'Uneti tree'], 'Fauna': ['Ahch-Tonian grub', 'Billfish', 'Coppergrin', 'Fingerlip garpon', 'Frondtrailer', 'Needlegawp', 'Pallaskean', 'Porg', 'Scalefin fish', 'Spetan channelfish', 'Thala-siren', 'Twinfin hyacander', 'Tytahuso fish', 'Unidentified creature', 'Unidentified fish', 'Wharlithan']}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Lanai', 'Immigrated species': 'Human', 'Primary language(s)': "Lanai's language", 'Demonym': 'Ahch-Tonian', 'Affiliation': 'Jedi Order'}}
paragraph: Ahch-To was a planet mostly covered in water, with numerous rocky islands blanketed with green trees located in the Unknown Regions. It was the birthplace of the Jedi Order and held the ancient Jedi texts. Three decades after the Galactic Civil War, it served as the home of Jedi Master Luke Skywalker who went into exile seeking the first Jedi Temple after his temple and his Jedi students were destroyed by Kylo Ren. After the Resistance pieced together two map fragments to reveal Skywalker's location, Rey traveled to Ahch-To in the Millennium Falcon accompanied by R2-D2 and Chewbacca, in search of him.

title: Ailon
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Inner Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-12'}}
paragraph: Ailon was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Inner Rim.

title: Akrit'tar
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'T-9'}}
paragraph: Akrit'tar was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Akuria
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-5'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Alliance to Restore the Republic '}}
paragraph: Akuria was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories, not far from the planet Dantooine, that was a suspected base of rebel operations. Akuria and several other locations were identified in a 3 ABY Imperial Security Bureau report that generated targets for Viper probe droid surveys by cross-referencing areas with a high degree of suspicious activity with the unsettled parts of the galaxy favored by the rebels.

title: Alakatha
side_bar: {'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Primary terrain': 'Beaches'}}
paragraph: Alakatha was a terrestrial astronomical object known for its beaches. Several weeks after the Battle of Endor, while playing the game Who? What? Where? with other New Republic pilots aboard the frigate Hellion's Dare, the pilot Rep Boy claimed that he wished to live until old age and die of heatstroke on the beaches of Alakatha. However, Rep Boy's wish was not fulfilled, as he was killed shortly afterwards by the forces of the Galactic Empire's 204th Imperial Fighter Wing during an attack on the Hellion's Dare.

title: Alderaan
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Core Worlds', 'Sector': 'Alderaan sector', 'System': 'Alderaan system', 'Suns': "1: Alderaan's sun", 'Moons': '0', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-10', 'Trade routes': 'Commenor Run', 'Rotation period': '18 standard hours', 'Orbital period': '364 standard days'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Diameter': ['12', '500 kilometers'], 'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Primary terrain': ['Forests', 'Mountainous', 'Plains'], 'Points of interest': ['Appenza Peak', 'Cloudshape Falls', 'Glarus Lagoons', 'Istabith Falls', 'Isatabith rain forest', 'River Wuitho', 'Royal Palace of Alderaan', 'University of Alderaan'], 'Flora': ['Chinar tree', 'Conifer', 'Starblossom', 'Starflower'], 'Fauna': ['Alderaanian wolf-cat', 'Nerf', 'Snow owl', 'Thranta', 'Unidentified bird']}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Human', 'Primary language(s)': ['Galactic Basic'], 'Government': 'Monarchy', 'Population': ['2 billion', '95% humans', '5% other'], 'Demonym': 'Alderaanian', 'Major cities': ['Aldera', 'Crevasse City', 'Sanctuary Coast', 'Unidentified city'], 'Major imports': ['Electronics', 'Manufactured goods'], 'Major exports': ['Art', 'Luxury goods', 'Wine'], 'Affiliation': ['Elder Houses', 'House of Organa', 'Galactic Republic', 'Galactic Empire', 'Alliance to Restore the Republic']}}
paragraph: Alderaan, located in the Core Worlds, was a terrestrial planet covered with mountains. During the waning decades of the Galactic Republic, it was ruled by Queen Breha Organa and represented in the Galactic Senate by her husband, Senator Bail Prestor Organa.

title: Aldraig
side_bar: {'General information': {'Location': ['Alderaan sector', 'Core Worlds']}}
paragraph: Aldraig was an astronomical object in the Alderaan sector of the Core Worlds. During the early rebellion against the Galactic Empire, Senator Bail Organa of the Imperial Senate attempted to cover up a theft of a UT-60D transport shipment by having an Aldraig data clerk mistakenly route a shipment of U-wings to Coruscant through Baylagon.

title: Aleen
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Sector': 'Bright Jewel sector', 'System': 'Aleen system', 'Moons': '1: Trohlu', 'Trade routes': ['Celanon Spur', 'Entralla Route'], 'Rotation period': '31 hours', 'Orbital period': '399 days'}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': ['Dual atmosphere', 'Surface: Breathable', 'Underworld: Non-oxygen'], 'Climate': 'Temperate', 'Primary terrain': ['Surface:Rocky mesas and buttes', 'Desert plains', 'Isolated forests', 'Underworld:Geological and arboreal root caverns', 'Luminescent vegetation groves'], 'Surface water': 'Shallow seas', 'Points of interest': ['Underworld', 'Aleena village', 'Jedi chapter house', 'Great Seal'], 'Flora': 'Arbozoic tree', 'Fauna': ['Bogwing', 'Can-cell', 'Firefly']}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': ['Aleena', 'Kindalo'], 'Primary language(s)': ['Aleena', 'Kindalo', 'Galactic Basic'], 'Government': ['Surface: Monarchy', 'Underworld: Anarchical consensus'], 'Population': ['At least 18', '000', '000', '99% Aleena', '1% other', 'Underworld: Unknow'], 'Major cities': 'None major', 'Major imports': 'None', 'Major exports': 'None', 'Affiliation': ['Galactic Republic', 'Jedi Order']}}
paragraph: Aleen was a rocky planet located within the Bright Jewel sector, of the galaxy's Mid Rim. It was home to the diminutive, surface-dwelling Aleena species, and a bioluminescent tree-like species, the Kindalo. At one point in their history, the two species clashed which almost resulted in the destruction of all sentient life on the planet. During the Clone Wars, the Galactic Republic arrived to help the Aleena rebuild after a series of devastating groundquakes.

title: Allyuen
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Anoat sector'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': 'Allyuen spaceport'}, 'Societal information': {'Major exports': 'Chromite', 'Affiliation': ['Noble Court', 'Galactic Empire']}}
paragraph: Allyuen was a planet located in the Anoat sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories and home to the Allyuen spaceport, which was garrisoned by the Galactic Empire.

title: Almania
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'S-5'}}
paragraph: Almania was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Alpheridies
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region', 'Grid coordinates': 'O-8'}}
paragraph: Alpheridies was an astronomical body located in the galaxy's Expansion Region.

title: Alsakan
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Core Worlds', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-9', 'Trade routes': 'Perlemian Trade Route'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': 'Alsakan Academy'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Human', 'Demonym': 'Alsakan'}}
paragraph: Alsakan was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Core Worlds, in grid square L-9 on the Standard Galactic Grid, on the Perlemian Trade Route. It was the homeworld of both Doctor Cornelius Evazan and Allegiant General Enric Pryde. Alsakan contained an Imperial Academy attended by Allegiant General Pryde.

title: Ambria
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Inner Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'O-10'}, 'Physical information': {'Primary terrain': 'Desert'}}
paragraph: Ambria was an unpleasant desert planet, in tune with the dark side of the Force, that was located in the galaxy's Inner Rim. It was rumored that Darth Bane, creator of the Rule of Two and the Great Plan, was supposedly killed by his Sith apprentice Darth Zannah while in a duel on Ambria.

title: Ammuud
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Corporate Sector'}, 'Physical information': {'Climate': 'Cold'}, 'Societal information': {'Government': 'Seven family clans'}}
paragraph: Ammuud was a cold planet located in the semi-independent Corporate Sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. The planet saw decades of fighting between its seven resident family clans, who eventually united to govern Ammuud under the Code of Ammuud.

title: Anantapar
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Anoat sector'}}
paragraph: Anantapar was a planet located in the Anoat sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Anaxes
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Core Worlds', 'Sector': 'Azure sector', 'System': 'Azure system', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-9', 'Trade routes': 'Perlemian Trade Route'}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Climate': 'Temperate', 'Primary terrain': ['Canyons', 'Caverns', 'Forests', 'Valleys'], 'Points of interest': ['Anaxes canyon', 'Anaxes Separatist Security Outpost', 'Anaxes shipyards', 'Anaxes War College', 'Cyber Center', 'Fort Anaxes', 'Sector One', 'Separatist stronghold'], 'Fauna': 'Fyrnock'}, 'Societal information': {'Major exports': 'Starships', 'Affiliation': 'Galactic Republic'}}
paragraph: Anaxes was a rocky planet located in the Azure sector of the galaxy's Core Worlds region. A majority of its surface was covered with tall, red plant-like life. In the early years of the Imperial Era, the planet was destroyed in a cataclysm, with the remains becoming the Anaxes asteroid belt.

title: Andara
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Core Worlds', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-13'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': ['Galactic Empire', 'New Republic']}}
paragraph: Andara was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Core Worlds.

title: Andelm IV
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Suns': 'At least 1', 'Moons': 'At least 1'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': 'Andelm beetle caverns', 'Flora': 'Trees', 'Fauna': 'Andelm beetles'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': ['Besalisk', 'Human', 'Jawa', 'Nikto', 'Quarren', 'Rodian', 'Shistavanen', "Twi'lek", 'Zabrak'], 'Major cities': 'Unidentified city', 'Major exports': ['Andelm beetles', 'Dedlanite'], 'Affiliation': ["Jaum's crime syndicate", 'Galactic Empire']}}
paragraph: Andelm IV was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories. During the Galactic Civil War, the planet was ruled by Jaum, a crime lord.

title: Ando
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Sector': 'Lambda sector', 'System': 'Ando system', 'Grid coordinates': 'Q-15'}, 'Physical information': {'Primary terrain': 'Water'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Aqualish', 'Demonym': 'Andoan', 'Affiliation': ['Galactic Republic', 'Confederacy of Independent Systems']}}
paragraph: Ando was a water-covered planet in the Ando system of the Lambda sector, a sector in the galaxy's Mid Rim, located in grid square Q-15 on the Standard Galactic Grid, that was homeworld of the amphibious Aqualish species. At the time of the Trade Federation's Invasion of Naboo, it was a member of the Galactic Republic and was represented in the Galactic Senate by Senator Po Nudo. During the Separatist Crisis, turmoil occurred on Ando that left the galaxy staggered and it seceded from the Republic, joining the Confederacy of Independent Systems, which promised it the support of the InterGalactic Banking Clan and Techno Union. A type of wine known as Andoan wine was produced on Ando. It was the homeworld of Senator Po Nudo, the weapons manufacturer Amda Wabo, and the smuggler Ponda Baba.

title: Andooweel
paragraph: Andooweel was a world within the reaches of the galaxy.

title: Ankus
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'I-7'}}
paragraph: Ankus was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim.

title: Annaj
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Moddell sector', 'System': 'Annaj system', 'Trade routes': 'Spar Trade Route'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Annaj was an astronomical object in the Annaj system of the Outer Rim Territories' Moddell sector. Prior to the Battle of Endor in 4 ABY, Annaj was mapped as part of a Rebel Alliance report on the navigation of the Moddell sector by Corporal Ractivelle of Stardust unit in preparation for the Rebel Alliance's attack on the second Death Star.

title: Anoat
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Anoat sector', 'System': 'Anoat system', 'Moons': '1', 'Trade routes': ['Incisor Sidestep', 'Corellian Trade Spine']}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Polluted', 'Climate': 'Toxic', 'Primary terrain': 'Urban', 'Points of interest': ['Dissident base', 'Jedi shrine', 'Resistance Camp'], 'Fauna': ['Akk dog', 'Anoatian pit beast']}, 'Societal information': {'Demonym': 'Anoatian', 'Affiliation': ['Noble Court', 'Galactic Empire', 'Resistance']}}
paragraph: Anoat was a polluted planet located in the Anoat system of the Outer Rim Territories.

title: Anoth
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Wild Space', 'Grid coordinates': 'J-20'}}
paragraph: Anoth was an astronomical object located in the Wild Space region of the galaxy, positioned at the coordinates J-20 on the Standard Galactic Grid.

title: Ansion
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'I-6'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': 'Ansion Imperial base'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Ansion was a planet located in the galaxy's Mid Rim. A border dispute occurred on Ansion during the Separatist Crisis, which, along with turmoil on the planet Ando, was enough to stagger the galaxy. Ansion was connected via hyperspace route to the planets Keitum, Glee Anselm, Namadii, and Rago.

title: Antar
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Inner Rim', 'System': ['Prindaar system'], 'Moons': ['At least 4:', 'Antar 4', 'Dead Moon of Antar'], 'Grid coordinates': 'N-12'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Gas giant'}, 'Societal information': {'Demonym': 'Antarian'}}
paragraph: Antar was a gas giant located in the galaxy's Inner Rim, located in grid square N-12 on the Standard Galactic Grid, that was orbited by Antar 4, homeworld of the sentient Gotal species, and the Dead Moon of Antar.

title: Anteevy
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'P-7'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': 'Ice Station Beta'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Anteevy was an astronomical object located on the edge of the galaxy's Mid Rim. During the reign of the Galactic Empire, the Empire maintained a facility known as Ice Station Beta on Anteevy. When a group of dissidents stole the Imperial corvette Carrion Spike from Moff Wilhuff Tarkin and used it to attack Galidraan Station, Anteevy and its Imperial facility were considered as potential targets for the ship-jackers. They, along with Lantillies and a facility on Cartao, were listed as theoretical targets by Vice Admiral Dodd Rancit of Naval Intelligence when he was questioned on the situation by Galactic Emperor Sheev Palpatine.

title: Anx Minor
paragraph: Anx Minor was a location where a massacre occurred during the time of the New Republic. The massacre was among several events reviewed by New Republic Intelligence agent Caern Adan and Alphabet Squadron pilot Yrica Quell in search of the 204th Imperial Fighter Wing.

title: Anzat
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'R-7'}}
paragraph: Anzat was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim.

title: Aquaris
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-7'}}
paragraph: Aquaris was a planet located in the galaxy's Expansion Region. It and Thustra were the closest principal planets to the location of the stolen Imperial corvette Carrion Spike while it was at the location sector-designated as LCC-4-4-7. Aquaris had a notable criminal presence, and was located near the Perlemian Trade Route.

title: Arami
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'T-13', 'Trade routes': 'Triellus Trade Route'}}
paragraph: Arami was an Outer Rim Territories world located at galactic coordinates T-13. It was part of the Triellus Trade Route which connected it to the moon Syvris and the planet Gamorr.

title: Arbra
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': "Bon'nyuw-Luq sector", 'Grid coordinates': 'N-17'}}
paragraph: Arbra was an astronomical object located in the Bon'nyuw-Luq sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Arda
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Gordian Reach', 'Grid coordinates': 'Q-6'}}
paragraph: Arda was an astronomical object located in the Gordian Reach of the Outer Rim Territories, near the moon Yavin 4 of the same sector.

title: Argai Minor
side_bar: {'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Points of interest': 'Treinhaus Citadel'}, 'Societal information': {'Demonym': 'Argai'}}
paragraph: Argai Minor was a terrestrial planet. The Galactic Empire had forces within the Treinhaus Citadel on Argai Minor, and when the New Republic attacked the citadel, the Barma Battle Group sent Meteor Squadron, Hail Squadron, and Vanguard Squadron to support their ground forces.

title: Argazda
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-4'}}
paragraph: Argazda was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Aridus
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region', 'Grid coordinates': 'O-14'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Confederacy of Independent Systems'}}
paragraph: Aridus was a planet located in the galaxy's Expansion Region. During the Clone Wars, it was under Separatist control and Republic High Command sent at least one commando squad to Aridus in hopes of coordinating with local freedom fighters.

title: Aris
side_bar: {'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Humans'}}
paragraph: Aris was a rustic planet in the galaxy. It was the homeworld of Resistance member Byrco Hansid.

title: Arkania
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Colonies', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-8'}, 'Physical information': {'Climate': 'Cold', 'Fauna': 'Arkanian polar drake'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Arkanian', 'Major exports': 'Diamond'}}
paragraph: Arkania was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Colonies region, positioned at the coordinates M-8 on the Standard Galactic Grid. It shared its name with the creatures known as Arkanian dragons. In the weeks following the Battle of Endor, the New Republic was involved in a battle on Arkania that included ground-level fighting.

title: Arkanis
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Arkanis sector', 'System': 'Arkanis system', 'Suns': 'At least 2', 'Moons': 'At least 2'}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Climate': 'Rainy', 'Points of interest': ['Arkanis Academy', 'Scaparus Port']}, 'Societal information': {'Government': 'Regency Worlds', 'Demonym': 'Arkanisian', 'Affiliation': ['Galactic Empire', 'New Republic']}}
paragraph: Arkanis was a rainy planet in the Arkanis sector of the Outer Rim Territories, and the throneworld of Leeya, the Empress of the Regency Worlds. The Galactic Empire's officers academy was located there. It was also the homeworld of Armitage Hux, one of the key leading figures in the First Order.

title: Ashas Ree
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Primary terrain': 'Forests', 'Points of interest': ['Ashas Ree Temple of the Force', 'Sith Temple', 'Unidentified trading outpost'], 'Fauna': 'Parvinoth'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Sith'}}
paragraph: Ashas Ree was a forested planet located in the Outer Rim Territories. Its sole inhabited trading outpost was situated next to a Jedi temple that had been built to seal the power of a Sith temple beneath it. During the war between the First Order and the Resistance, traveller Mika Grey came to Ashas Ree seeking a relic hidden in the Sith temple, intending to keep it out of the First Order's hands, but became trapped inside the temple as a result until being released by Colossus resistance members Kazuda Xiono, CB-23, Eila and Kel two days later.

title: Asmeru
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': ['Mid Rim', 'Senex-Juvex'], 'Sector': 'Senex sector', 'Orbital period': 'At least sixteen months'}, 'Societal information': {'Primary language(s)': 'Unidentified Asmeru language'}}
paragraph: Asmeru was a planet located in the galaxy's Mid Rim. On the 234th day of the world's sixteenth month, the natives at one point celebrated a festival known as Q'anah in their language. The noble House Elegin were based on the planet, and during the reign of the Galactic Republic they hired a man from the planet Brentaal IV to oversee their security. The man's daughter fell in love with a young Elegin noble who secretly lived as a pirate, and when the daughter too took up piracy she began using the name Q'anah in honor of the Asmeru festival.

title: Ast Kikorie
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Moddell sector'}}
paragraph: Ast Kikorie was a location in the Moddell sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Prior to the Battle of Endor in 4 ABY, Ast Kikorie was documented by Corporal Ractivelle of the Stardust unit as part of a Rebel Alliance report on the navigation of the Moddell sector in preparation for the Rebel Alliance's attack on the second Death Star.

title: Atollon
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Lothal sector', 'System': 'Atollon system', 'Suns': '1: Ashbo', 'Moons': '1', 'Grid coordinates': 'U-7', 'Trade routes': 'Secret Phoenix Cell route', 'Rotation period': '29.5 standard hours', 'Orbital period': '505 standard days'}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Climate': 'Arid', 'Primary terrain': ['HistoricAncient seas', 'ModernCaverns', 'Coral formations', 'Rocks', 'Deserts', 'Mesas'], 'Surface water': 'Dry', 'Points of interest': ['Atollon Coral Mesa', 'Chopper Base', 'Atollon wastes', "Bendu's valley"], 'Fauna': ['Convor', 'Dokma', 'Krykna', 'Plated tree coral']}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': ['Human', 'Lasat', "Twi'lek"], 'Primary language(s)': 'Galactic Basic', 'Government': 'None', 'Population': ['438', '77% Human', "19% Twi'lek", '4% other'], 'Major cities': 'None', 'Major imports': ['Foodstuffs', 'Starships', 'Technology', 'Weaponry'], 'Major exports': 'None', 'Affiliation': ['Alliance to Restore the Republic', 'Phoenix Cell']}}
paragraph: Atollon was a remote planet in the Lothal sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It was known to the ancient peoples of the sector and was depicted in their artwork. The only known inhabitant was the Bendu, a mysterious Force wielder. In the third year before the Battle of Yavin, the rebels of Phoenix Cell established a base there after receiving intel from rebel astromech Chopper and AP-5, an inventory droid formerly in service to the Empire. Eventually, the rebels were forced to flee the planet after Grand Admiral Thrawn located their base and launched an attack which destroyed Chopper Base and killed many of the rebels.

title: Atravis
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-19', 'Trade routes': 'Hydian Way'}}
paragraph: Atravis was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories, located along the Hydian Way hyperspace route.

title: Attahox
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region', 'Grid coordinates': 'P-12'}}
paragraph: Attahox was an astronomical object in the galaxy's Expansion Region. It was connected to Mimban and Nanth'ri by a hyperspace route.

title: Atzerri
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Inner Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-13'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Gotal'}}
paragraph: Atzerri was a Gotal colony world in the galaxy's Inner Rim, located in grid square M-13 on the Standard Galactic Grid. In the year 22 BBY, tens of millions of Gotal refugees fled to Atzerri when their homeworld of Antar 4 fell to the Confederacy of Independent Systems shortly after the First Battle of Geonosis, the first battle of the Clone Wars.

title: Avidich
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Unknown Regions'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Chiss Ascendancy'}}
paragraph: Avidich was a planet of the Chiss Ascendancy, located in the Unknown Regions. After a majority of the population of the Chiss capital of Csilla were forced offworld by changes in the planet's climate, Avidich was one of the planets they were sent to.

title: Axxila
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'O-5'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Human'}}
paragraph: Axxila was a planet located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories that was the homeworld of Imperial Admiral Firmus Piett.

title: Azure
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'P-8'}}
paragraph: Azure was an astronomical object located in the Mid Rim of the galaxy. It was positioned at the coordinates P-8 on the Standard Galactic Grid.

title: Bacrana
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region', 'Grid coordinates': 'O-14', 'Trade routes': 'Corellian Run'}}
paragraph: Bacrana was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Expansion Region along the Corellian Run.

title: Bakura
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Wild Space', 'Grid coordinates': 'G-16'}, 'Societal information': {'Major cities': "Salis D'aar "}}
paragraph: Bakura was a planet located in the galaxy's Wild Space. It was connected to the planet Endor by a hyperspace route. At some point, the Resistance pilot Venisa Doza and her astromech droid Torch had an adventure on Bakura, which Doza brought up while attempting to plan her escape from the First Order Star Destroyer that had captured her starfighter.

title: Balamak
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'Q-9'}}
paragraph: Balamak was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim. Sometime before the Battle of Scarif, a battle was fought on Balamak, the battle was denoted by red lining on the garb of senator Vasp Vaspar. The population of Balamak was brutally suppressed by the New Republic according to the news feeds of the First Order. The stormtrooper FN-2187 saw one such broadcast in a morale session during his training shortly before his deployment to the planet Jakku.

title: Balmorra
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Colonies', 'System': 'Balmorra system', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-10'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Balmorra was an astronomical body located in the Balmorra system of the galaxy's Colonies region.

title: Balnab
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim'}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Climate': 'Temperate', 'Primary terrain': ['Rocky canyons', 'Swamps'], 'Points of interest': 'Balnab Spaceport', 'Flora': ["Dianoga's Kiss", 'Umbrella tree'], 'Fauna': ['Hesten', 'Tee-muss']}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Balnab', 'Government': 'Dictatorship', 'Affiliation': 'Neutral'}}
paragraph: Balnab was a temperate planet located in the Mid Rim, near Patitite Pattuna. During the Clone Wars, it served as a home to a group of alien castaways.

title: Balosar
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Core Worlds', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-12'}, 'Physical information': {'Primary terrain': 'Factories', 'Flora': 'Balo mushroom'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Balosar', 'Primary language(s)': 'Balosar', 'Major exports': 'Ixetal cilona', 'Affiliation': ['BioTech Industries', 'Fergriss Pharmaceuticals', 'Galactic Empire']}}
paragraph: Balosar was a ruined planet in the galaxy's Core Worlds that was the homeworld of the Balosar species. Balosar was known for its balo mushrooms, exclusive to the planet, which were refined by companies such as BioTech Industries and Fergriss Pharmaceuticals into ixetal cilona, a powerful narcotic used in death sticks and interrogation drugs.

title: Baltizaar
paragraph: Baltizaar was a world in the galaxy. When Princess Leia Organa traveled to the Paucris system to warn the fleet of an impending Imperial attack, she realized that traveling directly back to Coruscant might be risky, so she instead set a course for Baltizaar. Before she could leave Paucris, however, she discovered that Kier Domadi had traveled to the system aboard a cutter.

title: Bandomeer
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'O-6', 'Trade routes': ['Braxant Run', 'Hydian Way']}}
paragraph: Bandomeer was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories, at the junction of the Hydian Way and the Braxant Run.

title: Bannistar Station
side_bar: {'General information': {'Location': 'Mid Rim'}}
paragraph: Bannistar Station was a location in the Mid Rim of the galaxy, linked to Kalarba and Enarc by hyperspace routes. It was located at the coordinates O-15 on the Standard Galactic Grid.

title: Barab
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'U-12'}}
paragraph: Barab was an astronomical object in the Outer Rim Territories of the galaxy, connected to Teth and Dubrava via hyperspace routes. It was positioned at the coordinates U-12 on the Standard Galactic Grid.

title: Baradas
paragraph: Baradas was a location where the New Republic intelligence officer Nath Tensent once experienced a bad landing prior to the battle at Chadawa. The landing tore off the underside of Tensent's first Y-wing starfighter, as well as one of its nacelles.

title: Bardotta
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Colonies', 'Sector': 'Shasos sector', 'System': 'Bardotta system', 'Suns': '1', 'Moons': 'At least 1', 'Trade routes': 'Giju Run', 'Rotation period': '25 hours', 'Orbital period': '608 days'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Climate': 'Cold', 'Gravity': 'Slightly lower than average', 'Primary terrain': ['Mountains', 'Highlands', 'Plains', 'Ice caps'], 'Surface water': 'Oceans', 'Points of interest': ['Bardottan Royal Palace', 'Frangawl Temple', 'Halsoun Dagoyan Monastery']}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Bardottan', 'Primary language(s)': 'Bardottan language', 'Government': 'Bahk-tov Council', 'Population': ['900', '000', '000', '95% Bardottans', '5% Other'], 'Demonym': 'Bardottan', 'Major cities': ['Bardotta Capital City', 'Nan-gau', 'Shun-go', 'Jour-un', 'Feng-gau'], 'Major imports': ['Medicines', 'Technology'], 'Major exports': ['Art', 'Bardottan silk', 'Music', 'Sculpture'], 'Affiliation': ['Frangawl Cult', 'Dagoyan Order', 'Galactic Empire']}}
paragraph: Bardotta was a remote planet located in the Bardotta system of the Shasos sector of the the galaxy's Colonies region. Renowned for the art and music produced by the simple locals, the planet was ruled by a monarch who was guided in their decisions by the Dagoyan Order, a group reputed for their mysticism and attention to spiritual matters.

title: Baros
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'U-7'}}
paragraph: Baros was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories, positioned at the coordinates U-7 on the Standard Galactic Grid.

title: Bastion
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'K-3'}}
paragraph: Bastion was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Bavva
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Anoat sector'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': 'Imperial outpost'}}
paragraph: Bavva was a planet inside the Anoat sector in the the galaxy. Over several months during the Iron Blockade of the sector by the Galactic Empire, a merchant on Bavva was robbed several times. The merchant then offered payment for an experienced individual to provide them personal security.

title: Belasco
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region', 'Grid coordinates': 'O-11'}}
paragraph: Belasco was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Expansion Region.

title: Belderone
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'System': 'Belderone system', 'Grid coordinates': 'R-6'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': ['Belderone Imperial naval base', 'R/M Facility Four deepdock']}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Belderone was a planet located in the Outer Rim Territories. In the early days of the Galactic Empire, members of the Imperial Army were reluctant to be stationed on Belderone, as it was understood that the troops stationed the farthest from Imperial Center were of least importance to the Empire's cause. As such, virtually any reassignment to the planet was viewed as punishment or demotion.

title: Belkadan
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-1'}}
paragraph: Belkadan was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Bellassa
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Core Worlds', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-11', 'Trade routes': 'Hydian Way'}}
paragraph: Bellassa was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Core Worlds. It was connected via the Hydian Way hyperspace route to Skako and Fedalle.

title: Belnar
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Colonies', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-9'}}
paragraph: Belnar was an astronomical body located in the Colonies region at the coordinates M-9. Prior to 3 ABY, some insurrections occurred around Belnar, during of which Everi Chalis, an emissary to the Galactic Empire's ruling council, punished the crew of the starship Mandible over for accident, executing those responsible. Chalis later cited the Belnar Insurrections to the crew of an Imperial heavy freighter in 3 ABY, referencing the punishment of the Mandible's crew to threaten the freighter into changing course.

title: Belsavis
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': ['Mid Rim', 'Senex-Juvex'], 'Grid coordinates': 'L-18'}}
paragraph: Belsavis was an astronomical object located in the Senex-Juvex, a part of the galaxy's Mid Rim. It was connected via hyperspace route to Karfeddion. Thull's Shroud was near Belsavis.

title: Bendeluum
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Anoat sector'}}
paragraph: Bendeluum was a planet in the Anoat sector of the Outer Rim Territories. The independent Nothoiin cartel criminal organization was based there. At the time of the Iron Blockade, gang wars broke out across Bendeluum, which disrupted business and endangered citizens. In an attempt to protect their shops, some merchants offered crystals to individuals who would quell the violence.

title: Berchest
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Inner Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-8'}}
paragraph: Berchest was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Inner Rim. In 4 ABY, General Hera Syndulla led a New Republic strike at Berchest in hopes of capturing Imperial Yachts and securing useful data.

title: Berrol's Donn
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'K-19', 'Trade routes': 'Corellian Trade Spine'}}
paragraph: Berrol's Donn was an astronomical object in the Outer Rim Territories, situated on the Corellian Trade Spine.

title: Bescane
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'K-3'}}
paragraph: Bescane was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Bespin
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Anoat sector', 'System': 'Bespin system', 'Moons': '2', 'Grid coordinates': 'K-18', 'Distance from Core': ['49', '100 light-years'], 'Rotation period': '12 standard-hours', 'Orbital period': '14 standard-years'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Gas giant', 'Diameter': ['118', '000 kilometers'], 'Atmosphere': 'Breathable ', 'Primary terrain': 'Gaseous', 'Flora': 'Algae', 'Fauna': ['Air shrimp', 'Beldon', 'Crab glider', 'Rawwk', 'Velker']}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': ['Human', 'Ugnaught'], 'Primary language(s)': ['Galactic Basic', 'Ugnaught'], 'Population': ['6', '000', '000'], 'Demonym': 'Bespinite', 'Major cities': ['Chinook Station', 'Cloud City', 'Ugnorgrad'], 'Major exports': 'Tibanna', 'Affiliation': ['Galactic Empire', 'New Republic', 'First Order']}}
paragraph: Bespin was a gas giant in the star system of the same name. Forming a part of the Anoat sector, its riches manifested in the form of rare tibanna gas. Attracting mining interests and remaining unaffiliated in galactic affairs, Ugnaughts were employed to extract tibanna from repulsorlifted facilities whilst Bespin's mostly human population resided in the open upper levels, exposed to a thin layer of breathable atmosphere in an area known as the "Life Zone."

title: Bilbringi
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Inner Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'J-8'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': 'Bilbringi shipyards'}}
paragraph: Bilbringi was a world located in the galaxy's Inner Rim. It was home to the Bilbringi shipyards, a facility which dismantled the Separatist dreadnought Lucid Voice within a year after the end of the Clone Wars. The smuggler Han Solo was fond of Bilbringi food, and shared cheesy meat pies with pepper from Bilbringi with his wife, Leia Organa, at their home on Hosnian Prime twenty-four years after the Battle of Endor.

title: Bimmiel
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-4'}}
paragraph: Bimmiel was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Bimmisaari
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'R-9'}}
paragraph: Bimmisaari was an astronomical object in the galaxy's Mid Rim that was located on a hyperspace route between Charros IV and Boonta.

title: Birgis
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-3'}}
paragraph: Birgis was an astronomical object in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Bogden
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Inner Rim', 'Moons': 'Multiple', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-8', 'Trade routes': 'Hydian Way'}}
paragraph: Bogden was a planet located in the galaxy's Inner Rim on the Hydian Way that was orbited by multiple moons, one of which was the location where the Sith Lord Darth Tyranus secretly hired the bounty hunter Jango Fett to become the cloning template for the future Grand Army of the Republic.

title: Bomis Koori
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'K-16', 'Trade routes': 'Corellian Trade Spine'}}
paragraph: Bomis Koori was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim, situated on the Corellian Trade Spine.

title: Bonadan
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Corporate Sector', 'Grid coordinates': 'Q-4', 'Trade routes': 'Hydian Way'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Corporate Sector Authority'}}
paragraph: Bonadan was a planet in the Corporate Sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories, and the starting point of the Hydian Way. An embassy for Bonadan was located on the planet Coruscant.

title: Boonta
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'S-8'}}
paragraph: Boonta was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories, in grid square S-8 on the Standard Galactic Grid, that was connected to Bimmisaari, Junkfort Station, Klatooine, Sriluur, and Sy Myrth by a hyperspace route.

title: Boranda
paragraph: Boranda was a location within the Galactic Empire. It was apparently a desirable vacation spot, as when Merei Spanjaf made it up as a possible prize for a raffle on the spot, a woman purchased five tickets for the raffle.

title: Borgo Prime
side_bar: {'General information': {'Location': 'Outer Rim Territories'}}
paragraph: Borgo Prime was a shadowport in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. Located on the Hydian Way, the former pirate Queen Maz Kanata marked it on a map that she included in the book that would eventually become known as the Smuggler's Guide.

title: Borleias
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Colonies', 'System': 'Borleias system', 'Grid coordinates': 'K-9'}}
paragraph: Borleias was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Colonies region.

title: Borosk
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Prefsbelt sector', 'Grid coordinates': 'K-5'}}
paragraph: Borosk was an astronomical object located in the Prefsbelt sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Botajef
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Belsmuth sector', 'System': 'Botajef system', 'Grid coordinates': 'O-6', 'Trade routes': ['Hydian Way', 'Salin Corridor']}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': ["Governor's palace", 'North-polar base', 'South-polar base']}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Jefi', 'Immigrated species': 'Human', 'Government': 'Imperial governorship', 'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Botajef was a planet located in the Belsmuth sector of the Outer Rim Territories, at the confluence of the Salin Corridor and Hydian Way hyperspace routes. It was the homeworld of the Jefi species and the headquarters of Botajef Shipyards.

title: Bothawui
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Sector': 'Bothan Space', 'Moons': 'At least 1', 'Grid coordinates': 'R-14'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Gas giant'}}
paragraph: Bothawui was an asteroid fieldâringed gas giant located in the Bothan Space region of the galaxy's Mid Rim. Several of the individuals who taught the human Wilhuff Tarkin to fly starships originated on this world, despite the great distance between the world and the planet Eriadu where Tarkin lived. Bothawui was considered to be strategically important during the Clone Wars, leading to it being the site of the battle that halted a Separatist advance. Later in the war, around the time the Republic suffered a loss on Ryloth, Bothawui hosted another battle, though this engagement ended with many Galactic Republic losses. Many years later, Imperial resources were redirected from Bothawui by the Imperial Navy to help deal with Tarkin's corvette, Carrion Spike, after it was stolen by dissidents.

title: Botor
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Core Worlds', 'Grid coordinates': 'K-12'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': 'Flesh Mongers lair'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': "Lo's species", 'Major cities': 'Flesh Mongers city', 'Affiliation': 'Flesh Mongers'}}
paragraph: Botor was a planet located in the galaxy's Core Worlds that was home to the pirate faction known as the Flesh Mongers during the Republic Era. The youngling Lo was from Botor.

title: Boz Pity
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'System': 'Boz Pity system', 'Grid coordinates': 'S-9'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Confederacy of Independent Systems'}}
paragraph: Boz Pity was an planet located in the Boz Pity system of the galaxy's Mid Rim. A largely-uninhabited world, the Confederacy of Independent Systems established a presence on it during the Clone Wars, enabling them to frequently strike at nearby Republic targets. It was then subject to a siege by Republic forces; after the conclusion of the Siege of Saleucami during the Outer Rim Sieges, Jedi General Quinlan Vos moved his troops to support the siege.

title: Brentaal
side_bar: {'Technical specifications': {'Communication systems': 'Equipped'}, 'Usage': {'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire', 'Navy': 'Imperial Navy'}}
paragraph: The Brentaal was a starship used by the Imperial Navy during the Imperial Era. It shared its name with the Core world Brentaal IV. In 14 BBY, the vessel was attached to Rampart Station, an Imperial marshaling depot for supply ships bound for the planet Geonosis, where the Imperial battle station later known as the Death Star was being constructed.

title: Brigia
side_bar: {'General information': {'Location': 'Outer Rim Territories'}, 'Chronological and political information': {'Affiliation': 'Alliance to Restore the Republic'}}
paragraph: Brigia was a location in the galaxy that served as an Alliance to Restore the Republic regional headquarters and operations sector during the early rebellion against the Galactic Empire. Brigia was included in a map of the galaxy that listed safe worlds, starfighter hubs at level five or higher, regional headquarters and operations sectors, and deep space caches.

title: Broest
paragraph: Broest was a location from which ruica seeds were transported across the galaxy to the planet Alderaan for farmers to grow. When, during her childhood, Princess Leia Organa would not eat ruica, her adoptive father Bail Organa told her about the seeds being brought to Alderaan from Broest in order to convince her.

title: Bunduki
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'H-16'}}
paragraph: Bunduki was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Burnin Konn
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Anoat sector', 'System': 'Burnin Konn system'}, 'Physical information': {'Climate': 'Mostly uninhabitable', 'Primary terrain': 'Inhospitable', 'Points of interest': ['Carbon Score Cantina', "Drifter's Gorge", 'Konn-Nevos Spaceport', 'Longstar Marketplace']}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': ['Human', 'Nothoiin'], 'Major cities': ['Arcis', 'Ashheap'], 'Major exports': ['Chromium', 'Dolovite'], 'Affiliation': ['Noble Court', 'Galactic Empire', 'Uprising']}}
paragraph: Burnin Konn was a planet in the Anoat sector that served as a mining colony for chromium and other ores. The surface was almost entirely uninhabitable, with the planet's population being contained to areas like the Konn-Nevos Spaceport, Longstar Marketplace, and the Carbon Score Cantina. Imperial Governor Ubrik Adelhard's Iron Blockade of the Anoat sector forced the citizenry of Burnin Konn to resort to acquiring much-needed goods from local crime bosses. Three months after the Battle of Endor, Burnin Konn was one of dozens of worlds targeted by the remnants of the Empire during Operation: Cinder.

title: Byblos
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Colonies', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-12', 'Trade routes': ['Corellian Run', 'Herglic Alley']}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': 'University of Byblos'}}
paragraph: Byblos was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Colonies region that was situated along the Corellian Run. The former pirate Queen Maz Kanata marked it as the location of an outlaw garage on a map that she included in the book that became known as the Smuggler's Guide. Around 10 BBY, the crime lord Dryden Vos owned a storehouse on Byblos which contained items he had collected.

title: Byss
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Deep Core', 'Orbital position': 'K-11'}}
paragraph: Byss was an astronomical object located within the galaxy's Deep Core. It was connected via hyperspace route to Prakith.

title: Caamas
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Core Worlds', 'System': 'Cirius system', 'Moons': 'At least 2', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-9'}}
paragraph: Caamas was an astronomical body located in the Cirius system within the galaxy's Core Worlds.

title: Cadinth
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Tion Cluster', 'Grid coordinates': 'S-6'}}
paragraph: Cadinth was an astronomical object located in the Outer Rim Territories of the galaxy.

title: Caluula
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Tion Cluster', 'Grid coordinates': 'T-6'}}
paragraph: Caluula was an astronomical object in the Outer Rim Territories of the galaxy, within the Tion Cluster. It was positioned at the coordinates T-6 on the Standard Galactic Grid.

title: Cantonica
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Corporate Sector', 'System': 'Cantonica system', 'Moons': 'At least 2'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Primary terrain': 'Desert', 'Surface water': 'Artificial ocean', 'Points of interest': 'Sea of Cantonica', 'Flora': ['Cantonican cactus', 'Chinar tree'], 'Fauna': ['Fathier', 'Tentacled creature']}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': ['Bufopel', 'Caskadag', 'Cloddogran', 'Dor Namethian', 'Heptooinian', 'Human', 'Ongidae', 'Palandag', 'Suerton', 'Unidentified horse-like species', 'Unidentified species', 'Wermal', 'Whippomorn', "Xi'Dec"], 'Primary language(s)': 'Cantonican', 'Demonym': 'Cantonican', 'Major cities': ['Canto Bight']}}
paragraph: Cantonica was a desert planet in the Cantonica system within the Corporate Sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. The planet was home to the casino city Canto Bight, which was a destination for wealthy tourists, gamblers, and war profiteers. During the First Order/Resistance War in 34 ABY, the Resistance operatives Finn, Rose Tico, and BB-8 traveled to Cantonica on a mission to recruit the Master Codebreaker to disable the First Order's hyperspace tracker.

title: Cargamalis
paragraph: Cargamalis was a location in the galaxy. At some point prior to the Battle of Endor, Cargamalis was subjected to Street Wars, in which the human "Happy" Dapp and the Aqualish Bohento Splinth fought.

title: Carida
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Colonies', 'System': 'Carida system', 'Suns': '2', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-9'}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Primary terrain': 'Mountains', 'Points of interest': ['Carida Academy', 'Imperial Navy Deepdock Facility Two', 'Valor']}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Human', 'Demonym': 'Caridan', 'Affiliation': ['Galactic Republic', 'Grand Army of the Republic', 'Galactic Empire', 'Imperial Academy']}}
paragraph: Carida was a mountainous planet located in the Carida system within the Colonies region of the galaxy. During the Clone Wars, the Valor space station orbited the planet, while the era of the Galactic Empire saw Carida as home to an Imperial academy and a naval docking facility.

title: Carlac
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories'}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Climate': 'Cold', 'Primary terrain': ['Forests', 'Mountains', 'Snowy plains'], 'Points of interest': ['Carlac Death Watch camp', 'Ming Po town']}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Ming Po', 'Major cities': 'Ming Po town', 'Affiliation': 'Death Watch '}}
paragraph: Carlac was a peaceful, snow-covered planet in the Outer Rim Territories. A town inhabited by members of the Ming Po culture existed on the planet during the Clone Wars. However, that village was burned to the ground by the Death Watch, a radical Mandalorian terrorist group.

title: Carsanza
paragraph: Carsanza was the site of a skirmish prior to the Galactic Civil War. The Rebellion's tactics during the skirmish were later re-usedâalong with tactics from a skirmish at Nexatorâduring the pivotal Battle of Scarif.

title: Cartao
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': 'Cartao Imperial facility'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Cartao was a terrestrial body located in the Expansion Region upon which an Imperial facility was built. When a group of dissidents stole the Imperial corvette Carrion Spike from Moff Wilhuff Tarkin and used it to attack Galidraan Station in 14 BBY, Cartao and its Imperial facility were considered as potential targets for the ship-jackers. They, along with Lantillies and Ice Station Beta on Anteevy, were listed as theorized targets by Vice Admiral Dodd Rancit of Naval Intelligence when he was questioned on the situation by Galactic Emperor Sheev Palpatine.

title: Castell
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Colonies', 'System': 'Castell system', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-9', 'Trade routes': 'Perlemian Trade Route'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Gossam', 'Immigrated species': 'Human', 'Government': 'Imperial Governor', 'Affiliation': ['Commerce Guild', 'Confederacy of Independent Systems', 'Galactic Republic', 'Galactic Empire']}}
paragraph: Castell was a planet located in the Castell system of the Colonies, situated along the Perlemian Trade Route. The Commerce Guild had interests on Castell and their Presidente Shu Mai hailed from the planet. Castell sided with the Confederacy of Independent Systems during the Clone Wars during which it was defended by Diamond-class cruisers, Recusant-class Commerce Guild destroyers, as well as Commerce Guild Bombers and Commerce Guild corvettes. By the time of the Battle of Felucia during the Clone Wars final year, Castell had been captured by Republic forces. During the Galactic Civil War, it was a colony world of the Galactic Empire. It was ruled by its sector's Imperial Governor, Moff Ssaria.

title: Cathar
paragraph: Cathar was the homeworld of Scape Loewig, a Force-sensitive child whose name was included in a memory crystal recovered by Jedi Chief Librarian Jocasta Nu following Order 66.

title: Cathar
paragraph: Cathar was the homeworld of Scape Loewig, a Force-sensitive child whose name was included in a memory crystal recovered by Jedi Chief Librarian Jocasta Nu following Order 66.

title: Cato Neimoidia
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Colonies', 'Sector': 'Quellor sector', 'System': 'Cato Neimoidia system', 'Moons': 'At least 2', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-11'}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Primary terrain': ['Acidic oceans', 'Canyons', 'Cliffs', 'Grasslands', 'Forests', 'Rock arches'], 'Points of interest': ['Bridge cities', 'Great Vaults of Cato Neimoidia', "Reya's palace"]}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Neimoidian', 'Major cities': 'Tarko-se', 'Affiliation': ['Trade Federation', 'InterGalactic Banking Clan', 'Galactic Republic', 'Galactic Empire']}}
paragraph: Cato Neimoidia was a planet in the Cato Neimoidia system, within the Quellor sector of the galaxy's Colonies region. It was a wealthy colony world of the Neimoidians and the base of operations for the Trade Federation. Much of the world was covered in a persistent fog, while the bridge cities of Cato Neimoidia were suspended above the planet's acidic ocean surface on bridges anchored on massive giant rock arches, upon which thrived forests and grasslands.

title: Celanon
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'O-6', 'Trade routes': 'Hydian Way'}}
paragraph: Celanon was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories, situated along the Hydian Way which connected it to Junction and Botajef. It was home to the Astarte line. The Dressellian smuggler Has Obitt was arrested on Celanon for blockade running, but was bailed out by the Galactic Republic.

title: Celegia
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region', 'Grid coordinates': 'O-10'}}
paragraph: Celegia was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Expansion Region.

title: Centares
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'R-7', 'Trade routes': 'Perlemian Trade Route'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Centares was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim on the Perlemian Trade Route. Imperial capital ships were re-deployed from Centares in order to try and protect targets that the stolen Imperial corvette Carrion Spike might attack. Moff Wilhuff Tarkin, owner of the corvette, was informed of these re-deployments by the captain of the Star Destroyer Liberator.

title: Cerea
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'I-16'}, 'Physical information': {'Fauna': 'Aryx'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Cerean', 'Immigrated species': 'Human', 'Major cities': 'Asphodar 3'}}
paragraph: Cerea was a planet located in the galaxy's Mid Rim. It was a paradise largely unspoiled by the ravages of technology. It was the homeworld of the Cereans, including the Jedi Master Ki-Adi-Mundi, who served as a member of the Jedi High Council during the waning days of the Galactic Republic. Prior to being arrested on the Five Points system, Jyn Erso spent time bouncing around the Mid Rim on planets such as Cerea and Coyerti before settling on Takodana for almost a year. Cerea was home to big bipedal birds known as aryx, which the Rebel communications specialist Kidi Aleri rode.

title: Chalacta
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'R-10'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Chalactan', 'Affiliation': 'Galactic Republic'}}
paragraph: Chalacta was a planet located in the galaxy's Mid Rim. that was the homeworld of the Chalactan people. Jedi Master Depa Billaba was born on Chalacta. In the C.R.C. year 7941, Chalacta was represented in the Galactic Senate of the Galactic Republic by Yudrish Sedran.

title: Chalcedon
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Sector': 'Tashtor sector', 'Grid coordinates': 'I-16'}}
paragraph: Chalcedon was astronomical object located in the galaxy's the Tashtor sector within the Mid Rim. Located on a hyperspace route between Cerea and Takodana, it was the center of the galactic slave trade. Chalcedon also housed a shadowport and was marked on a map included by the former pirate Queen Maz Kanata in the book that became known as the Smuggler's Guide.

title: Champala
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Inner Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-8', 'Trade routes': 'Hydian Way'}, 'Physical information': {'Primary terrain': 'Seas'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Chagrian', 'Demonym': 'Champalan', 'Major cities': 'Tidros ', 'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Champala was a world in the galaxy's Inner Rim. Located on the Hydian Way, it was home to the Chagrian species, including Mas Amedda, Vice Chancellor of the Galactic Republic and later Grand Vizier of the Galactic Empire. A popular pastime on Champala was fishing, but, according to Amedda, by the Clone Wars its oceans were "not what they once were." Nevertheless, the human architect Orson Callan Krennic used such as an analogy to explain his plans for scientist Galen Walton Erso to Amedda. The world had its own embassy on Coruscant. It was occupied by the Galactic Empire.

title: Chandrila
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Core Worlds', 'Sector': 'Bormea sector', 'System': 'Chandrila system', 'Suns': '1', 'Moons': 'At least 1', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-9'}, 'Physical information': {'Primary terrain': 'Rolling hills', 'Surface water': 'Calm seas', 'Points of interest': ['Junari Point', 'Lake Andrasha', 'Sarini Island', 'Silver Sea'], 'Flora': ['Balmgrass', 'Cedar', 'Garren tree', 'Orcanthus', 'Tintolive tree'], 'Fauna': ['Bulabird', 'Marmal-fish', 'Pearlshell', 'Preepnob', 'Priprak', 'Skor-fin', 'Starleg']}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Human', 'Immigrated species': ['Jawa', 'Mon Calamari', 'Pantoran', 'Rodian', 'Trandoshan', "Twi'lek"], 'Demonym': 'Chandrilan', 'Major cities': 'Hanna City ', 'Affiliation': ['Galactic Republic', 'Galactic Empire', 'Alliance to Restore the Republic', 'New Republic']}}
paragraph: Chandrila was a planet in the Core Worlds of the galaxy. The female human Mon Mothma hailed from Chandrila, and represented her homeworld in the Senate of the Galactic Republic. It was also the homeworld and birthplace of Ben Solo.

title: Charra
side_bar: {'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial'}}
paragraph: Charra was a terrestrial astronomical object where Governor Tarkin of the Galactic Empire attended a trade conference.

title: Chazwa
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Inner Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-8', 'Trade routes': 'Perlemian Trade Route'}}
paragraph: Chazwa was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Inner Rim, along the Perlemian Trade Route. After the Battle of Endor, remnants of the Galactic Empire had a presence on Chazwa, and the New Republic's Meteor Squadron were sent on a scouting mission to Chazwa.

title: Cheelit
paragraph: Cheelit was the homeworld of brain crawlers, a species of parasitic worm that could infest happabores.

title: Chiron
side_bar: {'Biographical information': {'Died': ['4 BBY', 'Arkanis']}, 'Physical description': {'Species': 'Human', 'Gender': 'Male'}, 'Chronological and political information': {'Affiliation(s)': ['Galactic Empire', 'Imperial Military', 'Imperial Officer Corps']}}
paragraph: Chiron was a lieutenant of the Galactic Empire, stationed at the Academy for Young Imperials on Lothal. He was an enthusiastic officer who would often lead Imperial cadets in song during morning runs. Chiron took a special liking to one such cadet the Academy, Zare Leonis, believing him to be a fine example of a model officer and often tried to protect Leonis from the more officious bureaucrats within the Academy.

title: Cholganna
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories'}, 'Physical information': {'Primary terrain': 'Forests', 'Fauna': ['Bark rat', 'Nexu']}}
paragraph: Cholganna was a dark, cool forest planet in the Outer Rim Territories that was the homeworld of the nexus, a species of predatory felines that spread off-world as a result of their value as attack beasts.

title: Christophsis
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Savareen sector', 'System': 'Christoph system', 'Suns': "1: Christophsis' sun", 'Moons': '1: Leesis', 'Grid coordinates': 'Q-16', 'Trade routes': 'Corellian Run'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Primary terrain': 'Crystalline formations', 'Points of interest': ['Christophsis double-towered building', 'Christophsis Republic base', 'Christophsis Separatist headquarters', 'Christophsis Separatist tower', 'Crystal forest', 'Eastern exurbs'], 'Fauna': 'Kyaddak'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': ['Human', 'Christophsian'], 'Demonym': 'Christophsian', 'Major cities': ['Chaleydonia', 'Tophen'], 'Major exports': 'Kyber crystals', 'Affiliation': ['Galactic Republic', 'Galactic Empire']}}
paragraph: Christophsis was a planet located in the Christoph system of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories where the Battle of Christophsis was fought during the Clone Wars. The crystalline planet was invaded by the battle droid armies of the Confederacy of Independent Systems but were repelled by the Jedi and Clone troopers dispatched by the Galactic Republic. Later, the planet was the site of a second battle between the Republic and the Separatists. After the transformation of the Galactic Republic into the Galactic Empire, the planet was placed under Imperial control, but nevertheless hosted rebellious elements.

title: Circumtore
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Hutt Space', 'Grid coordinates': 'S-12'}}
paragraph: Circumtore was a world located in the Hutt Space region of the galaxy. It was connected to fellow Hutt Space worlds Rorak, Nar Kaaga and Hollastin by hyperspace routes as well as Daalang outside of the region. Circumtore was located at galactic coordinates S-12.

title: Ciutric
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-5'}}
paragraph: Ciutric was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Codia
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Moons': 'Codian Moon', 'Grid coordinates': 'H-15'}, 'Societal information': {'Demonym': 'Codian'}}
paragraph: Codia was a planet located in the galaxy's Mid Rim, in grid square H-15 on the Standard Galactic Grid, that was orbited by the Codian Moon, a homeworld of the reek species. It shared its name with the location New Codia.

title: Colla IV
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Inner Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-9'}, 'Physical information': {'Fauna': 'Toothspike raptor'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Colicoid', 'Major exports': 'Droidekas'}}
paragraph: Colla IV was a planet located in the galaxy's Inner Rim, in grid square N-9 on the Standard Galactic Grid where droidekas were manufactured by the Colicoids, while the droid tri-fighter's three-armed design mimicked the skull features of one of its ferocious predators.

title: Columex
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'R-6', 'Trade routes': ['Perlemian Trade Route', 'Salin Corridor']}}
paragraph: Columex was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories along the Perlemian Trade Route and the Salin Corridor.

title: Columus
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Core Worlds', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-12'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Columi'}}
paragraph: Columus was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Core Worlds which was the homeworld of the Columi.

title: Commenor
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Colonies', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-10'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'New Republic'}}
paragraph: Commenor was a planet located in the Colonies region of the galaxy.

title: Comra
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Wild Space', 'Grid coordinates': 'J-5'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'New Republic'}}
paragraph: Comra was an astronomical object located in Wild Space that was represented in the New Republic Senate by the Centrist Mortan in 28 ABY.

title: Cona
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Inner Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'O-11'}, 'Physical information': {'Primary terrain': 'Desert'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Arcona'}}
paragraph: Cona was a desert planet located in the galaxy's Inner Rim that was the homeworld of the Arcona species. Hem Dazon, a male Arcona frequently spent time in the Mos Eisley cantina after becoming stranded on Tatooine. He was unable to return to his home planet because he had spent all his credits on salt and juri juice.

title: Concord Dawn
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Mandalore sector', 'System': 'Concord Dawn system', 'Moons': ['At least 3', 'Third moon of Concord Dawn']}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Human', 'Affiliation': ['Mandalorians', 'Galactic Empire']}}
paragraph: Concord Dawn was a planet located in the Concord Dawn system, within the Mandalore sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. The planet was devastated during one of the hundreds of wars it suffered, with roughly a third of its mass blasted out as asteroid-sized debris in its planetary orbit. During the Age of the Empire, Concord Dawn was ruled by the Mandalorian Protectors, under the leadership of Fenn Rau. Concord Dawn was also famous as the homeworld of many elite warriors, including the bounty hunter Rako Hardeen and the Mandalorian warrior and foundling Jango Fett.

title: Constancia
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Deep Core', 'Grid coordinates': 'K-12'}}
paragraph: Constancia was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Deep Core.

title: Contruum
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region', 'Grid coordinates': 'O-8'}}
paragraph: Contruum was an astronomical object in the galaxy's Expansion Region. Angilar Bosh, who created the Galactic Republic propaganda poster Strength and Unity, was an art director for a leading Contruum advertising agency.

title: Corbett Cluster
side_bar: {'General information': {'Location': 'Corbett sector'}}
paragraph: The Corbett Cluster was a location in the Corbett sector.

title: Corellia
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Core Worlds', 'Sector': 'Corellian sector', 'System': 'Corellia system', 'Suns': ['1:', 'Corell'], 'Moons': ['At least 2:', "Corellia's nearest moon"], 'Grid coordinates': 'M-11', 'Trade routes': ['Corellian Run', 'Corellian Trade Spine'], 'Rotation period': '25 standard hours', 'Orbital period': '329 standard days'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Diameter': ['11', '000 kilometers'], 'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Climate': 'Temperate', 'Primary terrain': ['Forests', 'Jungles', 'Oceans', 'Industrial urban'], 'Points of interest': ['Gilded Descent Casino', 'Imperial training center', 'Navigation institute', 'Santhe shipyards'], 'Flora': 'Tree', 'Fauna': ['Bluevev glider', 'Coppergrin', 'Corellian hound', 'Fleek eel', 'Garsmelt', 'Lancepyke', 'Needlegawp', 'Pulsar skate', 'Scalefin fish']}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': ['Human', 'Corellian'], 'Immigrated species': ['Barbadelan', 'Besalisk', 'Czerialan', 'Grindalid', 'Kel Dor', "Pa'lowick", 'Rodian', 'Sullustan', "Twi'lek", 'Ugor'], 'Population': '3 billion', 'Demonym': 'Corellian', 'Major cities': ['Coronet City', 'Kor Vella', 'Tyrena', 'Bela Vistal', 'Doaba Guerfel'], 'Major exports': 'Starships', 'Affiliation': ['Galactic Republic', 'Galactic Empire', 'New Republic', 'First Order']}}
paragraph: Corellia was a planet located in the galaxy's Core Worlds known for its ace pilots and large starships. Vessels such as the Millennium Falcon and Imperial starships were built on Corellia.

title: Corsin
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-7', 'Trade routes': 'Hydian Way'}}
paragraph: Corsin was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Expansion Region situated along the Hydian Way. The luxury liner Stellar Vista departed from Corsin before being pulled out of hyperspace in the Obroa-skai system as part of an attempt by the Galactic Empire to capture the stolen Imperial corvette Carrion Spike.

title: Corulag
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Core Worlds'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': ['Corulag Academy', 'Crullov']}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Human', 'Major cities': 'Curamelle', 'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Corulag was the home planet of Baron Lero Danthe. Merei Spanjaf played kicker in the youth bracket of grav-ball on this planet.

title: Coruscant
