side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Core Worlds', 'Sector': ['Corusca sector', 'Coruscant subsector'], 'System': 'Coruscant system', 'Suns': '1: Coruscant Prime', 'Moons': ['4', 'Centax 3'], 'Grid coordinates': 'L-9', 'XYZ coordinates': ['0', '0', '0'], 'Trade routes': ['Corellian Run', 'Metellos Trade Route', 'Namadii Corridor', 'Nexus Route', 'Perlemian Trade Route'], 'Rotation period': '24 standard hours', 'Orbital period': '365 standard days'}, 'Physical information': {'Diameter': ['12', '240 kilometers'], 'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Climate': 'Temperate ', 'Primary terrain': 'Ecumenopolis', 'Points of interest': ['Bureau of Ships and Services Heritage Museum', 'Federal District', '500 Republica', 'Galactic Courts of Justice', 'Jedi Temple/Imperial Palace', 'Republic Center for Military Operations/Naval Intelligence headquarters', 'Galactic Senate Building', 'Senate Office Building/Imperial Executive Building', 'Grand Republic Medical Facility', 'Lower market districts', 'Monument Plaza', 'Museum of Multispecies Sciences', 'Port Quarter', 'Eastern spaceport', 'Western spaceport', 'Republic Judiciary Central Detention Center', 'Republic Science and Technical Center', 'The Underworld', 'Uscru District', 'Galaxies Opera House', 'Outlander Club', 'The Works', 'Verity District', 'Hall of Imperial Register'], 'Fauna': 'Granite slug'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': ['Human'], 'Immigrated species': ['Besalisk', 'Balosar', 'Cerean', 'Nautolan', 'Iktotchi', 'Iridonian', 'Kel Dor', 'Lannik', 'Quermian', 'Tholothian', 'Togruta', "Yoda's species"], 'Primary language(s)': ['Galactic Basic', 'Thousands of others'], 'Government': ['Galactic Senate', 'Coruscanti government', 'Coruscant provisional government'], 'Population': ['Trillions', 'Over 50% humans'], 'Demonym': 'Coruscanti', 'Major cities': ['CoCo Town', 'Imperial City'], 'Affiliation': ['Galactic Republic', 'Jedi Order', 'Sith Order', 'Galactic Empire', 'New Republic', 'First Order']}}
paragraph: Coruscant , also known as Imperial Center during the rule of the Galactic Empire, was an ecumenopolisâa city-covered planet, collectively known as Imperial Cityâ in the Coruscant system of the Core Worlds. Though debated by historians, it was generally believed that Coruscant was the original homeworld of humanity. Noted for its cosmopolitan culture and towering skyscrapers, Coruscant's population consisted of approximately one trillion citizens hailing from a vast array of both humanoid and alien species. In addition, Coruscant's strategic location at the end of several major trade routes enabled it to grow in power and influence, causing the city-planet to surpass its early rivals and become the hub of galactic culture, education, finance, fine arts, politics and technology. It was the location of several major landmarks, including the Jedi Temple, Monument Plaza and the Senate Building.

title: Cotellier
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-20'}}
paragraph: Cotellier was an astronomical object in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Crait
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'System': 'Crait system', 'Suns': '1: Crait', 'Orbital position': 'First planet from the sun', 'Moons': '0', 'Rotation period': '27 standard hours', 'Orbital period': '525 standard days'}, 'Physical information': {'Diameter': ['7', '400 kilometers'], 'Atmosphere': ['Breathable', 'Oxygen', 'Nitrogen'], 'Climate': 'Temperate', 'Primary terrain': ['Briny seas', 'Canyons', 'Mountains', 'Salt flats'], 'Surface water': 'Waterways', 'Points of interest': ['Crait outpost', 'Mines of Crait', 'Nupayuni salt flats'], 'Fauna': 'Vulptex'}, 'Societal information': {'Population': 'Uninhabited', 'Major exports': ['Minerals', 'Rhodochrosite', 'Salt', 'Sodium'], 'Affiliation': ['Alliance to Restore the Republic', 'Resistance']}}
paragraph: Crait was a small salty mineral planet located in a remote sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. Covered with a layer of white salt over its red soil, the planet once hosted a Rebel Alliance outpost during their early rebellion against the Galactic Empire. Many years later, the uninhabited planet became a haven for Leia Organa's Resistance, which resulted in a battle between the Resistance and the First Order on the planet's surface.

title: Csilla
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Unknown Regions', 'System': 'Csilla system', 'Suns': '1', 'Grid coordinates': 'F-8'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Climate': 'Cold', 'Primary terrain': 'Ice-locked'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Chiss', 'Population': ['8 billion', '60-70 million', '4 billion'], 'Major cities': 'Csaplar ', 'Affiliation': 'Chiss Ascendancy'}}
paragraph: Csilla was a frigid, ice-locked planet in the Unknown Regions. It was the homeworld of the sentient Chiss species and a part of the Chiss Ascendancy. Though largely unknown to the wider galaxy during the age of the Galactic Empire, exploratory missions to the Unknown Regions conducted years later revealed Csilla and other worlds that could be reached through cautious hyperspace jumps.

title: Cularin
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region', 'Grid coordinates': 'P-14'}}
paragraph: Cularin was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Expansion Region. During the Clone Wars, a battle was fought there, during which the lead Maelstrom-class battle cruiser, Maelstrom, served with distinction under the command of Jedi General Darrus Jeht.

title: Cyborrea
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Hutt Space', 'Grid coordinates': 'S-9'}}
paragraph: Cyborrea was an astronomical object located in the Outer Rim Territories, within Hutt Space. It was positioned at the coordinates S-9 on the Standard Galactic Grid.

title: Cyphar
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-17'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': ['Afe clan meetinghouse', 'Hollenside Enclave', "Unidentified Twi'lek settlement"]}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Cyphari', 'Government': ['Afe clan', 'Cyphar government']}}
paragraph: Cyphar was a planet located in the galaxy's Mid Rim that was the homeworld of the Cyphari species.

title: Cyrillia
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region', 'Grid coordinates': 'O-12'}}
paragraph: Cyrillia was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Expansion Region.

title: D'Qar
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Sanbra sector', 'System': 'Ileenium system', 'Suns': '1: Ileenium', 'Moons': '2', 'Grid coordinates': 'O-17', 'Orbital period': '415 days'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Diameter': ['10', '400 kilometers'], 'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Climate': 'Temperate', 'Primary terrain': ['Jungle', 'Plains', 'Forest canopies'], 'Points of interest': 'Resistance base', 'Flora': ['Trees', 'Creepervine'], 'Fauna': ['Castua crane', 'Dragonflies', 'Dressto', 'Insects', 'Sonar swallow', 'Squonk', 'Stinging midge', 'Unidentified lizard']}, 'Societal information': {'Population': 'None', 'Affiliation': ['Alliance to Restore the Republic', 'Resistance']}}
paragraph: D'Qar was a verdant planet located in the Ileenium system of the Outer Rim Territories. By the thirtieth year after the formation of the New Republic, the planet was the location of the headquarters of the Resistance, a small military force formed by Senator Leia Organa to combat the growing threat of the First Order, a successor state to the Galactic Empire.

title: Daalang
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'System': 'Daalang system', 'Grid coordinates': 'Q-12'}}
paragraph: Daalang was an astronomical object located in the Daalang system of the Mid Rim.

title: Dagobah
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Sluis sector', 'System': 'Dagobah system', 'Moons': '0', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-19', 'Trade routes': 'Rimma Trade Route', 'Distance from Core': ['50', '250 light-years'], 'Rotation period': '23 hours', 'Orbital period': '341 days'}, 'Physical information': {'Diameter': ['14', '410 kilometers'], 'Atmosphere': ['Violent lightning storms', 'dense fog'], 'Climate': ['Hot and humid', 'Periods of torrential rainfalls'], 'Primary terrain': ['Bayous', 'Swamp', 'Bogs', 'Jungles', 'Dry uplands'], 'Points of interest': ['Cave of Evil', 'Dragonsnake Bog', 'Mount Dagger', "Yoda's Hut"], 'Flora': ['Blackvine', 'Gnarltree', 'Herbs', 'Lahdia plant', 'Stickle Tree', 'Swamp squash', 'Yarum seed', 'Yoghurt plant'], 'Fauna': ['Accipiptero', 'Bogwing', 'Greater Bogwing', 'Lesser Bogwing', 'Butcherbug', 'Dagobah python', 'Dragonsnake', 'Elephoth', 'Flying leaf-tail', 'Jubba bird', 'Pikobi', 'Posenaur', 'Scrange', 'Silver-nape beetle', 'Sleen', 'Smooka', 'Spiny bograt', 'Spotlight sloth', 'Swamp slug', 'Vine snake']}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Tash', 'Immigrated species': "Yoda's species", 'Population': 'At least 1: Yoda'}}
paragraph: Dagobah was a planet in the Dagobah system, and one of the purest places in the galaxy within the Force. A remote world of swamps and forests, it served as a refuge for Jedi Grand Master Yoda during his exile after the destruction of the Jedi Order. Luke Skywalker received advanced training in the ways of the Force under Jedi Master Yoda on Dagobah, and it was later the place of Yoda's death and transformation into the Force.

title: Daluuj
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'U-13'}}
paragraph: Daluuj was an astronomical object located in the Outer Rim Territories of the galaxy, positioned at the coordinates U-13 on the Standard Galactic Grid.

title: Dankayo
side_bar: {'General information': {'Location': 'Colonies'}, 'Chronological and political information': {'Affiliation': 'Alliance to Restore the Republic '}}
paragraph: Dankayo was a location in the galaxy's Colonies that was a suspected base of rebel operations. Dankayo and several other locations were identified in a 3 ABY Imperial Security Bureau report that generated targets for Viper probe droid surveys by cross-referencing areas with a high degree of suspicious activity with the unsettled parts of the galaxy favored by the rebels.

title: Dantooine
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Raioballo sector', 'System': 'Dantooine system', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-4', 'Trade routes': "Myto's Arrow"}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Primary terrain': 'Lush forests and green landscapes', 'Points of interest': ['Dantooine base', 'Jedi Temple']}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Humans', 'Demonym': 'Dantooinian', 'Major cities': 'Dantoo Town', 'Affiliation': ['Jedi Order', 'Galactic Republic', 'Alliance to Restore the Republic', 'First Order']}}
paragraph: Dantooine was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories within the Galactic Republic and later the Galactic Empire.

title: Dargulli
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Inner Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-14'}}
paragraph: Dargulli was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Inner Rim.

title: Darkknell
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-17', 'Trade routes': 'Hydian Way'}}
paragraph: Darkknell was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories that was situated along the Hydian Way. The Rebel Alliance intelligence officer Cassian Jeron Andor acted under the alias "Aach" as a senatorial contact on Darkknell.

title: Darlyn Boda
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Anoat sector'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': 'Darlyn Boda Shadowpor'}}
paragraph: Darlyn Boda was a planet in the Anoat sector of the Outer Rim Territories. During the Galactic Empire's Iron Blockade, Darlyn Boda had a criminal network which included the Trade Spine League and the Ivax Syndicate.

title: Dasoor
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim'}}
paragraph: Dasoor was a planet located in the Mid Rim region of the galaxy. It was known as a world overrun by thieves, and gangs of slavers. Some months after the Battle of Endor, the smuggler Han Solo and his Wookiee co-pilot Chewbacca were headed to this planet, before changing course to the Wookiee's home planet of Kashyyyk.

title: Datar
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Inner Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-8'}}
paragraph: Datar was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Inner Rim.

title: Dathomir
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Quelli sector', 'System': 'Dathomir system', 'Suns': '1', 'Moons': 'At least 2', 'Grid coordinates': 'O-6', 'Trade routes': 'None', 'Rotation period': '24 hours', 'Orbital period': '491 days'}, 'Physical information': {'Diameter': ['10', '460 kilometers'], 'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Climate': 'Temperate', 'Primary terrain': ['Canyons', 'Caves', 'Cliffs', 'Forests', 'Hills', 'Jungles', 'Mountains', 'Rivers', 'Swamps', 'Waterfalls', 'Valleys'], 'Points of interest': ["Brother's Bastion", 'Cliffside Fortress', 'Collapsed Settlement', 'Dreaming River', 'Great Canyon', 'Halls of the Nydak', 'Hidden Cave', 'Misty Falls', 'Nardithi Cluster', 'Nightbrother arena', 'Nightbrother Dungeon', 'Nightmare Ruins', 'Red Hills', 'Singing Mountain', 'Strangled Cliffs', 'Upper Strangled Cliffs', 'Swamp of Sacrifice', 'Unidentified Nightbrother arena', 'The Haunted Lands', 'The Oteroan Sky crash site', 'Tomb of Kujet', 'Treacherous Approach', 'Witches Horn'], 'Flora': ['Brula fruit', 'Bleeding Gut', 'Blue coral', 'Fire lichen', 'Fungus', 'Grave Thorn', 'Hydraatis', 'Mushling'], 'Fauna': ['Bane back spider', 'Belonuk', 'Burra fish', 'Chirodactyl', 'Lizard', 'Nydak', 'Nydak Alpha', 'Rancor', 'The Sleeper', 'Snake', 'Sprantal', 'Veeka', 'Vursonk']}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': ['Dathomirian', 'Fromprath'], 'Immigrated species': ['Human', 'Zabrak', 'Zeffo', 'Toydarian'], 'Primary language(s)': ['Paecian', 'Dathomirian language', 'Galactic Basic'], 'Government': 'Tribal', 'Population': ['Roughly 600', '90% human', '7% Zabrak', '3% other'], 'Demonym': 'Dathomirian', 'Major cities': ['Nightsister lair', 'Nightbrother village', 'Oteroa Zero-Twenty', 'Unidentified Nightbrother village'], 'Major exports': 'Ore', 'Affiliation': ['Nightsisters', 'Galactic Republic', 'Confederacy of Independent Systems', 'Shadow Collective', 'Crimson Dawn', 'Galactic Empire']}}
paragraph: Dathomir, nicknamed the "rancor planet," was a remote, neutral planet in the Quelli sector and the home of the Nightsisters, Nightbrothers, Blue Coral Divers Clan, Singing Mountain, and the Howling Crag. The planet, bathed in blood-red light by its central star, had numerous continents that were overrun with vegetation, forests, and swamplands. The dark side of the Force had an immensely strong presence on Dathomir, which allowed for the nurturing of many malevolent Force wielders native to the planet. The Nightsisters, also known as the Dathomir witches, made their home in the swamps, and wielded magicks fueled by Dathomir's own power. Dathomir was also home to the Nightbrothers, Zabraks who were ruled by the Nightsisters. It was also the homeworld of the semi-sentient rancor species.

title: Daupherm
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Core Worlds', 'Grid coordinates': 'K-12'}}
paragraph: Daupherm was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Core Worlds.

title: Dela
side_bar: {'Biographical information': {'Died': ['During or prior to c. 4 ABY']}, 'Physical description': {'Gender': 'Female'}}
paragraph: Dela was a female who was the sister of Lindon Javes. At some point, she was killed during hazardous maneuvers. By around 4 ABY, she was mentioned on Javes' Imperial record.

title: Delacrix
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'T-9'}}
paragraph: Delacrix was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Dellalt
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Tion Cluster', 'Grid coordinates': 'T-6'}}
paragraph: Dellalt was an astronomical object in the Tion Cluster, within the Outer Rim Territories of the galaxy. It was positioned at the coordinates T-6 on the Standard Galactic Grid.

title: Delphon
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Anoat sector'}, 'Societal information': {'Major cities': 'Delphon City', 'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Delphon was a planet in the Anoat sector of the Outer Rim Territories. During the Galactic Empire's Iron Blockade, the criminal Trade Spine League wanted to quietly move a shipment of crystals from the planet Burnin Konn to Delphon, but had to first deal with the Black Hole Gang. At another point during the blockade, an anonymous party hired a young smuggler to break into Delphon's senatorial compound and convince one of the aides to secretly work against the Empire. One notable settlement on Delphon was Delphon City, which housed at least one cantina, at least one docking bay, and Cage's Tech Emporium.

title: Delrakkin
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'K-21'}}
paragraph: Delrakkin was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Dennogra
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'S-8'}}
paragraph: Dennogra was an astronomical object in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories, connected via hyperspace route to Junkfort Station and Taskeed.

title: Denon
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Inner Rim', 'System': 'Denon system', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-13', 'Trade routes': ['Corellian Run', 'Hydian Way']}, 'Physical information': {'Primary terrain': 'Urban', 'Points of interest': ['House Vahali cloudcutter', "Sakhet's Noodles"]}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Human', 'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Denon was a planet located in the Denon system of the galaxy's Inner Rim, at the confluence of the Corellian Run and the Hydian Way. An ecumenopolis world, it had city growth covering the entire surface, similar to Coruscant. It was the homeworld of Imperial General Maximilian Veers and the Rebel pilot Pedrin Gaul.

title: Dentaal
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Core Worlds', 'Grid coordinates': 'K-13', 'Trade routes': 'Rimma Trade Route'}}
paragraph: Dentaal was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Core Worlds along the Rimma Trade Route.

title: Derra
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-15'}}
paragraph: Derra was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Expansion Region.

title: Desevro
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Tion Cluster', 'Grid coordinates': 'S-6', 'Trade routes': 'Perlemian Trade Route'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Desevro was an astronomical object located in the Tion Cluster of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. It was also located on the Perlemian Trade Route. It was contested territory during the Galactic Civil War.

title: Devaron

paragraph: Devaron was a terrestrial planet located in the Devaron system of the galaxy's Colonies that was the homeworld of the Devaronian species.

title: Dolla
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': ['Mid Rim', 'Senex-Juvex'], 'Grid coordinates': 'L-18'}}
paragraph: Dolla was an astronomical object located in the Senex-Juvex, a part of the galaxy's Mid Rim. It was connected via hyperspace route to Karfeddion.

title: Dorin
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region', 'Grid coordinates': 'J-8'}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Dorin gas and helium'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Kel Dor'}}
paragraph: Dorin was a planet located in the galaxy's Expansion Region that was the homeworld of the Kel Dor species. Its Dorin gas and helium-rich environment meant that they were forced to rely on rebreathers to survive off-world, as oxygen was deadly to them. During the Clone Wars, Jedi General Anakin Skywalker and Commander Ahsoka Tano routed Separatist forces near Dorin.

title: Dornea
side_bar: {'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Dornean', 'Affiliation': 'Alliance to Restore the Republic'}}
paragraph: Dornea was the homeworld of the Dornean species. The native species designed the Braha'tok-class gunship, which were manufactured by the Dornean Braha'ket Fleetworks Conglomerate to protect Dornea from the Galactic Empire Some of these gunships saw service with the Rebel Alliance during the early rebellion against the Empire. After the Alliance secured a decisive victory at the Battle of Yavin, Dornea joined their cause and brought more Braha'tok-class gunships with them.

title: Dorvalla
paragraph: Dorvalla was a celestial body where the Rebel Alliance's 61st Mobile Infantry recruited a number of new soldiers at some point by the year 0 BBY. The company's Captain Micha Evon soon noticed that the soldier Brand, who was secretly a bounty hunter, lingered around those new recruits. Evon cited this when Brand attempted to take a bounty on the captain during a battle on the planet Allst Prime. He mentioned his point about the recruits from Dorvalla while trying to convince Brand to stay with the 61st.

title: Drearia
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Inner Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-8', 'Trade routes': 'Hydian Way'}}
paragraph: Drearia was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Inner Rim that was situated along the Hydian Way.

title: Dressel
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'Q-13'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Dressellian'}}
paragraph: Dressel was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim that was the homeworld of the Dressellian species.

title: Drexel
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Orbital position': 'Q-18'}, 'Societal information': {'Demonym': 'Drexelian'}}
paragraph: Drexel was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories, positioned at the coordinates Q-18 on the Standard Galactic Grid. The astronomical object was associated with individuals known as Drexelian shell-diggers, who often dressed in ragged clothing.

title: Drongar
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'T-5'}}
paragraph: Drongar was an astronomical object located in the Outer Rim Territories of the galaxy, positioned at the coordinates T-5 on the Standard Galactic Grid.

title: Druckenwell
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'P-15', 'Trade routes': 'Corellian Run'}}
paragraph: Druckenwell was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim along the Corellian Run.

title: Dubrava
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'T-13'}}
paragraph: Dubrava was an astronomical object in the Outer Rim Territories of the galaxy, linked via hyperspace routes to Barab and Syvris, and positioned at the coordinates T-13 on the Standard Galactic Grid.

title: Dubrillion
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'K-3'}}
paragraph: Dubrillion was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Dulathia
paragraph: Dulathia was the homeworld of Kaydel Ko Connix, a human lieutenant of the Resistance.

title: Durkteel
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'System': 'Durkteel system', 'Suns': '1', 'Moons': 'At least 2'}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Points of interest': ['Orphan farm', 'Phirmist temple', 'Tak-Beam complex'], 'Flora': 'Hemmel', 'Fauna': 'Tawd'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Saurin', 'Immigrated species': ['Cerean', 'Human', 'Skup', 'Snivvian'], 'Government': 'Planetary governor', 'Major cities': ['Lund Berlo', 'Lund Gourley'], 'Affiliation': ['Galactic Empire', 'Alliance to Restore the Republic', 'Saurin resistance']}}
paragraph: Durkteel was a agricultural planet located in the galaxy's Mid Rim that was the homeworld of the reptilian Saurin species. Durkteel was also the homeworld of Mattis Banz, a Force-sensitive human who joined the Resistance. Lund Gourley and Lund Berlo were cities located on Durkteel.

title: Duro
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Core Worlds', 'Sector': 'Duro sector', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-11', 'Trade routes': 'Corellian Trade Spine'}, 'Physical information': {'Climate': 'Temperate'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Duros', 'Demonym': 'Durosian', 'Major cities': 'Unidentified satellite city', 'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Duro was a temperate planet located in the Duro sector of the galaxy's Core Worlds that was the homeworld of the Duros species.

title: Eadu
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Bheriz sector', 'System': 'Eadu system', 'Moons': '1', 'Grid coordinates': 'U-10', 'Trade routes': 'Triellus Trade Route'}, 'Physical information': {'Diameter': ['14', '121 km'], 'Climate': 'Stormy', 'Primary terrain': 'Rocky', 'Points of interest': ['Eadu Energy Conversion Laboratory', 'Eadu Flight Station']}, 'Societal information': {'Population': '2.5 million', 'Demonym': 'Eaduan', 'Affiliation': ['Galactic Empire', 'Tarkin Initiative']}}
paragraph: Eadu  was a storm-stricken planet in the Outer Rim Territories. It hosted the Eadu Energy Conversion Laboratory prior to the outbreak of the Galactic Civil War, where Galen Erso and his team of scientists attempted to unlock the secrets of the kyber crystals as part of the Death Star project. The refinery was targeted by agents of the Alliance to Restore the Republic following the destruction of Jedha City and resulted in the ruination of the facility and the death of Erso.

title: Eclipse
paragraph: An eclipse was an astronomical event that occurred when a celestial body was temporarily obscured by another. Having witnessed one such event once on Coruscant, the Queen of Alderaan Breha Organa initially thought she was witnessing another eclipse when the Death Star obscured Alderaan's sun. The Death Star had previously created the same scenario when it obscured Jedha's sun before destroying Jedha City in a test.

title: Edusa
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'O-5'}}
paragraph: Edusa was an astronomical object in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Eiattu
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-17'}}
paragraph: Eiattu was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim.

title: Elom
side_bar: {'Biological classification': {'Designation': 'Sentient', 'Classification': 'Mammal'}, 'Physical characteristics': {'Hair color': 'Dark gray', 'Eye color': 'Black'}, 'Sociocultural characteristics': {'Homeworld': 'Elom', 'Habitat': 'Frozen grottos'}}
paragraph: The Elom were a mysterious sentient species that were native to Elom who lived in frozen grottos. They were short and stocky, and covered in thick, oily fur. As a result of living in darkness, Eloms had exceptional eyesight, but found natural or bright lights intolerable. They had two tusks covering the opening of their mouth and small, black eyes located on the far ends of their wide faces. Though as a species that rarely ventured outside their caves, one Elom did make a name for himself offworld. Tanus Spijek was a spy for the Rebel Alliance during the Galactic Civil War. Most, though not all, members of this species were sympathetic to the Rebel Alliance.

title: Elrood
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-20'}}
paragraph: Elrood was an astronomical object in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Empress Teta
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Deep Core', 'Sector': 'Koros sector', 'System': 'Empress Teta system', 'Moons': 'Atale', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-10', 'Trade routes': ['Byss Run', 'Carbonite Run', 'Koros Trunk Line']}, 'Societal information': {'Government': 'Tetan monarchy', 'Major cities': 'Cinnagar ', 'Affiliation': ['Krath', 'Sith Empire', 'Galactic Republic', 'Mining Guild', 'Confederacy of Independent Systems', 'Galactic Empire']}}
paragraph: Empress Teta, known as Koros Major during the lifetime of its namesake, was a planet located in the Empress Teta system, in the Koros sector of the Deep Core. It was connected via hyperspace routes to Prakith and Coruscant, being situated on the Byss Run, Carbonite Run, and Koros Trunk Line. It was orbited by the moon Atale. Empress Teta's capital city was Cinnagar.

title: Enarc
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'O-17'}}
paragraph: Enarc was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim. During the Trade Federation blockade of the planet Naboo leading up to their invasion, Governor Kelma of Karlinus sent an agricultural transport full of grain to Naboo as a sign of good faith due to the recent summit, but the starship was refused passage and was forced to divert to Enarc, where the grain cargo was placed in cold storage.

title: Endor
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region(s)': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Moddell sector', 'System': 'Endor system', 'Planet': 'Endor', 'Grid coordinates': 'H-16', 'Rotation period': '18 hours', 'Orbital period': '402 standard days'}, 'Physical information': {'Diameter': ['4', '900 km'], 'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Gravity': 'Light', 'Primary terrain': ['Forests', 'Savannas', 'Mountains', 'Plains'], 'Surface water': '8%', 'Points of interest': ['Campalan mountain range', "Death Star's shield generator", 'Imperial outpost', 'Imperial Turbolaser Outpost', 'Lake Marudi', 'Lake Sui', 'Mount Krana', 'Platform 4', 'Research Station 9', "Syndulla's camp"], 'Flora': ['Ferns', 'Life tree', 'Mattberry', 'Orchids', 'Redwood tree', 'Sanctuary tree', 'Savanna grass', 'Tree palm'], 'Fauna': ['Blurrg', 'Boar-wolf', 'Bordok', 'Churi', 'Condor dragon', 'Endor blue butterfly', 'Gaupa', 'Geejaw', 'Gurreck', 'Kroolok', 'Lantern bird', 'Pony', 'Pulga', 'Rakazzak beast', 'Munyip', 'Rugger', 'Splledark', 'Temptor', 'Tip-yip', 'Unidentified bird', 'Unidentified bug', 'Verkle']}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': ['Dulok', 'Ewoks', 'Gorax', 'Wistie', 'Yuzzum'], 'Primary language(s)': 'Ewokese', 'Demonym': 'Endorian', 'Major cities': 'Bright Tree Village', 'Population': ['Over 30', '000', '000 Ewoks'], 'Affiliation': ['Galactic Empire', 'Alliance to Restore the Republic', 'First Order']}}
paragraph: Endor, designated IX3244-A, also known as the Forest Moon of Endor or the Sanctuary Moon, was a small forested moon that orbited the Outer Rim planet of the same name and was the homeworld of the sentient Dulok, Ewok, and Yuzzum species, as well as the semi-sentient Gorax and Wistie races.

title: Entralla
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'K-4'}}
paragraph: Entralla was an astronomical object located within the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Er'Kit
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-6'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Primary terrain': ['Deserts', 'Mountains'], 'Points of interest': ['Crimson Gultch', 'Luun Heights', 'Gundark Pass']}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': "Er'Kit"}}
paragraph: Er'Kit was a desert planet located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. It was the homeworld of the Er'Kit species. Before the outbreak of the Clone Wars, Er'Kit senator Danry Ledwellow took bribes from Thalassian slavers, allowing them to use his planet for their illicit activities in exchange for a private army of IG-227 Hailfire-class droid tanks.

title: Eriadu
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Seswenna sector', 'Suns': 'At least 1', 'Moons': 'At least 1', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-18', 'Trade routes': ['Hydian Way', 'Rimma Trade Route']}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Climate': 'Temperate', 'Primary terrain': ['Jungles', 'Mountains'], 'Points of interest': ['Carrion Plateau', 'Carrion Spike', 'Mount Veermok', "Jova Tarkin's cabin", 'Orrineswa River', 'Rivoche Ranges', 'Tarkin family compound'], 'Flora': ['Grass', 'Tree'], 'Fauna': ['Birds', 'Rodents', 'Veermok', 'Eriadu veermok']}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': ['Human', 'Rodian'], 'Primary language(s)': 'Galactic Basic', 'Demonym': 'Eriaduan', 'Major cities': ['Eriadu City', 'Phelar'], 'Major exports': 'Lommite', 'Affiliation': ['Tarkin family', 'Galactic Republic', 'Outland Regions Security Force', 'Galactic Empire']}}
paragraph: Eriadu was a planet in the Outer Rim. The planet featured mountains as well as jungles and had a black pall. Eriadu's chief industry and export revolved around lommite ore which was abundant on the planet. Eriadu was also the homeworld of the Tarkin family including Grand Moff Wilhuff Tarkin.

title: Ertegas
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Anoat sector', 'Moons': 'At least 1'}, 'Physical information': {'Fauna': 'Woshrike'}, 'Societal information': {'Demonym': 'Ertegan', 'Major exports': 'Foodstuff'}}
paragraph: Ertegas was an agriworld located in the Anoat sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. It had at least one moon, where the Galactic Empire exploited a crystal mine. Ertegas never held any interest to the Trade Spine League until the Iron Blockade, which was established by the Empire in an attempt to prevent news of their crushing defeat by the Alliance to Restore the Republic at the Battle of Endor from reaching the Anoat sector's populace, caused the value of foodstuff to rise, though the harvests were disrupted when malfunctioning droids began threatening Ertegan civilians.

title: Esfandia
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Wild Space', 'Grid coordinates': 'I-6'}}
paragraph: Esfandia was an astronomical object located in Wild Space.

title: Eshan
side_bar: {'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Human'}}
paragraph: Eshan was a planet in the galaxy where the infamous Droid Gotra caused a gang dispute, resulting in the loss of many innocents. Eshan was also the homeworld of Tayshin Maxa and Moda Maxa.

title: Esseles
side_bar: {'Physical information': {'Points of interest': 'Esseles listening post'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Esseles was a planet in the galaxy that had been contested territory throughout the Galactic Civil War and had a secret Imperial listening post concealed in its icy rings.

title: Excarga
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'T-16'}}
paragraph: Excarga was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Exodeen
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Colonies', 'System': 'Exodeen system', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-12', 'Trade routes': 'Hydian Way'}}
paragraph: Exodeen was an astronomical object located in the Exodeen system within the galaxy's Colonies region that was situated along the Hydian Way.

title: Fabrin
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region', 'Trade routes': "Nanth'ri Trade Route"}}
paragraph: Fabrin was a world located on the Nanth'ri Trade Route, situated within the Expansion Region. The world was defended by the Resistance's Cobalt Squadron.

title: Falleen
side_bar: {'Biological classification': {'Designation': 'Sentient', 'Classification': ['Reptillian', 'humanoid']}, 'Physical characteristics': {'Skin color': 'Green', 'Hair color': 'Black', 'Distinctions': ['Ridged skulls', 'dorsal spine']}, 'Sociocultural characteristics': {'Homeworld': 'Falleen'}}
paragraph: Falleen were a sentient species native to the planet of the same name. They were capable of projecting powerful pheromones. During the Clone Wars, the Black Sun criminal syndicate was run by a cabal of Falleen nobles, Ziton Moj, from their fortress on Mustafar.

title: Farana
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'S-3'}}
paragraph: Farana was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Wild Space

title: Farstine
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'P-17'}}
paragraph: Farstine was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim.

title: Fedalle
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Core Worlds', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-10', 'Trade routes': 'Hydian Way'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Points of interest': 'Warplands'}, 'Societal information': {'Demonym': 'Fedallese'}}
paragraph: Fedalle was a terrestrial planet within the galaxy's Core Worlds. It was connected via the Hydian Way hyperspace route to the planets Skako and Bellassa. A separate hyperspace lane connected it to the planet Kuat.

title: Feenix
side_bar: {'Societal information': {'Affiliation': ['Galactic Republic', 'Galactic Empire']}}
paragraph: Feenix was a planet represented by Senator Tanner Cadaman in the Galactic Senate of the Galactic Republic until he was arrested one day after the formation of the Galactic Empire.

title: Felucia
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Thanium sector', 'System': 'Felucia system', 'Moons': '8', 'Grid coordinates': 'R-6', 'Trade routes': 'Perlemian Trade Route', 'Rotation period': '34 hours', 'Orbital period': '231 days'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Climate': 'Hot and humid', 'Primary terrain': 'Jungles', 'Points of interest': 'Separatist outpost', 'Flora': ['Nysillin', 'Yerdua'], 'Fauna': ['Cerulean droch', 'Felucia bird', 'Felucian firefly', 'Felucian Ripper', 'Felucian snail', 'Gelagrub', 'Jungle rancor', 'Manta', 'Sarlacc', 'Slimesnipe']}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': ['Felucian', 'Jungle Felucian'], 'Immigrated species': ['Gossam', 'Kyuzo', 'Tee-muss'], 'Population': '425 million', 'Demonym': 'Felucian', 'Major cities': ['Akira', 'Har Gau', 'Jiaozi', 'Kway Teow', 'Niango'], 'Major imports': ['Fuel', 'foodstuffs', 'farming equipment'], 'Major exports': 'Nysillin', 'Affiliation': ['Commerce Guild', 'Confederacy of Independent Systems', 'Galactic Empire']}}
paragraph: Felucia was a colorful, humid jungle planet located in the Felucia system of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. The headquarters of the Commerce Guild, its primary agricultural export was the valuable crop nysillin, which was largely farmed by the native Felucian tribes. Its important strategic location along the Perlemian Trade Route made it a major battleground throughout the Clone Wars.

title: Fengrine
paragraph: Fengrine was an agri-industrial world that had hydroponic shells, in which farmers led a relatively easy life. Around the year 22 BBY, it enjoyed a certain degree of prestige, at least compared to Tatooine.

title: Fest
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Atrivis sector'}, 'Physical information': {'Climate': 'Cold', 'Primary terrain': 'Mountains'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Human', 'Affiliation': 'Alliance to Restore the Republic'}}
paragraph: Fest was a planet located within the Atrivis sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories that was the home to a human population.

title: Filordis
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Inner Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-8'}}
paragraph: Filordis was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Inner Rim.

title: Firrerre
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'H-16'}}
paragraph: Firrerre was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. The New Republic consular office on Firrerre was considered to be the closest New Republic authority for spacers passing in and around the planet Jakku.

title: Florn
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'T-5'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Lamproid'}}
paragraph: Florn was an astronomical object with a dangerous environment located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories that was the homeworld of the Lamproid species.

title: Florrum
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Sertar sector', 'System': 'Florrum system', 'Moons': '1'}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Climate': 'Hot and dry', 'Primary terrain': ['Deserts', 'Sulfurous', 'Geysers'], 'Points of interest': ['Doshar fields', "Hondo's complex", "Hondo's secret ship vault"], 'Fauna': 'Skalder'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': ['Weequay', 'Nikto', 'Bith', 'Jawa'], 'Primary language(s)': 'Galactic Basic', 'Affiliation': ['Ohnaka Gang', 'Confederacy of Independent Systems']}}
paragraph: Florrum was a sulfurous desert planet located in the Florrum system, within the Sertar sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. During the Clone Wars, it was the location of a pirate gang led by Hondo Ohnaka. Florrum was briefly held by the Confederacy of Independent Systems before the forces of General Grievous were repelled by Ohnaka's forces and the Jedi.

title: Foerost
side_bar: {'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Points of interest': 'Foerost communications tower'}}
paragraph: Foerost was a terrestrial world where the Drabatan Pao carried out a demolitions job which involved taking out a communications tower sometime by the year 0 BBY. Captain Cassian Andor remembered this shortly before the Battle of Scarif that year, where the captain's team carried out a similar job. Andor thought to himself that he would ask Pao about the job before the mission began. The Imperial Captain Tabor Seitaron participated in a battle at Foerost at some by the year 3 ABY. While showing Seitaron around the Imperial II-class Star Destroyer Herald that year, an Imperial ensign commented on how the Herald's ten percent increase in efficiency might have been useful at the Battle of Foerost.

title: Foless
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Colonies', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-13', 'Trade routes': 'Corellian Trade Spine'}}
paragraph: Foless was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Colonies region, situated on the Corellian Trade Spine.

title: Fondor
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Colonies', 'Moons': 'At least 1', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-13'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': ['Fondor Shipyards', 'Fondor Station']}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Human', 'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Fondor was a planet located in the Colonies region. During the reign of the Galactic Empire, Fondor served as a massive manufacturing hub for the Imperials, featuring dozens of orbital shipyards known as the Fondor Shipyards. Late in the Galactic Civil War, Fondor served as the site of two attacks from the Rebel Alliance against the Empire, the latter of which resulted in an Imperial defeat. During the First Order/Resistance War, the shipyards were seized by the First Order.

title: Formos
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'T-10', 'Trade routes': ['Pabol Sleheyron', 'Triellus Trade Route']}}
paragraph: Formos was an Outer Rim Territories astronomical object lying on the hyperspace routes known as the Pabol Sleheyron and the Triellus Trade Route. During the reign of the Galactic Empire, Formos served as a processing location for spice transported out of the the planet Kessel. Following the collapse of the Empire, heavy fighting between competitors in the spice trade engulfed Formos.

title: Fornax
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'J-7'}}
paragraph: Fornax was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim, in grid square J-7 on the Standard Galactic Grid.

title: Foundry
side_bar: {'Chronological and political information': {'Affiliation': ['Techno Union', 'Galactic Empire']}}
paragraph: Foundry was a location in the galaxy that was under control of the Galactic Empire. During the operation at the Berullian Checkpoint, Imperial Grand General Ormeddon was dispatched to deal with the situation. With Ormeddon in less restrictive security, Beckett's gang stole Ormeddon's shuttle and returned to Foundry. They landed in Ormeddon's personal docking bay and stole experimental deflector shield generator technology.

title: Fresia
side_bar: {'Chronological and political information': {'Affiliation': ['Galactic Republic', 'Alliance to Restore the Republic']}}
paragraph: Fresia was a location in the galaxy with a human population. During the Clone Wars, it was represented in the Galactic Senate by Seti Ashgad. Jaldine Gerams was from this world, and joined the Alliance to Restore the Republic when they arrived on Fresia.

title: G'wenee
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-6'}}
paragraph: G'wenee was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Galidraan
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'System': 'Galidraan system', 'Grid coordinates': 'R-6'}}
paragraph: Galidraan was a planet located in the Galidraan system within the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. It shared its name with Galidraan III and Galidraan IV, all of which were located in the same system.

title: Gamor
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region', 'Grid coordinates': 'O-14', 'Trade routes': 'Corellian Run'}}
paragraph: Gamor was an astronomical body located in the galaxy's Expansion Region, situated on the Corellian Run.

title: Gamorr
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Galov sector', 'Grid coordinates': 'T-14', 'Trade routes': 'Triellus Trade Route'}, 'Physical information': {'Primary terrain': ['Forests', 'Croplands'], 'Flora': 'Snoruuk'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Gamorrean'}}
paragraph: Gamorr was a lush planet located in the Galov sector of the Outer Rim Territories, near Hutt Space and on the Triellus Trade Route. It was the homeworld of a porcine sentient species, the Gamorreans, who chopped down forests to clear land for farming.

title: Gand
side_bar: {'Biological classification': {'Designation': 'Sentient', 'Classification': 'Insectoid'}, 'Physical characteristics': {'Skin color': 'Brown', 'Eye color': 'Silver', 'Distinctions': 'Breathe ammonia'}, 'Sociocultural characteristics': {'Homeworld': 'Gand', 'Language': 'Gand'}}
paragraph: Gand were an insectoid sentient species native to the planet Gand that breathed ammonia, forcing them to wear respirators to survive in oxygen-rich atmospheres. A notable member of this species was Zuckuss, a bounty hunter who was one of the first traditional findsmen to leave his homeworld.

title: Gannaria
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Trilon sector', 'Grid coordinates': 'H-15'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Humans'}}
paragraph: Gannaria was a terrestrial planet located in the Trilon sector of the Outer Rim Territories, positioned at the coordinates H-15 on the Standard Galactic Grid. It sat on a hyperspace route between the planet Batuu and astronomical object Zaddja. An illegal spice trade had existed on the planet for hundreds of years, and it was often visited by smugglers who used the town of Black Spire Outpost on Batuu as a waypoint. Gannaria also shared its name with the Gannarian Run hyperspace route.

title: Garel
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Lothal sector', 'System': 'Garel system', 'Moons': '2', 'Trade routes': 'Outer Rim trade route'}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Climate': 'Temperate', 'Primary terrain': ['Deserts', 'Mountains', 'Urban'], 'Points of interest': 'North Hoostra'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': ['Bith', 'Human'], 'Government': 'Governorship', 'Major cities': 'Garel City', 'Affiliation': ['Galactic Empire', 'Garel City cell', 'First Order']}}
paragraph: Garel was a planet located in the Garel system of the Outer Rim Territories' Lothal sector that was controlled by the Galactic Empire. It was the homeworld of Imperial Supply Master Yogar Lyste. Garel was several minutes away from the planet Lothal via hyperspace travel. Several years before the Battle of Yavin, the rebel cell Phoenix Cell established a temporary hiding place on Garel. The rebels were forced to move after the Empire discovered their presence and assembled a fleet to attack them. Many years later, individuals such as Statura fought to liberate Garel from the yoke of the Galactic Empire.

title: Gargon
side_bar: {'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Primary terrain': 'Mountains', 'Points of interest': 'Imperial medical spice cache'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': ['Old Mandalorians', 'Galactic Empire']}}
paragraph: Gargon was a mountainous planet. It was settled by the Old Mandalorians, who were exiled from their homeworld of Mandalore by the pacifistic New Mandalorians after a civil war in approximately 42 BBY. On Gargon, they lived as mercenaries working for the highest bidder, as Mandalorians had done for millennia.

title: Garos
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'P-7'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': ['Garos Imperial facility', 'Unidentified university']}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Garos was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim. It was the location of a university and Imperial facility five years after the Clone Wars.

title: Garqi
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'K-5'}}
paragraph: Garqi was an astronomical object in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Gaulus
side_bar: {'Chronological and political information': {'Affiliation': 'Alliance to Restore the Republic'}}
paragraph: Gaulus was a location in the galaxy. Alliance to Restore the Republic Lieutenant Caluan Ematt and Sergeant Ruescott Melshi served together on Gaulus during the early rebellion against the Galactic Empire. During the Alliance's retreat from Gaulus, they deployed the UT-60D U-wing starfighter/support craft as a medevac lifter. It shared its name with the Gaulus sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

title: Genassa
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-7'}}
paragraph: Genassa was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim.

title: Generis
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Atrivis sector', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-5'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Human', 'Affiliation': 'Alliance to Restore the Republic'}}
paragraph: Generis was an astronomical object located in the Atrivis sector within the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. The Rebel pilot Paril Ritta was from Generis. During the early rebellion against the Galactic Empire, Generis served as an Alliance to Restore the Republic regional headquarters and operations sector. Generis was included in a map of the galaxy that listed safe worlds, starfighter hubs at level five or higher, regional headquarters and operations sectors, and deep space caches.

title: Geonosis
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Arkanis sector', 'System': 'Geonosis system', 'Suns': 'Ea', 'Orbital position': 'Second from the sun', 'Moons': ['15;', 'including:Bahryn', 'Later 4'], 'Grid coordinates': 'R-16', 'Trade routes': 'Triellus Trade Route', 'Distance from Core': ['43', '000 light years from the Galactic Core'], 'Rotation period': '30 hours', 'Orbital period': '256 standard days'}, 'Physical information': {'Diameter': ['11', '370 kilometers'], 'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Climate': 'Hot and arid', 'Gravity': 'Light', 'Primary terrain': ['Deserts', 'Mesas', 'Mountains'], 'Surface water': '5%', 'Points of interest': ["Badlands of N'g'zi", 'Caltrop field', 'Eastern barrier', "E'Y-Akh Desert", 'Geonosian Command Center', 'Geonosian droid factories', 'Geonosis primary droid foundry ray shield generator', 'Trippa hive droid factory', 'Geonosian hive spires', 'Geonosis catacombs', 'Geonosis primary droid foundry ray shield generator', "Im'g'twe Hills", "Karina's lair", 'Orbital Foundry 7', 'Petranaki Arena', 'Point Rain', 'Progate Temple', 'Rings of Geonosis', 'Sector 5-1-5', 'Stalgasin war room'], 'Flora': 'Spider-sponge', 'Fauna': ['Brain worm', 'Merdeth', 'Mongworst', 'Orray', 'Phidna', 'Pygmy porlceetin']}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Geonosian', 'Immigrated species': ['Acklay', 'Massiff', 'Nexu', 'Reek'], 'Primary language(s)': 'Geonosian hive-mind', 'Government': ['Monarchy', 'Geonosian hives'], 'Population': ['100 billion'], 'Demonym': 'Geonosian', 'Major cities': ['Gehenbar hive', 'Golbah hive', 'Stalgasin hive spires', 'Trippa hive'], 'Major imports': 'Raw materials', 'Major exports': ['Battle droids', 'Technology'], 'Affiliation': ['Stalgasin hive', 'Techno Union', 'Confederacy of Independent Systems', 'Galactic Republic', 'Galactic Empire']}}
paragraph: Geonosis, referred to as Geonosia by some natives, and known as Genosha, was the desert home planet of the Geonosians. It was the Confederacy of Independent Systems' first capital and hosted its major battle droid foundries. It was the site of the First Battle of Geonosis, the opening conflict of the Clone Wars, as well as the subsequent invasion by the Galactic Republic. During and after the war, the Death Star was constructed above the planet. Five years after the conflict's conclusion and transformation of the Galactic Republic, the Galactic Empire would garrison the planet heavily and attempt to mine the planet's asteroids for minerals. At least five years after the Clone Wars, the Empire moved the Death Star to another construction site and the planet was sterilized by the Empire as a security measure, an act which resulted in the virtual elimination of the planet's native population.

title: Gerrenthum
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': ['Greater Javin', 'Anoat sector'], 'System': 'Gerrenthum system', 'Grid coordinates': 'K-18', 'Trade routes': 'Corellian Trade Spine'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': "Gerrenthum's orbital security station"}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Human', 'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Gerrenthum was a planet located in the Gerrenthum system of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories, serving as the Anoat sector's capital after the previous capital, Anoat, was rendered uninhabitable. For many years, Imperial Governor Ubrik Adelhard governed the sector with an iron fist and absolute loyalty to the Galactic Empire. Orbited by a security station, many business owners and politicians on Gerrenthum openly bribed Imperials to ignore their illegal activities.

title: Ghorman
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Colonies', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-13', 'Trade routes': 'Rimma Trade Route'}}
paragraph: Ghorman was a planet located in the galaxy's Colonies region along the Rimma Trade Route. At some point during the reign of the Galactic Empire, the Empire carried out one of its worst atrocities on Ghorman, an event which Senator Tynnra Pamlo was exposed to evidence of.

title: Gigor
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Tynquay sector'}, 'Physical information': {'Climate': 'Frigid', 'Primary terrain': ['Snow-covered', 'mountainous with caves', 'Hot springs', 'Valleys'], 'Flora': ['Bushes', 'Trees', 'Mushrooms'], 'Fauna': ['Ice scrabbler', 'Icetromper', 'Jakobeast', 'Jexxel cat', 'Snow shredder bat']}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Gigoran', 'Primary language(s)': 'Gigoran', 'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Gigor was a frigid planet located in the Tynquay sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories that was the homeworld of the Gigoran species. During the age of the Galactic Empire, many Gigorans on their homeworld were rounded up by Zygerrian slavers and forced in labor. Among these individuals was Senna, a Gigoran who was forced to work as a slave in the spice mines of Kessel.

title: Giju
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Colonies', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-13', 'Trade routes': ['Herglic Alley', 'Rimma Trade Route']}}
paragraph: Giju was a planet located in the galaxy's Colonies region along the Rimma Trade Route. Shortly after the Battle of Yavin, Red Squadron from the Alliance to Restore the Republic evacuated rebel leaders from Giju before they could be discovered by Imperial agents.

title: Gizer
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region', 'Grid coordinates': 'P-8', 'Trade routes': 'Perlemian Trade Route'}}
paragraph: Gizer was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Expansion Region, located on Perlemian Trade Route.

title: Glee Anselm
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'System': 'Jalor system', 'Grid coordinates': 'J-7'}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Primary terrain': ['Jungles', 'Grassy fields', 'Mountains', 'Oceans'], 'Points of interest': 'District 74', 'Flora': 'Trees', 'Fauna': ['Hammerfish', 'Lizard-gull', 'Sandmoth', 'Whales', 'Wooriid']}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': ['Anselmi', 'Human', 'Nautolan'], 'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Glee Anselm was an ocean planet located in the Jalor system of the galaxy's Mid Rim that was the homeworld of the Anselmi and Nautolan species. Star Tours, a tour company, offered vacation tours of Glee Anselm during the Clone Wars. During the reign of the Galactic Empire, senators representing the planet in the Imperial Senate were fiercely loyal to the Empire. Glee Anselm was also the homeworld of the criminal Tobias Beckett and the Jedi Master Kit Fisto.

title: Goroth
paragraph: Goroth, also known as Goroth Prime, was a location in the galaxy. When Agent Alecia Beck of the Imperial Security Bureau requested a meeting with Senator Mon Mothma, Mothma's aide, Hendri Underholt, lied to Beck and told her that Mothma had already left Coruscant and had gone on a fact-finding mission to Goroth.

title: Gorse
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Inner Rim', 'System': 'Gorse system', 'Moons': 'Cynda'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Points of interest': ["Calladan's field", 'Moonglow Polychemical refinery', 'The Asteroid Belt'], 'Flora': ['Nightfern', 'Yettice'], 'Fauna': ['Gorsian dragonfly', 'Rodents']}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': ['Besalisk', 'Chagrian', 'Devaronian', 'Human', 'Ithorian', 'Neimoidian', 'Sullustan', "Twi'lek", 'Wookiee'], 'Primary language(s)': 'Galactic Basic', 'Demonym': 'Gorsian', 'Major cities': ['Gorse City', 'Highground', 'Shaketown'], 'Major imports': 'Crystalline Thorilide', 'Major exports': 'Refined Thorilide', 'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Gorse  was a tidally-locked planet located on the Inner Rim. It had one moon called Cynda, which was rich in thorilide crystals. During the Age of the Empire, Gorse had seemingly exhausted its thorilide reserves and had become a major refinery for thorilide exports from Cynda, which had been opened up to thorilide mining. Gorse served as the location of a conflict between the Galactic Empire and a small rebel cell led by Hera Syndulla and the former Jedi Padawan Kanan Jarrus. Following the Gorse conflict, thorilide mining was established in Gorse's sunward side while Cynda was restored to its former status as a nature reserve.

title: Gravlex Med
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-4'}, 'Physical information': {'Gravity': 'High'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Anx'}}
paragraph: Gravlex Med was a high gravity world located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. It was the homeworld of the Anx species.

title: Gree
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-2'}}
paragraph: Gree was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories, in the grid square L-2 of the Standard Galactic Grid.

title: Grizmallt
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Core Worlds'}}
paragraph: Grizmallt was a war-torn planet in the Core Worlds, and the origin of the humans who crash-landed on and colonized Naboo long before the Clone Wars.

title: Gromas
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Sector': 'Perkell sector', 'Grid coordinates': 'Q-7'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': 'Gromas Imperial depot'}, 'Societal information': {'Major exports': 'Phrik', 'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Gromas was an astronomical object located in the Perkell sector of the galaxy's Mid Rim. It was the location of an Imperial depot and supported a mining operation for phrik, a metallic compound that was nearly indestructible. In the year 14 BBY, the Imperial Joint Chiefs believed Gromas' depot was a possible target for former Republic Intelligence captain Berch Teller and his rebel cell and dispatched a task force to defend the installation. The rebels learned of this, however, and attacked Phindar instead.

title: Gyndine
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region', 'Sector': 'Circarpous sector', 'Grid coordinates': 'O-12'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': "Bin Essada's offices"}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Gyndine was an administrative planet in the galaxy's Expansion Region. Hyperspace routes connected it to the planets Mimban, Antar and Belasco. Moff Bin Essada coordinated efforts of the Mimban campaign from his offices on Gyndine.

title: Halmad
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-6'}}
paragraph: Halmad was an astronomical object in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Hapes
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Inner Rim', 'Sector': 'Hapes Consortium', 'Grid coordinates': 'O-9'}}
paragraph: Hapes was an astronomical object located in the Hapes Consortium, a sector of the galaxy's Inner Rim.

title: Harrin
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Inner Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-15', 'Trade routes': 'Corellian Trade Spine'}}
paragraph: Harrin was an astronomical object in the galaxy's Inner Rim, situated on the Corellian Trade Spine.

title: Haruun Kal
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-17'}, 'Physical information': {'Flora': 'Lammas tree', 'Fauna': 'Fever wasp'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': ['Human', 'Korun']}}
paragraph: Haruun Kal was a planet located in the galaxy's Mid Rim, in grid square M-17 on the Standard Galactic Grid, that was the homeworld of Mace Windu, a human Jedi Master and champion of the Jedi Order. During the Clone Wars, it was the site of a battle between the Galactic Republic and Confederacy of Independent Systems.

title: Helska
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-2'}}
paragraph: Helska was an astronomical object located in the Outer Rim Territories, in the grid square L-2 of the Standard Galactic Grid.

title: Herdessa
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'Q-16', 'Trade routes': 'Corellian Run'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': ['Galactic Republic', 'Galactic Empire']}}
paragraph: Herdessa was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim that was situated along the Corellian Run at Q-16 on the Standard Galactic Grid. Herdessa was represented in the Galactic Senate and later the Imperial Senate by Senator Shea Sadashassa. Vryant, a soldier in the Imperial Army, served six years on Herdessa.

title: Hok
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Colonies', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-9'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Gran'}}
paragraph: Hok was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Colonies region that was the homeworld of the Gran podracer Mawhonic.

title: Hollastin
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Hutt Space', 'Grid coordinates': 'S-12'}}
paragraph: Hollastin was a world located in the Hutt Space region of the galaxy. It was connected to fellow Hutt Space world Circumtore as well as the world Syvris by hyperspace routes. Hollastin was located at galactic coordinates S-12.

title: Honoghr
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'T-10'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Noghri'}}
paragraph: Honoghr was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories that was the homeworld of the Noghri species.

title: Horuz
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-5'}}
paragraph: Horuz was a planet located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. Shortly before the Battle of Scarif, Imperial forces were deployed to Horuz. In the lead-up to the Battle of Jakku in 5 ABY, Horuz was reportedly to still be in the thrall of some Imperial remnant or criminal syndicates or gangs.

title: Hosnian Prime
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Core Worlds', 'System': 'Hosnian system', 'Suns': '1', 'Moons': '1', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-12', 'Trade routes': 'Corellian Trade Spine'}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Primary terrain': 'Urban', 'Points of interest': ['Hanging gardens', 'Hosnian Prime Academy of Law Enforcement', 'Hosnian Prime factory complex', 'Hosnian Prime flight academy', 'Hosnian Prime orbital outpost', 'New Republic senatorial complex', 'Offices of the Galaxy Beacon', 'Senate hangar', 'Unidentified New Republic veteran hospital'], 'Fauna': 'Snowbird'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Human', 'Government': 'New Republic', 'Major cities': ['Darropolis', 'Republic City'], 'Affiliation': ['Galactic Republic', 'Galactic Empire', 'New Republic']}}
paragraph: Hosnian Prime was a planet in the Hosnian system of the Core Worlds, located along the Corellian Trade Spine. Thirty years after the Battle of Endor, it served as the headquarters of the Galactic Senate and was the galactic capital of the New Republic during the conflict between the Resistance and the First Order.

title: Hoth
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Anoat sector', 'System': 'Hoth system', 'Suns': ['1:', 'Hoth'], 'Orbital position': '6', 'Moons': '3', 'Grid coordinates': 'K-18', 'Trade routes': ['Ison Trade Corridor', 'Corellian Trade Spine'], 'Distance from Core': ['50', '250 light years'], 'Rotation period': '23 standard hours', 'Orbital period': ['549 days']}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Diameter': ['7', '200 km'], 'Atmosphere': ['Breathable', 'clean'], 'Climate': 'Frigid', 'Primary terrain': ['Frozen ice plains', 'glaciers', 'oceans', 'mountains'], 'Surface water': '33% ', 'Points of interest': ['Clabburn Range', 'Echo Base', 'Echo Station 3-T-8', 'Icefall Plains', 'Moorsh Moraine', 'Outpost Beta', 'Perimeter Outpost Delta', "Shyloah's Crest", 'Wampa Mountain'], 'Fauna': ['Fork-nosed ice worm', 'Ice scrabbler', 'Rayboo', 'Sapphire ice worm', 'Tauntaun', 'Wampa']}, 'Societal information': {'Population': 'Fewer than 10', 'Demonym': 'Hothian', 'Affiliation': 'Alliance to Restore the Republic'}}
paragraph: Hoth was a remote, icy planet that was the sixth planet in the star system of the same name. It notably hosted Echo Base, the temporary headquarters of the Alliance to Restore the Republic, until the Galactic Empire located the Rebels, initiating a major confrontation known as the Battle of Hoth.

title: Huk
side_bar: {'Societal information': {'Native species': "Yam'rii"}}
paragraph: Huk was the homeworld of the technologically-advanced, insect-like Yam'rii species.

title: Humbarine
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Core Worlds', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-10'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': 'Humbarine Academy of Advanced Studies', 'Fauna': 'Sycanid'}}
paragraph: Humbarine was a planet located in the galaxy's Core Worlds. Galen Walton Erso attended the Humbarine Academy of Advanced Studies after an internship at the Galactic Republic's Ministry of Energy. Lega Fossang was a member of Humbarine's planetary defense force prior to her recruitment to the Resistance.

title: Hypori
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'S-16'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': 'Hypori Imperial research station'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': ['Techno Union', 'Confederacy of Independent Systems', 'Galactic Empire']}}
paragraph: Hypori was a world located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories with a hydrothermal landscape that was host to a Techno Union droid factory. The hulk of a crashed Acclamator-class transgalactic military assault ship stood as a grim memorial of a battle during the Clone Wars in which a group of Jedi Knights were taken by surprise. During the Imperial Era, Commander Orson Krennic's engineering team was based at an Imperial facility on the planet where they worked in weapon development for the Galactic Empire. In 18 BBY, the research station was destroyed by Star Destroyer turbolasers.

title: Iego
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Moons': ['1', '000 moons', 'including:', 'Clepresdan', 'Cobarb', 'Flitrude', 'Millius Prime', 'Rawnde', 'Uncovalor', 'Winlion'], 'Grid coordinates': 'T-7'}, 'Physical information': {'Climate': ['Hot', 'Humid', 'Temperate', 'Tropical'], 'Primary terrain': ['Basaltic spires', 'Canyons', 'Deserts'], 'Flora': 'Reeksa', 'Fauna': 'Xandu'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': ['Diathim', 'Human', 'Ithorian', "Kajain'sa'Nikto", 'Quarren', 'Rodian'], 'Demonym': 'Iegoan', 'Major cities': 'Cliffhold', 'Major exports': 'Spice', 'Affiliation': 'Confederacy of Independent Systems'}}
paragraph: Iego was a mysterious planet located in the Outer Rim Territories on the fringes of the known galaxy that was surrounded by a thousand moons collectively known as the moons of Iego, at least one of which was populated by a race of beings known as Angels. During the Clone Wars, the Confederacy of Independent Systems constructed a laser field that prevented anyone from leaving the planet, before the field was destroyed by Obi-Wan Kenobi and Anakin Skywalker, freeing the Iegoans.

title: Iktotchon
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region', 'Sector': 'Narvath sector', 'System': 'Iktotch system', 'Moons': 'Iktotch', 'Grid coordinates': 'O-14'}, 'Physical information': {'Climate': 'Windy'}}
paragraph: Iktotchon was a planet located in the Expansion Region of the galaxy. It had a moon, Iktotch, which was the homeworld of Iktotchi Jedi Master Saesee Tiin.

title: Ilum
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Unknown Regions', 'Sector': '7G sector', 'System': ['Ilum system', 'Starkiller Base system'], 'Suns': ['Asar', 'Unidentified star'], 'Orbital position': '5', 'Moons': ['2', '0'], 'Grid coordinates': ['G-7'], 'Trade routes': 'Metellos-Ilum hyperspace route', 'Rotation period': '66 hours', 'Orbital period': ['301 days', 'Variable']}, 'Physical information': {'Diameter': '660 kilometers', 'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Climate': 'Frigid', 'Primary terrain': ['Crystallized glaciers', 'Ice plains', 'Mountains', 'Forests'], 'Points of interest': ['Jedi Temple', 'Crystal Cave', 'Imperial Trench', 'Starkiller Base'], 'Flora': 'Trees', 'Fauna': ['Asharl panther', 'Blismal', 'Gorgodon', 'Razhak', 'Snowfeather bird', 'Unidentified creature']}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Human', 'Population': ['5', '200'], 'Major exports': 'Kyber crystals', 'Affiliation': ['Jedi Order', 'Galactic Empire', 'First Order']}}
paragraph: Ilum was a snow-covered planet located in the 7G sector of the Unknown Regions, within the Ilum system. Ilum was the fifth planet from its parent star Asar, a blue dwarf, located roughly equidistant from Asar and the system's cometary cloud. Ilum had a kyber crystalline core, and had been utilized by the Jedi Order for the Gathering, a rite of passage in which Jedi younglings had to find and harvest kyber crystals for their lightsabers, which had existed for thousands of standard years.

title: Imynusoph
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'J-21', 'Trade routes': 'Hydian Way'}}
paragraph: Imynusoph was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. It marked the end of the Hydian Way hyperspace route, which linked it to Terminus. Imynusoph was positioned at the coordinates J-21 on the Standard Galactic Grid.

title: Indu San
paragraph: Indu San was a location where the Galactic Empire's 204th Imperial Fighter Wing operated, during which some of their members were killed.

title: Indupar
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim'}}
paragraph: Indupar was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim.

title: Ingo
paragraph: Ingo was a location in the galaxy. In 0 BBY, Rebel corporal Eskro Casrich sun-sailed its dunes prior to the Battle of Scarif.

title: Ione
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Anoat sector', 'System': 'Ione system'}}
paragraph: Ione was a planet in the Ione system of the Outer Rim Territories. During the Galactic Empire's Iron Blockade of the Anoat sector, Imperials seized all crystal shipments landing on Ione, causing an overflow of crystals in Imperial holdings. At the time of the Iron Blockade, many of the planet's inhabitants resented the Empire, but could not fight back as they lacked proper training.

title: Iridonia
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'J-7'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Zabrak', 'Demonym': 'Iridonian'}}
paragraph: Iridonia was a planet located in the galaxy's Mid Rim, in grid square J-7 on the Standard Galactic Grid. It was the homeworld of the near-human Zabrak species, with Zabraks hailing from Iridonia being specifically known as Iridonian Zabraks.

title: Isde Naha
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': ['Outer Rim Territories', 'Western Reaches'], 'Sector': 'Greater Javin', 'Grid coordinates': 'K-18', 'Trade routes': 'Corellian Trade Spine'}}
paragraph: Isde Naha was a world trailing on the Outer Rim edge of the Western Reaches. It was home to the Clan of the Toribota, a nomadic enclave.

title: Iseno
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Inner Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-13', 'Trade routes': 'Corellian Run'}}
paragraph: Iseno was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Inner Rim that was situated along the Corellian Run.

title: Ishanna
paragraph: Ishanna was a location where the Ishanna inversion occurred, which hampered the performance of the rebel starship Nautilian.

title: Iskalon
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'R-16', 'Trade routes': "Mumble's Turnaround"}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Primary terrain': 'Aquatic', 'Points of interest': 'Facility 2335DA', 'Fauna': 'Serpents'}}
paragraph: Iskalon was a planet located in the galaxy's Mid Rim.

title: Ison
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Anoat sector', 'System': 'Ison system', 'Grid coordinates': 'K-18', 'Trade routes': 'Ison Trade Corridor'}}
paragraph: Ison was a planet in the Ison system and found on the Ison Trade Corridor. Ison was near pirate-controlled territory, and at the time of the Iron Blockade, it hosted a debris field which inflicted critical damage to a passenger transport attempting to navigate it. The transport drifted into the pirate territory, so the ship's captain requested help from a young smuggler.

title: Ithor
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'System': 'Ottega system', 'Suns': '1: Ithorian sun', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-6'}, 'Physical information': {'Primary terrain': 'Jungles', 'Points of interest': 'Mother Jungle', 'Flora': ['Johinuu tree', "N'lor tree"], 'Fauna': ['Molsume', 'Toscwon']}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Ithorian', 'Primary language(s)': 'Ithorese', 'Demonym': 'Ithoria', 'Affiliation': 'Galactic Republic'}}
paragraph: Ithor was a planet located in the galaxy's Mid Rim that was the homeworld of the Ithorian species, who spoke Ithorese. The expansive jungles of Ithor were considered to be sacred, and hunting there was highly illegal. Their flora included the dense n'lor trees, the carnivorous johinuu trees, a variety of green and rust-hued bushes, and carpets of blue and pink edible fungi. Their fauna included the rare and deadly molsume, and the toscwon.

title: Ixtlar
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Core Worlds', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-10', 'Trade routes': 'Corellian Run'}}
paragraph: Ixtlar was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Core Worlds, along the Corellian Run, which connected it to Coruscant.

title: Jabiim
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'S-7'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial'}, 'Societal information': {'Major exports': 'Ore', 'Affiliation': 'First Order'}}
paragraph: Jabiim was a terrestrial astronomical object in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. Connected to Sy Myrth and Taskeed by hyperspace routes, it was positioned at the coordinates S-7 on the Standard Galactic Grid. During the war between the First Order and the Resistance, it fell under the control of the First Order, who sent slaves to mine ore on Jabiim.

title: Jaemus
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'K-4'}}
paragraph: Jaemus was an astronomical object in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Jaguada
side_bar: {'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Primary terrain': 'Desert'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Sith'}}
paragraph: Jaguada was a desert planet and one of many worlds of the ancient Sith.
