According to legend, the Sith Lord Darth Noctyss carried out research on the planet that eventually led her to the lost Sith world of Exegol in her quest to attain immortality. In the time of the Galactic Republic, Jaguada was quarantined, and its affiliation to the Sith was hidden from history.

title: Jakku
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': ['Western Reaches', 'Inner Rim'], 'System': 'Jakku system', 'Suns': '1', 'Orbital position': 'First from the sun', 'Moons': '2', 'Grid coordinates': 'I-13', 'Trade routes': "Burke's Trailing", 'Rotation period': '26.8 standard hours', 'Orbital period': ['352 standard days', '315 local days']}, 'Physical information': {'Diameter': ['6', '400 kilometers'], 'Atmosphere': 'Type I ', 'Climate': 'Arid; hot days with cold nights', 'Primary terrain': ['Modern:Deserts', 'Historic:Forests'], 'Points of interest': ['Anchorite habit house', 'Carbon Ridge', "Ergel's Bar", 'Fallen Teeth', "Feressee's Point", 'Goazon Badlands', 'Imperial research base', 'Kelvin Ravine', 'Kelvin Ridge', 'Main Imperial base', "Namenthe's Crater", 'Niima Outpost', "Old Meru's", 'Orkoon Hub', "Pilgrim's Road", 'Plaintive Hand plateau', 'Sinking Fields', 'Starship Graveyard'], 'Flora': 'Tuanulberry bush', 'Fauna': ['Bloggin', 'Cricket', 'Gnaw-jaw', 'Happabore', 'Luggabeast', 'Nightwatcher worm', 'Pole-snake', 'Ripper-raptor', 'Skittermice', 'Steelpecker', 'Thissermount', 'Vworkka']}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': ['Teedo', 'Uthuthma'], 'Immigrated species': ['Abednedo', 'Crolute', 'Human', 'Hutt', 'Kyuzo', 'Melitto', 'Nu-Cosian', 'Dybrinthe'], 'Primary language(s)': ['Galactic Basic', 'Hideo', 'Teedospeak', 'Uthuthma'], 'Population': 'Unknown ', 'Demonym': 'Jakkuvian', 'Major cities': ['Blowback Town', 'Cratertown', 'Niima Outpost', 'Reestkii', 'Tuanul'], 'Major imports': ['Foodstuffs', 'Luxury goods', 'Technology', 'Water'], 'Major exports': ['Bezorite', 'Junk metal', 'Kesium gas', 'Magnite', 'Osmiridium', 'Salvaged tech', 'Silicon'], 'Affiliation': ['Galactic Empire', 'First Order']}}
paragraph: Jakku was a remote desert planet located in the system of the same name, within the Western Reaches of the galaxy's Inner Rim. Though considered by many within the galaxy to be distant and relatively worthless, Jakku was the site of important events that would shape galactic history. In 5 ABY, Jakku was the site of the pivotal Battle of Jakku, which ended the Galactic Civil War in favor of the New Republic. A generation later, the planet was the home of the scavenger Rey, who became involved in the events of the Cold War after helping the former First Order stormtrooper Finn and the astromech droid BB-8 escape offworld with a map leading to the missing Jedi Luke Skywalker.

title: Jaminere
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Tion Cluster', 'Grid coordinates': 'S-6'}}
paragraph: Jaminere was an astronomical object located in the Tion Cluster of the Outer Rim Territories, linked to Cadinth by a hyperspace route. It was positioned at the coordinates S-6 on the Standard Galactic Grid.

title: Jamiron
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Unknown Regions'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Chiss Ascendancy'}}
paragraph: Jamiron was a world of the Chiss Ascendancy. Mitth'ali'astov undertook her formal schooling on Jamiron.

title: Jazbina
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-8'}}
paragraph: Jazbina was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Expansion Region, positioned at the coordinates M-8 on the Standard Galactic Grid.

title: Jedha
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region(s)': 'Mid Rim', 'Sector': ['Terrabe sector', 'Freestanding subsectors'], 'System': 'Jedha system', 'Planet': 'NaJedha', 'Grid coordinates': 'H-10', 'Trade routes': "Burke's Trailing", 'Rotation period': '23 hours', 'Orbital period': '420 days'}, 'Physical information': {'Diameter': ['11', '263 kilometers'], 'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Climate': 'Cold', 'Primary terrain': ['Deserts', 'Mesas', 'Rocky dustbowls'], 'Points of interest': ['Catacombs of Cadera', 'Desiccated tablelands', 'Kyber mines', 'Temple of Central Isopter', 'Temple of the Kyber'], 'Fauna': ['Birds', 'Lizards', 'Sand slug', 'Spamel']}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': ['Anomid', 'Human', 'Lorrdian', 'Vobati'], 'Demonym': 'Jedhan', 'Major cities': ['Ai-jed', 'Jedha City'], 'Population': ['11.3 million'], 'Major imports': ['Foodstuffs', 'water', 'medicine', 'pilgrims'], 'Major exports': 'Kyber crystals', 'Affiliation': ['Jedi Order', 'Galactic Empire']}}
paragraph: Jedha, also known as the Pilgrim Moon, or as the Cold Moon, was a small desert moon which orbited the planet NaJedha. Located in the Jedha system of the galaxy's Mid Rim, the moon had a cold climate due to its lasting winter. The historical and spiritual significance of Jedha led the moon to become a world of worship for those who believed in the Force, and a holy site for pilgrims who sought spiritual guidance.

title: Jelucan
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories'}, 'Physical information': {'Climate': 'Cold', 'Primary terrain': ['Mountains', 'plateaus'], 'Points of interest': ['The Fortress', 'Jelucan preparatory academy', "Stepson's Gorge", "Wavers' Peak"], 'Fauna': 'Muunyak'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': ['Falleen', 'Human', "Twi'lek"], 'Demonym': 'Jelucani', 'Major cities': ['Valentia'], 'Major exports': 'Jelucani fogstone', 'Affiliation': ['Confederacy of Independent Systems', 'Galactic Empire']}}
paragraph: Jelucan was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories. The planet sided with the Confederacy of Independent Systems during the Clone Wars. During the Age of the Empire, Jelucan was annexed by the Galactic Empire. It was the homeworld of Thane Kyrell and Ciena Ree, two star-crossed lovers who fought on opposite sides of the Galactic Civil War.

title: Jeyell
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': ['Alliance to Restore the Republic', 'Mid Rim revolutionaries']}}
paragraph: Jeyell was a planet in the Mid Rim. During the Galactic Civil War between the Galactic Empire and the Alliance to Restore the Republic, the Alliance was forced to retreat from its failed Mid Rim Offensive, an operation by the Alliance and the Mid Rim revolutionaries to take control of the Mid Rim. The Alliance also retreated from Pothor, Durkteel, Ord Tiddell, Charros IV, and Trasse. Several revolutionaries evacuated with Alliance forces, although most remained on their planets to harass the Empire, who was expected to take quick control over the former Alliance territories.

title: Jiroch
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'Ð-17', 'Trade routes': 'Corellian Trade Spine'}}
paragraph: Jiroch was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim on the Corellian Trade Spine.

title: Jomark
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'R-7'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': 'Jomark Imperial outpost'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Jomark was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories which housed an Imperial outpost and which was located close to the Galidraan system. When the Imperial corvette Carrion Spike was stolen and attacked Galidraan Station, Moff Wilhuff Tarkin requested a list of all nearby Imperial resources the ship might next attack; Jomark and its outpost were amongst those included in the list given to him. Some time between 4 and 5 ABY, Han Solo told Maz Kanata in her castle over a tankard of Parkellan Sling that the long-range communicator of his ship, the Millennium Falcon, took a hit back at the planet and Chewbacca was fixing it.

title: Jovan
side_bar: {'Physical description': {'Species': 'Human', 'Gender': 'Male', 'Hair color': 'Brown', 'Eye color': 'Golden brown', 'Skin color': 'Fair'}, 'Chronological and political information': {'Affiliation(s)': ['Galactic Empire', 'Royal Imperial Academy', 'Imperial Officer Corps']}}
paragraph: Jovan was a male human who served in the military forces of the Galactic Empire in the years prior to the Battle of Yavin. He used his station within the Imperial military to enrich his own life, which resulted in his arrest by his former friend, Agent Kallus of the Imperial Security Bureau.

title: Jubilar
side_bar: {'Chronological and political information': {'Affiliation': ['Confederacy of Independent Systems', 'New Republic']}}
paragraph: Jubilar was a location that was used as a prison by the Confederacy of Independent Systems. During the Clone Wars, it was one of several locations where a majority of Separatist prisoners were sent.

title: Junkfort Station
side_bar: {'Location information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories'}}
paragraph: Junkfort Station was a space station located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories region. It served as the intersection between two hyperspace routes, and was connected by them to the planets Kubindi, Dennogra, Oseon and Boonta.

title: Kaal
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'K-17', 'Trade routes': 'Corellian Trade Spine'}}
paragraph: Kaal was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim.

title: Kabal
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-18'}}
paragraph: Kabal was an astronomical object in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Kadavo
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Wild Space', 'System': 'Kadavo system'}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Climate': 'Cold', 'Primary terrain': 'Volcanic', 'Points of interest': 'Kadavo slave processing facility'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Zygerrian', 'Primary language(s)': 'Galactic Basic', 'Affiliation': ['Zygerrian Slave Empire', 'Confederacy of Independent Systems']}}
paragraph: Kadavo was an ugly, barren planet located in the Kadavo system of Wild Space. During the Clone Wars, it was under the control of the Zygerrian Slave Empire, which used it to process slaves. Kadavo had multiple volcanoes, but for the most part, they were dormant. Nonetheless, the planet's atmosphere was affected and remained filled with smog.

title: Kal'Shebbol
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-21', 'Trade routes': 'Rimma Trade Route'}}
paragraph: Kal'Shebbol was a planet located within the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. It was located close to one end of the Rimma Trade Route, which connected it to the planet Karideph. Cal Alder, an Alliance to Restore the Republic lieutenant, hailed from the planet.

title: Kalaan
paragraph: Kalaan was a location in the galaxy. Prior to the Galactic Civil War, Visler Korda, a captain in the Imperial Navy, threatened to send Dil Pexton to an Imperial prison camp on Kalaan if he didn't betray Lina Graf.

title: Kalarba
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Moons': ['At least 2', 'including an unidentified moon'], 'Grid coordinates': 'P-15'}}
paragraph: Kalarba was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim. It was orbited by multiple moons, including one that had the Imperial space station Hosk Station built entirely around its surface. During the Galactic Civil War, the Ishi Tib pilot Sata Neek claimed that he and the Alliance to Restore the Republic RZ-1 A-wing interceptor squadron designated Riot Squadron and its commanding officer Creel had searched for a rebel base on Kalarba for six hours before realizing that Creel had mistaken a flight simulator mission for a set of redeployment orders. His squadron mate Kamala disputed the truth of this story.

title: Kalee
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Wild Space', 'Grid coordinates': 'J-4'}, 'Physical information': {'Fauna': 'Mumuu'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Kaleesh'}}
paragraph: Kalee was a planet located in Wild Space that was the homeworld of the Kaleesh species. Grievous, a male Kaleesh warlord, was from this world.

title: Kalevala
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Mandalore sector', 'System': 'Mandalore system', 'Grid coordinates': 'O-7'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': 'Museum of Mythos'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Human', 'Affiliation': ['House Kryze', 'New Mandalorians', 'Galactic Republic']}}
paragraph: Kalevala was a planet located in the Mandalore system, within the Mandalore sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories, that was the homeworld of House Kryze. It was the birthplace of Duchess Satine Kryze, leader of the New Mandalorians and the Council of Neutral Systems during the Clone Wars.

title: Kalinda
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'O-16'}}
paragraph: Kalinda was an astronomical object located in the Mid Rim, in the grid square O-16 of the Standard Galactic Grid. A hyperspace route linked Kalinda to the planet Naboo and the celestial body Kira.

title: Kalki Nebula
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region(s)': 'Trans-Hydian Borderlands', 'Sector': 'Cassander sector'}}
paragraph: The Kalki Nebula was a nebula located in the Cassander sector, a part of the Trans-Hydian Borderlands region. Around 34 ABY, the Resistance gunner Paige Tico wrote in her journal that pirates had been building bases inside the nebula for centuries, allowing them to organize hit-and-run attacks on nearby star systems.

title: Kamar
side_bar: {'Physical information': {'Fauna': 'Howlrunner'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Unidentified insectoid species'}}
paragraph: Kamar was an astronomical object that was home to a sentient insectoid species.

title: Kamino
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Extragalactic', 'System': ['Kamino system'], 'Moons': '3', 'Distance from Core': ['70', '000 light-years'], 'Rotation period': '27 hours', 'Orbital period': '463 standard days'}, 'Physical information': {'Diameter': ['19', '270 kilometers'], 'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Primary terrain': 'Oceans', 'Surface water': '100%', 'Fauna': ['Aiwha', 'Krill']}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Kaminoan', 'Immigrated species': 'Human', 'Primary language(s)': ['Galactic Basic', 'Kaminoan'], 'Government': 'Ruling Council', 'Population': '1 billion', 'Demonym': 'Kaminoa', 'Major cities': 'Tipoca City ', 'Major imports': 'Foodstuff', 'Major exports': ['Clones', 'Covert technology', 'Military hardware'], 'Affiliation': ['Sith Order', 'Galactic Republic']}}
paragraph: Kamino  was an aquatic planet located in an extragalactic star system that straggled south of the Rishi Maze satellite galaxy and beyond the larger galaxy. It was inhabited by the Kaminoansâa race of tall, elegant beings with long necks who were regarded as a mysterious species that tended to keep to themselves. They were also known for their cloning technology which ultimately led to the creation of a clone army for the Galactic Republic.

title: Karazak
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'P-19'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial'}}
paragraph: Karazak was a terrestrial world located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories, positioned at the coordinates P-19 on the Standard Galactic Grid. Karazak was known for its slavery, a trade that was tolerated, but also regulated, by the Galactic Empire. It shared its name with the slaver organization known as the Karazak Slavers' Cooperative.

title: Karfeddion
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': ['Mid Rim', 'Senex-Juvex'], 'Sector': 'Senex sector', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-18'}}
paragraph: Karfeddion was a planet located in the Senex sector within the galaxy's Mid Rim. Years prior to the Battle of Naboo, Q'anah's lover, a pirate leader in the Senex and member of House Elegin, was captured, sentenced to death, and executed on the planet. Karfeddion was connected via hyperspace route to Belsavis and Dolla.

title: Karideph
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-20', 'Trade routes': 'Rimma Trade Route'}}
paragraph: Karideph was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories, situated along the Rimma Trade Route.

title: Karlinus
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Sector': 'Chommell sector'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Climate': 'Humid'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': ['Human', 'Rodian'], 'Demonym': 'Karlini', 'Major exports': ['Grain', 'Karlini silk', 'Karlini tea'], 'Affiliation': 'Galactic Republic'}}
paragraph: Karlinus was a prosperous planet located in the Chommell sector of the galaxy's Mid Rim, known for its agricultural industry and its workforce with a high turnover rate. When PadmÃ© Amidala wished to rescue slaves from Tatooine, she and SabÃ© chose to let them live a new life on Karlinus. SabÃ© managed to rescue twenty-five slaves, giving them jobs on Karlinus with the help of the planet's governor, Kelma.

title: Kashyyyk
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Sector': 'Mytaranor sector', 'System': 'Kashyyyk system', 'Suns': '1', 'Moons': '3', 'Grid coordinates': 'P-9', 'Trade routes': ['Durkteel Loop', 'Great Kashyyyk Branch', 'Nightroad', 'Randon Run'], 'Rotation period': '26 hours', 'Orbital period': '381 days'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Diameter': ['12', '765 kilometers'], 'Climate': 'Temperate', 'Primary terrain': ['Forests', 'Jungles', 'Mountains'], 'Points of interest': ["Ashmead's Lock", 'Wawaatt Archipelago', 'Black Forest', 'Garden Preserve', 'Imperial Work Settlement #121', 'Kashyyyk oil refinery', "Lozen Tolruck's island fortress", 'River of Origin', 'Rowrakruk', 'Cargo Pad 119-Grek', 'Forest Trench', 'Imperial Refinery', 'Overgrown Pass', 'Kyyyalstaad Falls', 'Kyyyalstaad Basin', 'Gloomroot Hollow', 'Origin Lake', 'Shadowlands', 'Deserted Village', 'Origin Tree', 'Gnarled Heights', "Chieftain's Canopy"], 'Flora': ['Bonshyyyr', 'Jaw plant', 'Kashyyyk orchidfern', 'Kshyyy-vine', 'Lung plant', 'Saava', 'Shi-shok tree', 'Syren plant', 'Wroshyr trees', 'Mushbloom', 'Milk Grass'], 'Fauna': ['Anakkona', 'Arrawtha-dyr', 'Can-cells', 'Drriw-tcha blood-worm fly', 'Flame beetle', 'Gnasp', 'Kabatha', 'Katarn', 'Kinrath', 'Mykal', 'Oevvaor', 'Shyyyo bird', 'Slyyyg', 'Srifly', 'Tach', 'Terentatek', 'Webweaver', 'Wroshyr louse', 'Wyrm-weaver', 'Wyyyschokk', 'Albino Wyyyschokk']}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Wookiee', 'Primary language(s)': 'Shyriiwook', 'Government': 'Wookiee Council', 'Population': ['56', '000', '000'], 'Demonym': 'Kashyyykian', 'Major cities': ['Awrathakka', 'Kachirho', 'Rwookrrorro', 'Thikkiiana'], 'Major imports': 'Processed metals', 'Major exports': 'Electronic components', 'Affiliation': ['Czerka Arms', 'Galactic Republic', 'Galactic Empire', 'Alliance to Restore the Republic', 'Imperial territory G5-623', 'New Republic', 'First Order']}}
paragraph: Kashyyyk, also known as Planet Wookiee C to some humans in the Core Worlds, was a wroshyr tree-covered forest planet located in the southwestern quadrant of the galaxy and the homeworld of the Wookiee species. It was a member of the Galactic Republic and after the Clone Wars endured enslavement under the Galactic Empire. The planet was classified by the Empire as G5-623, but would be liberated shortly after its fall and the rise of the New Republic.

title: Katarr
paragraph: Katarr was a location studied by the Jedi Master and seer Oorallon, with the help of Padawan Qui-Gon Jinn.

title: Kattada
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Colonies', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-10'}}
paragraph: Kattada was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Colonies region.

title: Keitum
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'J-6'}, 'Societal information': {'Major cities': 'Cartherston'}}
paragraph: Keitum was a planet located in the galaxy's Mid Rim, connected via hyperspace route to Ansion. Cartherston was a city located on the planet.

title: Kelada
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Colonies', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-13', 'Trade routes': 'Corellian Trade Spine'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Points of interest': 'The Labyrinth'}}
paragraph: Kelada was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Colonies region, situated along the Corellian Trade Spine. The Labyrinth, a cantina owned by Lorana, was located on Kelada.

title: Keldooine
side_bar: {'General information': {'Location': ['Outer Rim Territories', 'Hutt Space']}}
paragraph: Keldooine was a world on the edge of the Hutt Space region of the Outer Rim Territories. The former pirate Queen Maz Kanata marked it as a point of interest on a map she included in the book that would become known as the Smuggler's Guide.

title: Kerkoidia
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-15'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Kerkoiden', 'Affiliation': ['Galactic Empire', 'New Republic']}}
paragraph: Kerkoidia was a blue-gray planet located in the Expansion Region, in the grid square N-15 of the Standard Galactic Grid. The Kerkoiden male Whorm Loathsom was a native of Kerkoidia and for a long time served in its planetary defense forces. Loathsom eventually earned the rank of general with the Confederacy of Independent Systems. In addition to Loathsom joining the Confederacy of Independent Systems, the Retail Caucus was headquarted on Kerkoida and was a large donor of the CIS. After the Battle of Endor, the New Republic managed to liberate Kerkoidia from the Galactic Empire.

title: Kessel
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Kessel sector', 'System': 'Kessel system', 'Moons': '3', 'Grid coordinates': 'T-10', 'Trade routes': ['Kessel Run', 'Pabol Sleheyron', 'Sanity Skip'], 'Rotation period': '12 hours', 'Orbital period': '322 days'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Diameter': ['7', '200 kilometers'], 'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Climate': ['Hot', 'humid'], 'Primary terrain': ['Barren spice mines in the north', 'lush sanctuaries in the south'], 'Points of interest': ['Spice mines of Kessel', 'Spice mine K76']}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': ['Dwuni', 'Gigoran', 'Human', 'Pyke', "Twi'lek", 'Wookiee'], 'Government': 'Monarchy', 'Population': ['10', '000'], 'Major imports': 'Slaves', 'Major exports': ['Coaxium', 'Kesselstone', 'Kessoline', 'Spice'], 'Affiliation': ['Yaruba Family of Kessel', 'Galactic Empire', 'Pyke Syndicate']}}
paragraph: Kessel was a planet within the Akkadese Maelstrom that hosted spice mines. The planet also exported coaxium and Kesselstone. While Kessel's northern hemisphere was devoted to mining, the planet's southern hemisphere was home to lush sanctuaries. During the Imperial Era, the Galactic Empire and Pyke Syndicate ran several mining operations that employed slave labor. These slave mining operations were targeted by various underworld and rebel factions.

title: Ketaris
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-5'}}
paragraph: Ketaris was an astronomical object in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Khomm
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Deep Core', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-12'}}
paragraph: Khomm was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Deep Core.

title: Kiffu
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Inner Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-14'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Kiffar'}}
paragraph: Kiffu was a planet located in the Inner Rim region of the galaxy. It was one of two home planets of the sentient Kiffar species, along with Kiffex. It was the homeworld of the human/Kiffar Jedi Master Quinlan Vos, who was active in the Jedi Order from at least 32 years before the Battle of Yavin until at least near the end of the Clone Wars.

title: Kinooine
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Wild Space', 'Grid coordinates': 'J-21'}}
paragraph: Kinooine was an astronomical object located in Wild Space, positioned at the coordinates J-21 on the Standard Galactic Grid.

title: Kinoss
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Unknown Regions', 'System': 'Kinoss system'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Chiss Ascendancy'}}
paragraph: Kinoss was a planet located in the Kinoss system of the Unknown Regions. It was situated within the borders of the Chiss Ascendancy.

title: Kinyen
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-15', 'Trade routes': 'Corellian Trade Spine'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': 'Kemalo Farming Cluster', 'Fauna': 'Houjix'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': ['Gran'], 'Major exports': 'Foodstuffs', 'Affiliation': 'Galactic Republic'}}
paragraph: Kinyen was an agriworld located in the galaxy's Expansion Region. on the Corellian Trade Spine. It along with the planet Malastare was the homeworld of the Gran, including both Philo and Kharrus, who served as the world's senators within the Galactic Republic during the Clone Wars.

title: Kira
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-16'}}
paragraph: Kira was an astronomical object located in the Expansion Region, in the grid square N-16 of the Standard Galactic Grid. Hyperspace routes linked Kira to the locations known as Pax, Kalinda, Bacrana, and Wroona.

title: Kiros
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region', 'System': 'Kiros system', 'Moons': 'At least 1'}, 'Physical information': {'Climate': 'Temperate', 'Primary terrain': ['Rivers', 'Valleys', 'Waterfalls'], 'Fauna': 'Kiros bird'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Togruta', 'Primary language(s)': 'Galactic Basic', 'Population': ['50', '000'], 'Major cities': 'Artisan colony', 'Affiliation': 'Confederacy of Independent Systems'}}
paragraph: Kiros was an idyllic world filled with vast green valleys and flowing waterfalls located in the galaxy's Expansion Region. The world was host to 50,000 Togruta colonists. The planet was ruled by Governor Roshti, who was contacted by Master Yoda just prior to the Separatist occupation of Kiros during the Clone Wars.

title: Kirtarkin
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Anoat sector'}, 'Physical information': {'Climate': 'Polluted', 'Points of interest': 'Imperial depots'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Kirtarkin was a planet located in the Anoat sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. The Galactic Empire had several depots on Kirtarkin that contained large recycling centers, though they were too late to save the world's polluted environment.

title: Kitel Phard
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': ['Core Worlds', 'The Interior'], 'Grid coordinates': 'J-12'}, 'Societal information': {'Government': 'Atrisian Emperor'}}
paragraph: Kitel Phard was an astronomical object located in the regions known as the Core Worlds and the Interior, in the grid square J-12 of the Standard Galactic Grid. A hyperspace route connected it to the planet Giju. Kitel Phard shared its name with the Kitel Phard dynasty. During the reign of the Galactic Empire, the latter was associated with a style of expensive vases.

title: Klatooine
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Hutt Space', 'Grid coordinates': 'S-9'}, 'Physical information': {'Primary terrain': 'Desert', 'Fauna': 'Klatooine paddy frog'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Klatooinian'}}
paragraph: Klatooine was a desert planet located within Hutt Space of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories that was the homeworld of the Klatooinian species. The xenolinguist Jaiyna Sibinth who studied the language of Pasaana's Aki-Aki saw similar recurring symbols and themes to the native cultures of other desert planets, including Klatooine's.

title: Koda Station
side_bar: {'General information': {'Location': 'Outer Rim Territories'}}
paragraph: Koda Station was a location in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Koiogra
side_bar: {'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial'}}
paragraph: Koiogra was a world which had been visited by the New Republic pilot Chass na Chadic. While on Koiogra, she discovered a recording of Jyn Erso's speech prior to the Battle of Scarif, realizing she had previously met the rebel on Uchinao a year earlier.

title: Kol Huro
side_bar: {'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial'}}
paragraph: Kol Huro was a terrestrial astronomical object. The journalist Caern Adan was detained and imprisoned by the Galactic Empire after he published a story about droid production forecasts on Kol Huro.

title: Kooriva
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Inner Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-14'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': 'Lebrasa Argente School for the Arts and Persuasive Sciences'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Koorivar', 'Affiliation': ['Galactic Republic', 'Corporate Alliance', 'Confederacy of Independent Systems']}}
paragraph: Kooriva was a planet located in the galaxy's Inner Rim.

title: Kothlis
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Sector': 'Bothan Space', 'Grid coordinates': 'R-14'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Alliance to Restore the Republic'}}
paragraph: Kothlis was an astronomical object located within Bothan Space of the galaxy's Mid Rim. Luke Skywalker was stationed on Kothlis during the conclusion of Princess Leia Organa's involvement in Operation Yellow Moon. Following the completion of her mission, Organa contacted Skywalker at Kothlis, from where he informed her that the Rebel Alliance had discovered the whereabouts of Han Solo, still trapped in carbonite. Organa informed Skywalker that she would tell him about an idea she had about a role she could play in their attempt to rescue Solo when she reached Kothlis.

title: Kowak
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Sevetta sector', 'System': 'Kowak system', 'Grid coordinates': 'S-16', 'Trade routes': "Slaver's Chain", 'Rotation period': '23 standard hours', 'Orbital period': '311 standard days'}, 'Physical information': {'Primary terrain': ['Oceans', 'Plateaus', 'Rainforests'], 'Points of interest': ["Lugubrious Mote's colony", "Salacious Crumb's hideout"], 'Flora': 'Pasol trees', 'Fauna': ['Kowakian monkey-lizard', 'Kowakian ape-lizard']}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Mole-flea', 'Primary language(s)': ['Galactic Basic', 'Huttese', 'Zygerrian'], 'Government': 'Colonial governorship', 'Population': ['200', '000 - 400', '000 enslaved sentients:', '21% Human', "19% Twi'lek", '15% Wookiee', '14% Rodian', '9% Togruta', '6% Ugnaught', '5% Other', '40', '000 - 60', '000 free sentients:', '62% Zygerrian', '21% Human', '14% Thalassian', '3% Other'], 'Major cities': ['Caden', 'Lanturi', 'Sclavos'], 'Major imports': ['Foodstuffs', 'Slaves', 'Technology'], 'Major exports': 'Slaves'}}
paragraph: Kowak was a planet located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories that was the homeworld of the Kowakian monkey-lizards, the kowakian ape-lizards, and mole-fleas.

title: Kril'Dor
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'I-7'}, 'Societal information': {'Major exports': 'Tibanna'}}
paragraph: Kril'Dor was a planet located in the galaxy's Mid Rim that was a source of tibanna gas. Located close to the Uba system, Kril'Dor was positioned at the coordinates I-7 on the Standard Galactic Grid.

title: Kriselist
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'K-16', 'Trade routes': 'Corellian Trade Spine'}}
paragraph: Kriselist was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim.

title: Ktil
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Inner Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-9'}}
paragraph: Ktil was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Inner Rim.

title: Kuat
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Core Worlds', 'Sector': 'Kuat sector', 'System': 'Kuat system', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-10'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Points of interest': "Gideon Hask's house"}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': ['Human', 'Kuati'], 'Major exports': 'Civilian and military starships', 'Affiliation': ['Galactic Republic', 'Galactic Empire', 'New Republic']}}
paragraph: Kuat was a vital shipbuilding and industrial planet located in the Kuat system of the galaxy's Core Worlds region. Known for the prestigious Kuat Drive Yards corporation and its large shipyards, the planet notably produced warships for both the Galactic Republic and Galactic Empire.

title: Kubindi
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'System': "Ku'Bakai system", 'Suns': "1: Kubindi's star", 'Grid coordinates': 'T-9'}, 'Physical information': {'Fauna': 'Picolet beetle'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Kubaz', 'Primary language(s)': 'Kubazian', 'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Kubindi was a planet located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories that was the homeworld of the insectivorous Kubaz species. Its population was enslaved by the Galactic Empire, and the Kubaz spy and Kubindi native Garindan ezz Zavor plotted to free his world and its people from Imperial oppression.

title: Kuna's Eye
side_bar: {'General information': {'Location': ['Moddell sector', 'Outer Rim Territories']}}
paragraph: Kuna's Eye was a location in the Moddell sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Prior to the Battle of Endor in 4 ABY, Corporal Ractivelle of the Stardust unit featured Kuna's Eye in a map as part of a Rebel Alliance report on the navigation of the Moddell sector in preparation for the Rebel Alliance's attack on the second Death Star.

title: Kuna's Fist
side_bar: {'General information': {'Location': ['Moddell sector', 'Outer Rim Territories']}}
paragraph: Kuna's Fist was a location in the Moddell sector of the Outer Rim Territories. In preparation for the Battle of Endor in 4 ABY, Corporal Ractivelle of the Stardust unit compiled a report on the navigation of the Moddell sector on behalf of the Rebel Alliance, and featured Kuna's Fist.

title: Kuna's Horn
side_bar: {'General information': {'Location': ['Moddell sector', 'Outer Rim Territories']}}
paragraph: Kuna's Horn was a location in the Moddell sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Before the Battle of Endor in 4 ABY, Kuna's Horn was featured in a map by Corporal Ractivelle of the Stardust unit as part of the Rebel Alliance's preparation for their attack on the second Death Star.

title: Kuna's Tail
side_bar: {'General information': {'Location': ['Moddell sector', 'Outer Rim Territories']}}
paragraph: Kuna's Tail was a location in the Moddell sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Before the Battle of Endor in 4 ABY, Kuna's Tail was featured as part of a map composed by Corporal Ractivelle of the Stardust unit for the preparation of the Rebel Alliance's attack on the second Death Star.

title: Kuna's Tooth
side_bar: {'General information': {'Location': ['Moddell sector', 'Outer Rim Territories']}}
paragraph: Kuna's Tooth was a location in the Moddell sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Before the Battle of Endor in 4 ABY, Kuna's Tooth was featured in a map by Corporal Ractivelle of the Stardust unit as part of the Rebel Alliance's preparation for their attack on the second Death Star.

title: Kwenn
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'R-10'}}
paragraph: Kwenn was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim.

title: Lah'mu
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Raioballo sector', 'System': "Lah'mu system", 'Moons': '1; formerly more', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-3'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Diameter': ['12', '618 km'], 'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Primary terrain': ['Black sand and beaches', 'Fertile lowlands', 'Plateaus', 'mountains'], 'Points of interest': ["Chief's fortress", 'Erso homestead'], 'Fauna': 'None'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'None', 'Immigrated species': 'Humans', 'Population': 'Estimated: less than 500'}}
paragraph: Lah'mu was a ringed agrarian planet in the Raioballo sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Its small population of settlers included the Erso family, who relocated to Lah'mu after the Clone Wars, and were ultimately tracked down by Director Orson Callan Krennic years later.

title: Lahsbane
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'R-15'}}
paragraph: Lahsbane was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim. During Dooku's time as a Jedi Padawan, Master Yoda took him on a voyage to Lahsbane, which he later chronicled in his journal.

title: Lamaredd
paragraph: Lamaredd was a location in the galaxy where the Quarren pirate Isquik Tors was active prior to his capture by the bounty hunter Boba Fett in 7972 C.R.C. Imperial Security Bureau agent Andressa Divo mentioned Lamaredd while writing to her father Tanivos Divo about Tors's capture.

title: Lannik
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'R-13'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Lannik'}}
paragraph: Lannik was a planet with a long history of war that was located in the galaxy's Mid Rim and was the homeworld of the Lannik species.

title: Lanteeb
side_bar: {'Physical information': {'Fauna': "Maxilan's explosive bloatworm"}}
paragraph: Lanteeb was a planet that was the origin of Maxilan's explosive bloatworm.

title: Lantillies
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'P-8', 'Trade routes': ['Perlemian Trade Route', 'Randon Run']}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Human', 'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Lantillies was a world located in the galaxy's Mid Rim, at the confluence of the Perlemian Trade Route and the Randon Run. By 14 BBY, it hosted an Imperial base. When the corvette Carrion Spike was stolen from Imperial Governor Wilhuff Tarkin by a rebel cell and used to attack TaggeCo mining facilities on Lucazec, Imperial forces stationed at Lantillies and Centares were moved in triage redeployments to try and protect other Imperial assets that might be attacked. Vice Admiral Dodd Rancitâwho was secretly one of those behind the attacksâlater outlined fears to Galactic Emperor Sheev Palpatine that Lantillies itself might be a potential target since it was no longer as protected due to the redeployments; however, the base was never attacked by the corvette as the rebel cell was destroyed by Tarkin. Lantillies was the homeworld of Resistance bombardier Nix Jerd.

title: Leritor
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'Q-15'}}
paragraph: Leritor was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim.

title: Lettow
paragraph: Lettow, known as "Old Lettow", was a location mentioned in Our Empire's Army, an Imperial marching song that Zare Leonis and other Imperial cadets sang during their morning running drills.

title: Lexrul
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim'}, 'Societal information': {'Major cities': 'Sativran City'}}
paragraph: Lexrul was a heavily industrialized planet in the galaxy's Mid Rim. Orson Callan Krennic was born in Sativran City on the planet in 51 BBY.

title: Lianna
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Tion Cluster', 'Grid coordinates': 'S-6', 'Trade routes': 'Perlemian Trade Route'}}
paragraph: Lianna was an astronomical object located in the Tion Cluster of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories that was home to the powerful Santhe family.

title: Lipsec
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'I-18'}}
paragraph: Lipsec was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Listehol
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'Q-4', 'Trade routes': 'Hydian Way'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Unidentified species'}}
paragraph: Listehol was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. Located on the Hydian Way, it was also connected to Mirial by another hyperspace route. It was the homeworld of the tyrant Baron Yasto Attsmun, captain of the Undisputed Victor on Cantonica.

title: Llanic
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'System': 'Llanic system', 'Grid coordinates': 'Q-16', 'Trade routes': ['Llanic Spice Route', 'Triellus Spice Route']}}
paragraph: Llanic was a planet located in the Llanic system within the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. It was situated at the intersection of the Llanic Spice Route and the Triellus Trade Route. Bustling with smugglers and other shady characters, Llanic was considered to be similar to Mos Eisley. The Galactic Empire kept watch on Llanic due to the illicit credits that circulated there.

title: Lok
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'Q-17'}}
paragraph: Lok was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Lola Sayu
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Belderone sector', 'System': 'Lola Sayu system'}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Primary terrain': 'Volcanic', 'Points of interest': ['Citadel', 'Point Tarron', 'Sulfur Sea']}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': ['Galactic Republic', 'Confederacy of Independent Systems', 'New Republic']}}
paragraph: Lola Sayu was a sulfurous, cracked planet that was home to the Citadel, a prison engineered to hold Jedi, during the Clone Wars.

title: Loovria
paragraph: Loovria was a location in the galaxy.

title: Lorahns
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'P-14'}}
paragraph: Lorahns was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim.

title: Loronar
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Colonies', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-12', 'Trade routes': 'Corellian Run'}}
paragraph: Loronar was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Colonies region that was situated along the Corellian Run. During the early rebellion against the Galactic Empire, the intelligence branch of the Rebel Alliance witnessed a spike in transmitter traffic from Loronar. Alliance Intelligence was able to deduce that a constellation of Torpedo Spheres were active. Paired with intelligence on equipment suppliers, Colonel Haxen Delto expressed to Chief of Rebel Intelligence General Airen Cracken that they should be worried.

title: Lorrd
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-4'}}
paragraph: Lorrd was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. During the early rebellion against the Galactic Empire, Freemarch had operations on Lorrd.

title: Lorta
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'J-17'}}
paragraph: Lorta was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim.

title: Lothal
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Lothal sector', 'System': 'Lothal system', 'Suns': "1: Lothal's sun", 'Moons': '2', 'Grid coordinates': 'U-7', 'Trade routes': 'Outer Rim trade route'}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Climate': 'Temperate', 'Primary terrain': ['Mountainous', 'Prairies', 'Rock formations', 'Semi-arid savannah', 'Marshes'], 'Surface water': 'Shallow inland seas', 'Points of interest': ['Boo Boo barn', 'Clustered rock spires', 'Dinar', 'Easthills', 'Far Hiradne', 'Haven', 'Imperial Armory Complex', 'Imperial Communications Center', 'Kinpany Gap', 'Krai family farm', "Lando Calrissian's farm", 'Lothal cliff dwelling', 'Lothal Jedi Temple', 'Lothal re-settlement camp 43', 'Lothal resistance camp', 'Lothal wolf den', 'LothalNet comm tower E-272', 'Monad Outpost', "Morad Sumar's farm", 'Pelamir Gorge', 'Pretor Flats', "Ryder's camp", 'Sienar Advanced Projects Laboratory', "Stel's uncle's repair shop", 'Tangletown', 'Westhills'], 'Flora': 'Spine tree', 'Fauna': ['Bloodfly', 'Crickbeet', 'Edgehawk', 'Loth-bat', 'Loth-cat', 'Loth-rat', 'Nek', 'Nerf', 'Sabercat', 'Snot-hopper']}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Loth-wolf', 'Immigrated species': ['Anx', 'Aqualish', 'Balosar', 'Bardottan', 'Chagrian', 'Devaronian', 'Feeorin', 'Gotal', 'Houk', 'Human', 'Ithorian', 'Rodian', 'Ruurian', 'Sakiyan', 'Ugnaught', 'Xexto'], 'Primary language(s)': ['Aqualish', 'Galactic Basic', 'Huttese', 'Ithorese'], 'Government': ["Lothal's planetary government", 'Imperial governorship'], 'Demonym': ['Lothalian', 'Lothalite'], 'Major cities': ['Capital City', 'Jalath', 'Kothal'], 'Major imports': ['Agricultural equipment', 'Industrial machinery', 'Raw materials'], 'Major exports': ['Doonium', 'Foodstuffs', 'Starfighters', 'Starship components', 'Technology'], 'Affiliation': ['Jedi Order', 'Galactic Republic', 'Galactic Empire', 'First Order']}}
paragraph: Lothal was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories. During the early years of the Galactic Empire, Lothal was in a state of economic disrepair and invited the Empire to take over the planet's industries, with the promise of prosperity and security. Although many people said the Empire would bring doom, the ones preaching new jobs and prosperity were vindicated. By 5 BBY, Lothal became the nesting ground for the Spectres, a small rebel cell which operated from the starship Ghost. After harrying Imperial forces and disrupting Imperial activities for at least a year, the Spectres eventually attracted the attention of Grand Moff Wilhuff Tarkin and Darth Vader, who tried unsuccessfully to stamp out these rebels. Vader even imposed a blockade on the planet, but the Spectres managed to slip through and rejoin the larger rebellion.

title: Lowick
paragraph: Lowick was the swampy homeworld of the Pa'lowick singer Sy Snootles.

title: Lucazec
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'Q-6', 'Trade routes': 'Salin Corridor'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Lucazec was an astronomical object located in the Outer Rim Territories along the Salin Corridor that was controlled by the Galactic Empire. A group of rebels once stole an Imperial corvette known as the Carrion Spike and launched an attack on the Empire's mining operations on Lucazec, controlled through TaggeCo. They broadcasted a holovid of their activities.

title: Lutrillia
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Greater Javin', 'Grid coordinates': 'J-18'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Lutrillian'}}
paragraph: Lutrillia was a planet in the Greater Javin Region of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories that was the homeworld of the Lutrillian species.

title: Lwhekk
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Unknown Regions', 'Grid coordinates': 'C-16'}}
paragraph: Lwhekk was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Unknown Regions.

title: Lyran
paragraph: Lyran was a world in the galaxy where Chass na Chadic, pilot in the New Republic's Alphabet Squadron, had once visited. Several weeks after the Battle of Endor in 4 ABY, Chadick and her squadron visited a Jedi temple on the moon of the planet Harkrova I, where they found a holographic map of the galaxy. Chadick recognized Lyran in this map.

title: M'haeli
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-15'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': "D'olop mountain range"}, 'Societal information': {'Major exports': 'Dragite gems'}}
paragraph: M'haeli was an agriworld located in the galaxy's Expansion Region. The world contained the D'olop mountain range, where dragite gems were mined for use in lightsabers.

title: Maires
side_bar: {'General information': {'Fauna': 'Mairan'}}
paragraph: Maires was the homeworld of the Mairan species.

title: Makem Te
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Orbital position': 'S-5', 'Trade routes': 'Perlemian Trade Route'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Swokes Swokes'}}
paragraph: Makem Te was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories that was the homeworld of the Swokes Swokes species. It was located close to one end of the Perlemian Trade Route, which connected it to the planets Quermia and Desevro.

title: Malachor
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Chorlian sector', 'System': 'Malachor system', 'Moons': 'At least 2'}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Primary terrain': ['Rocky wastes', 'barren'], 'Points of interest': ['Malachor Sith Temple', 'Malachor superweapon'], 'Fauna': 'Convor'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': ['Dathomirian Zabrak'], 'Primary language(s)': 'Old tongue', 'Population': 'At least 1: Maul ', 'Affiliation': 'Sith'}}
paragraph: Malachor was a rocky, hellish wasteland planet located in the Chorlian sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories region. It was a planet shrouded in mystery, and the location of an event known as the Great Scourge of Malachor, which took place thousands of years before the rise of the Empire. The Great Scourge was an ancient battle at Malachor's Sith temple between the Sith and the Jedi Order, which saw a superweapon activated, killing and petrifying all the participants of the battle, remaining for years after.

title: Malagarr
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'V-8'}}
paragraph: Malagarr was an astronomical object located within the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Malastare
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Sector': 'Dustig sector', 'System': 'Malastare system', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-16', 'Trade routes': ['Biox Detour', 'Hydian Way']}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Climate': 'Temperate', 'Primary terrain': ['Forests', 'Rocky'], 'Points of interest': ['Imperial palace', 'Malastare communications station', 'Malastare Narrows', "Pandion's vacation palace"], 'Fauna': ['Insectomorph', 'Zillo Beast']}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Dug', 'Immigrated species': ['Gran', 'Human'], 'Government': 'Dug Council', 'Demonym': 'Malastarian', 'Major cities': 'Pixelito', 'Major exports': 'Malastarian fuel', 'Affiliation': ['Galactic Republic', 'Galactic Empire', "Kenner Loring's faction"]}}
paragraph: Malastare was a forested planet located in the Malastare system of the Mid Rim, situated along the Hydian Way. Its core was home to large reserves of Malastarian fuel, a toxic fuel found only on Malastare. It was the homeworld of the Dug species, though it was represented in the Galactic Senate by the Gran species, who had colonised Malastare. Ainlee Teem, the senator of Malastare, was nominated in the election for Supreme Chancellor during the Invasion of Naboo. During the Clone Wars, Malastare was the location of a battle between the Galactic Republic and the Confederacy of Independent Systems over the planet's fuel reserves. The battle awoke a creature known as the Zillo Beast, which the Republic successfully neutralized, leading the Dug Council to sign a treaty with the Republic allowing them access to their fuel reserves.

title: Maltha Obex
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'O-3'}}
paragraph: Maltha Obex was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Manaan
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Inner Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'O-11'}, 'Physical information': {'Primary terrain': 'Oceans'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Selkath'}}
paragraph: Manaan was an ocean planet located in the galaxy's Inner Rim, in grid square O-11 on the Standard Galactic Grid. It was the homeworld of the sentient Selkath species, which had been historically devoted to the care of their native oceans. The Selkath bounty hunters Mantu and Chata Hyoki hailed from Manaan.

title: Manda
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'R-15'}}
paragraph: Manda was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim with plenty of transport. The freighter Eclipse once set course in hyperspace to Manda to drop off several of its crewmembers. Tibbs Ospe, the owner of the Lodge on the planet Vandor, thought that Vandor might make a good stop for traders heading to Manda or Deneba, so by 10 BBY, he had fixed the ruins of Ypsobay Trading Company's old headquarters, filled in craters in old landing strips, and let people know they could find fuel and food at Fort Ypso.

title: Mandalore
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Mandalore sector', 'System': 'Mandalore system', 'Moons': 'Concordia', 'Grid coordinates': 'O-7', 'Rotation period': '19 standard hours', 'Orbital period': '366 standard days'}, 'Physical information': {'Diameter': ['9', '200 kilometers'], 'Atmosphere': 'Breathable but Inhospitable', 'Climate': 'Hot and dry', 'Primary terrain': ['Desert', 'Domed cities'], 'Points of interest': ['Royal Academy of Government/Imperial Academy of Mandalore', 'Mandalore Banking Center', 'Mandalore prison outpost', 'Peace Park', 'Royal prison', 'Statue of Tarre Vizsla', 'Sundari Royal Palace'], 'Fauna': ['Galaar', 'Shriek-hawk']}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Human', 'Primary language(s)': ['Galactic Basic', "Mando'a"], 'Government': ['Duchess', "Mand'alor", 'Prime Minister', 'Viceroy', 'Governor'], 'Population': ['4', '000', '000:', '81% humans', '19% other'], 'Demonym': 'Mandalorian', 'Major cities': ['Keldabe', 'Ronion', 'Sundari'], 'Major imports': 'Raw materials', 'Major exports': ['Mercenaries', 'starships'], 'Affiliation': ['Mandalorians', 'New Mandalorians', 'Shadow Collective', 'Galactic Empire']}}
paragraph: Mandalore was a planet located in the Outer Rim Territories. It was the homeworld of the Mandalorians, a fearsome warrior people who fought the Jedi and raided their temple during the fall of the Old Republic. Wearing distinctive armor that was often made from Beskar, they were feared throughout the galaxy, and had political influence over two thousand other star systems.

title: Manpha
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'K-20', 'Trade routes': 'Corellian Trade Spine'}, 'Physical information': {'Primary terrain': 'Swamp'}}
paragraph: Manpha was a swampy, wet Outer Rim planet and the homeworld of the Shawda Ubb musician Rappertunie. Located on the Corellian Trade Spine, it was positioned at the coordinates K-20 on the Standard Galactic Grid.

title: Mantooine
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Atrivis sector'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': ['Galactic Empire', 'Alliance to Restore the Republic']}}
paragraph: Mantooine was an astronomical object located in the Atrivis sector where an Imperial garrison was based. In 14 AFE, a resistance group known as the Liberators managed to seize the garrison but were soon defeated by the Imperial Navy in the same year.

title: Maridun
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Rolion sector', 'System': 'Maridun system', 'Suns': '1', 'Grid coordinates': 'Q-6'}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Climate': 'Temperate', 'Primary terrain': ['Plains', 'Savannas'], 'Points of interest': ['Lurmen village', 'Separatist outpost'], 'Fauna': ['Carrier butterflies', 'Mastiff phalones']}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Amani', 'Immigrated species': 'Lurmen'}}
paragraph: Maridun was a planet located in the Rolion sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It was a temperate and verdant world, with a comfortable climate despite its challenging ecosystem and dangerous predators. Covered in grassy plains where large seed pods grew, it was the homeworld of the Amanin and was inhabited by mastiff phalones.

title: Mataou
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Anoat sector', 'System': 'Mataou system', 'Moons': 'Nar Hypa', 'Grid coordinates': 'K-18', 'Trade routes': ['Corellian Trade Spine', 'Ison Trade Corridor']}, 'Physical information': {'Climate': 'Hot', 'Primary terrain': 'Desert', 'Points of interest': ['Gnuda Kajidic ancestral estate', 'Imperial garrison', 'Necropolis', 'Shrine of Dynasties', "Yantuh's palace"], 'Fauna': 'Ro hypa'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': ['Hutts', 'Gnuda Kajidic', 'Kouhun', 'Galactic Empire']}}
paragraph: Mataou was a hot desert planet located in the Mataou system, in the Anoat sector of the Outer Rim Territories, on the edge of the Ivax Nebula. Long before the Galactic Civil War, Mataou was ruled by Hutts, including the Gnuda Kajidic. In their heyday, the Hutts of Mataou established vast settlements in the classical architectural Hutt style.

title: Maya Kovel
side_bar: {'General information': {'Location': ['Moddell sector', 'Outer Rim Territories']}}
paragraph: Maya Kovel was a location in the galaxy's Moddell sector. It was near Thonner and Vasha.

title: Mechis III
side_bar: {'Chronological and political information': {'Affiliation': 'Techno Union'}}
paragraph: Mechis III was a vital Techno Union world located in the galaxy. It was defended by a mix of starships from member corporations and design firms such as SoroSuub Corporation.

title: Media
paragraph: The media were the means of communication with which information could be transmitted to the public. Publication was a type of media.

title: Mephout
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Wild Space', 'Grid coordinates': 'H-20'}}
paragraph: Mephout was an astronomical object located in Wild Space, positioned at the coordinates H-20 on the Standard Galactic Grid.

title: Metalorn
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'R-8'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': 'Unreal City'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Skakoan', 'Affiliation': ['Techno Union', 'Confederacy of Independent Systems', 'Galactic Empire', 'New Republic']}}
paragraph: Metalorn was an industrial planet located in the galaxy's Mid Rim. A vital Techno Union world, it was aligned with the Confederacy of Independent Systems during the Clone Wars. Its Skakoan population was enslaved by the Galactic Empire for their Separatists sympathies, causing some to join the Alliance to Restore the Republic. Metalorn's production capacity supported the Imperial Military during the Galactic Civil War, causing the Rebel Alliance to consider it a potential target. The Skakoan Wat Tambor began his career in techology on Metalorn, going on to become Foreman of the Techno Union.

title: Metellos
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Core Worlds', 'Trade routes': 'Metellos-Ilum hyperspace route'}}
paragraph: Metellos was a planet in the galaxy's Core Worlds region connected via hyperspace route to the planet Ilum. The route was mapped by hyperspace surveyors hired by the Jedi Order as Ilum was a world important to the training of a Jedi.

title: Mexeluine
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Anoat sector'}}
paragraph: Mexeluine was a planet located in the Anoat sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Mijos
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Anoat sector'}, 'Physical information': {'Primary terrain': 'Swamps'}}
paragraph: Mijos was a planet located in the Anoat sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. It was covered in swamps inhabited by savage beasts.

title: Milagro
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region', 'Grid coordinates': 'O-14', 'Trade routes': 'Corellian Run'}}
paragraph: Milagro was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Expansion Region, located on the Corellian Run hyperspace route.

title: Milvayne
side_bar: {'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Atmosphere': 'Breathable'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Humans', 'Demonym': 'Milvaynian', 'Major cities': 'Milvayne City', 'Affiliation': ['Milvayne Authority', 'Galactic Empire']}}
paragraph: Milvayne was a planet controlled by the Milvayne Authority, a harsh, justice-oriented law enforcement agency. After the establishment of the Galactic Empire, Milvayne fell under its protection, under the terms it kept an invisible presence. Milvayne's law enforcement made it a good example for the Empire, and it was promoted through propaganda as an ideal world. After being linked with proximity bombs by Cornelius Evazan, Chelli Aphra and 0-0-0 traveled to Milvayne, where they were forced to evade the law as fugitives. After Evazan widened the broadcast from Triple Zero's eyes to reach the residents of Milvayne, the Empire's Coalition for Progress wished to intervene to prevent the live feed from inspiring mischievous ideas. They were eventually forced to fire on Milvayne City as the chase escalated.

title: Mimban
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region', 'Sector': 'Circarpous sector', 'System': 'Circarpous system', 'Moons': 'Minemoon', 'Grid coordinates': 'O-12'}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Climate': 'Humid', 'Primary terrain': ['Mud fields', 'Rainforests', 'Swamps'], 'Points of interest': ['Camp Forward', 'Nanth flatlands', 'Southern marshlands', 'Station 3-7']}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': ['Greenie', 'Mimbanese'], 'Demonym': 'Mimbanese', 'Major exports': 'Hyperbaride', 'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Mimban, formally known as Circarpous V, was a swamp planet located in the Circarpous sector of the galaxy's Expansion Region that was the homeworld of several intelligent species, including the Mimbanese. For many decades, it was the site of conflict between its natives and mining interests attracted by the planet's deep hyperbaride mineral deposits. During the Clone Wars, the Mud Jumpers of the Grand Army of the Republic's 224th Division helped the Mimbanese Liberation Army repel the invading Separatist Droid Army. Following the rise of the Galactic Empire, the 224th returned to Mimban as part of the Imperial Army to subjugate the Mimbanese and ensure Imperial energy mining operations continued unabated.

title: Minashee
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Sector': 'Cassandran Worlds'}}
paragraph: Minashee was the homeworld of the Jedi Master Sifo-Dyas, whose father worked as a fisherman. It was part of the Cassandran Worlds.

title: Mindor
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Inner Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-8'}}
paragraph: Mindor was an astronomical object in the Inner Rim of the galaxy.

title: Minntooine
side_bar: {'Chronological and political information': {'Affiliation': ['Confederacy of Independent Systems', 'Commerce Guild']}}
paragraph: Minntooine was a world off the end of the Perlemian Trade Route where the Commerce Guild had major interests. During the Clone Wars, where the Guild sided with the Confederacy of Independent Systems, the world was protected by Diamond-class cruisers, Recusant-class Commerce Guild destroyers and Guild corvettes and bombers.

title: Mirial
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'System': 'Mirial system', 'Grid coordinates': 'Q-4'}, 'Physical information': {'Climate': 'Cold and dry', 'Primary terrain': 'Desert'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Mirialan'}}
paragraph: Mirial was a cold and dry desert planet located in the Mirial system of the Outer Rim Territories. It was the homeworld of the near-human Mirialan species including the Jedi Master Luminara Unduli and her Padawan Barriss Offee. Unduli honored the traditions of the world by selecting a fellow Mirialan as her apprentice.

title: Molavar
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'S-15', 'Trade routes': ['Manda Merchant Run', 'Triellus Trade Route']}}
paragraph: Molavar was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories, on the junction of the Triellus Trade Route and the Manda Merchant Run, just a short jump south of Scarif.

title: Moltok
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-5'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': "Unidentified Ho'Din settlement"}}
paragraph: Moltok was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories that was home to a Ho'Din settlement. During the reign of the Galactic Empire, the settlement came under attack from a local Makurth boss leading the Ho'Din to request the aid of Imperial muscle to prevent the crisis from becoming a full-fledged war. Imperial forces stationed aboard the Gozanti-class cruiser Blood Crow under the command of Captain Filia Rossi were sent to settle the matter.

title: Mon Calamari
side_bar: {'Biological classification': {'Designation': 'Sentient', 'Classification': 'Amphibious humanoid'}, 'Physical characteristics': {'Skin color': ['Brown', 'Cyan', 'Blue', 'Gold', 'Green', 'Grey', 'Mottled', 'Orange', 'Pink', 'Red', 'Reddish brown', 'Salmon', 'White'], 'Eye color': ['Blue', 'Gray', 'Green', 'Orange', 'Yellow'], 'Distinctions': ['Large', 'goggle-like eyes', 'high-domed heads', 'webbed hands']}, 'Sociocultural characteristics': {'Homeworld': 'Mon Cala', 'Habitat': 'Ocean'}}
paragraph: The Mon Calamari were a humanoid, aquatic species native to the planet of Mon Cala. They shared their home planet with the Quarren.

title: Mon Gazza
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'Q-16', 'Trade routes': 'Corellian Run'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': ["Ravi's palace", 'Zugga Challenge']}, 'Societal information': {'Major exports': 'Spice', 'Affiliation': 'Pyke Syndicate'}}
paragraph: Mon Gazza was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim along the Corellian Run. It hosted raw spice mining operations, which were controlled by the Pyke Syndicate during the Clone Wars. At some point, it hosted podraces.

title: Monastery
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'Q-16'}}
paragraph: Monastery was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim, in grid square Q-16 on the Standard Galactic Grid.

title: Moorja
side_bar: {'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Human'}}
paragraph: Moorja was a planet that was once home to Zare Leonis and his family.

title: Morellia
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Sector': 'Morellian Commonwealth'}}
paragraph: Morellia was a planet in the galaxy. Prior to the Galactic Civil War, Auric Graf gave an emerald pendant to his wife, Rhyssa, while on Morellia.

title: Mortis
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Wild Space', 'Sector': 'Unknown', 'System': 'Chrelythiumn syste', 'Suns': 'None'}, 'Physical information': {'Primary terrain': ['Floating mountains', 'lush forests', 'molten caverns'], 'Points of interest': ['Altar of Mortis', "Daughter's grave", 'Mortis monastery', 'Mortis monolith', "Son's cathedral", 'Well of the Dark Side']}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Force-wielders', 'Population': ['3:Father', 'Daughter', 'Son']}}
paragraph: Mortis was an ethereal realm within the Force which was whispered over in legends and stories passed down through the millennia by Jedi, Sith, and the average spacer alike. It was believed to have existed outside any star system, and potentially the galaxy or even the universe. Some believed that the origins of the Force came from Mortis.

title: Mugaar
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'K-18', 'Trade routes': 'Corellian Trade Spine'}}
paragraph: Mugaar was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim.

title: Munto Codru
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'T-6'}}
paragraph: Munto Codru was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Murk
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Moddell sector', 'Trade routes': 'Sanctuary Pipeline'}}
paragraph: Murk was an astronomical object located in the Moddell sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It lay on the Sanctuary Pipeline, a hyperspace route that connected the Moddell sector moon of Endor to the Sullust sector planet Sullust. Murk was depicted on a map of the Moddell sector included with the Rebel Alliance collection of non-electronic documents known as The Rebel Files.

title: Murkhana
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Tion Cluster', 'System': 'Murkhana system', 'Grid coordinates': 'S-6'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': ['Argente Tower', 'Corporate Alliance landing field', 'Corporate Alliance medcenter']}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': ['Aqualish', 'Chagrian', 'Gossam', 'Gran', 'Human', 'Koorivar', 'Sugi'], 'Major cities': 'Murkhana City', 'Affiliation': ['Confederacy of Independent Systems', 'Corporate Alliance', 'Galactic Empire']}}
paragraph: Murkhana was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories. Known for its natural beauty, it was a major tourist attraction in the last years of the Republic Era. During the Clone Wars, the world became a major Separatist bastion; consequently, much of its environment was destroyed by a Republic orbital bombardment. By the Imperial Era, Murkhana was an impoverished, polluted world crippled by Imperial sanctions and a ruined environment. The planet was also a crime haven that was dominated by smugglers and crime lords such as the Sugi Faazah. In 14 BBY, the insurgent leader Berch Teller stole Moff Wilhuff Tarkin's corvette Carrion Spike whilst the latter, along with Darth Vader, were investigating a communications cache in Murkhana City.

title: Mustafar
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': ['Western Reaches', 'Outer Rim Territories'], 'Sector': 'Atravis sector', 'System': 'Mustafar system', 'Suns': '1', 'Orbital position': ['Third planet from the sun', 'overlapping orbit'], 'Moons': '0', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-19', 'Rotation period': '36 standard hours', 'Orbital period': '412 local rotations'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Diameter': ['4', '200 kilometers'], 'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Climate': ['Hot', 'ash-laden', 'and stormy'], 'Primary terrain': ['Forests', 'Glens', 'Lava oceans', 'Lava rivers', 'Molten rock plains', 'Lava pits', 'Obsidian mountain ranges', 'Obsidian shores', 'Volcanoes'], 'Surface water': 'Lacking to support even traditional farms underground.', 'Points of interest': ['Black Sun fortress', "Darth Sidious's secret facility", 'Gahenn Plains', 'Corvax Fen', 'Corvax Fortress', 'Fortress Vader', 'Imperial base', 'Sith cave', 'Sith temple', 'The Last Resort', 'Mensix Mining Facility', 'Mustafar droid factory', 'Mustafarian Mining Complex', 'Tulrus Island', "Ziton's palace"], 'Flora': ['Irontree', 'Kahel cave fungus'], 'Fauna': ['Darkghast', 'Fire rat', 'Krishel', 'Lava eel', 'Lava flea', 'Lava nymph', 'Lizard-crow', 'Mustafar beetle', 'Roggwart', 'Spark-roach', 'Xandank']}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Mustafarian', 'Immigrated species': ['Falleen', 'Human', 'A large variety of other species'], 'Primary language(s)': 'Mustafarian', 'Population': ['Approximately 15', '000', 'â20', '000'], 'Demonym': 'Mustafarian', 'Major cities': ['Fralideja', 'Zitontown'], 'Major imports': 'Water', 'Major exports': ['Dolovite', 'Lava', 'minerals', 'and metal ore'], 'Affiliation': ['Sith', 'Techno Union', 'Black Sun', 'Confederacy of Independent Systems', 'Mining Guild', 'Galactic Empire']}}
paragraph: Mustafar was a small planet located in the Mustafar system, within the Atravis sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. Once a garden world nourished by the Bright Star artifact, its orbit was shifted when Lady Corvax unleashed the energies of the Bright Star in an attempt to return her husband to life. The resulting gravimetric duel between the gas giants Jestefad and Lefrani over Mustafar heated the planet's core, transforming the lush world into an imbalanced volcanic hellscape. Adapting to life on their devastated homeworld, the arthropodal Mustafarians evolved into two distinct subspecies that cooperated to ensure their continued survival. Legends of Corvax's search for immortality brought the ancient Sith to Mustafar, seeking the same secrets of eternal life. There, they built a temple over a locus in the dark side of the Force, above the buried ruins of Corvax Fortress.

title: Muunilinst
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'K-4'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Muun', 'Affiliation': ['InterGalactic Banking Clan', 'Muunilinst Banking Clan']}}
paragraph: Muunilinst was a planet located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories that was home to a division of the InterGalactic Banking Clan and inhabited by members of the Muun species.

title: Mygeeto
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'K-5'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Climate': 'Frigid', 'Primary terrain': 'Crystalline', 'Points of interest': ['Mygeeto Hammertong facility', 'Southern Mesas']}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Lurmen', 'Affiliation': ['InterGalactic Banking Clan', 'Muunilinst Banking Clan', 'Confederacy of Independent Systems', 'Galactic Empire']}}
paragraph: Mygeeto was a frigid, crystalline planet located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories that was the homeworld of the Lurmen species. An InterGalactic Banking Clan stronghold, it was aligned with the Confederacy of Independent Systems during the Clone Wars. It was the site of the Third Battle of Mygeeto, and the Galactic Republic assaulted Mygeeto during the Outer Rim Sieges. During the Imperial Era against the Galactic Empire, Mygeeto was the site of a battle featuring the Alliance to Restore the Republic's 61st Mobile Infantry and Riot Squadron. During the Galactic Civil War, the planet's Imperial forces were attacked by the Plasma Devils.

title: Myomar
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': 'Myomar Academy'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Myomar was a planet located in the galaxy's Expansion Region. Myomar Academy, an Imperial Academy, was located on the planet.

title: Myrkr
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Inner Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-7'}}
paragraph: Myrkr was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Inner Rim.

title: Mytus
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'S-3'}}
paragraph: Mytus was an astronomical object in the Outer Rim Territories of the galaxy, positioned at the coordinates S-3 on the Standard Galactic Grid.

title: N'Zoth
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Core Worlds', 'Sector': 'Koornacht Cluster', 'Grid coordinates': 'K-10'}}
paragraph: N'Zoth was a planet located in the Koornacht Cluster in the galaxy's Core Worlds. On the periphery of the Deep Core, it was connected via hyperspace route to Jedha and Coruscant.

title: Naalol
side_bar: {'Physical information': {'Primary terrain': 'Mountainous', 'Fauna': 'Valdeer'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Human', 'Affiliation': ['Galactic Empire', 'New Republic']}}
paragraph: Naalol was a strategically insignificant mountainous planet. It had a series of mountainous towns with small crooked mountainous houses. The people who lived here were valdeer shepherds as well as artisans or miners.

title: Naboo
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Sector': 'Chommell sector', 'System': 'Naboo system', 'Suns': '1: Naboo', 'Orbital position': '3', 'Moons': ['3', "Ohma-D'un", 'Onoam', 'Veruna'], 'Grid coordinates': 'O-17', 'Trade routes': ['Enarc Run', 'Old Trade Federation Route'], 'Rotation period': '26 standard hours', 'Orbital period': '312 standard days'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Diameter': ['12', '120 kilometers'], 'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Climate': 'Temperate', 'Primary terrain': ['Swamps', 'Hills', 'Plains', 'Cities', 'Mountains'], 'Points of interest': ['Gallo Mountains', "Hiram Zataire's vineyard", 'Kwilaan Spaceport', 'Lake Country', 'Lake Paonga', 'Solleu River', 'Theed Royal Palace', 'Varykino'], 'Flora': ['Cambylictus tree', 'Locap', 'Millaflower', 'Naboo lettuce', 'Perlote tree'], 'Fauna': ['Bee', 'Blarth', 'Bogwing', 'Colo claw fish', 'Doo', 'Faa', 'Falumpaset', 'Fambaa', 'Golden pheasant', 'Gualama', 'Guarlara', 'Ikopi', 'Kaadu', 'Laa', 'Mee', 'Mott', 'Nuna', 'Odupiendo', 'Ollopom', 'Opee sea killer', 'Peko-peko', 'Pelikki', 'Pikobi', 'Ray', 'Sando aqua monster', 'See', 'Soo', 'Shaak', 'Slitherfish', 'Slug-beetle', 'Tee', 'Tusk-cat', 'Veermok', 'Yobshrimp']}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Gungans', 'Immigrated species': ['Elders', 'Humans', 'Naboo'], 'Primary language(s)': 'Galactic Basic', 'Government': 'Elective monarchy', 'Population': ['4.5 billion:', '72% Gungan', '27% Human', '1% Other'], 'Demonym': 'Nabooian', 'Major cities': ["Dee'ja Peak", 'Jan-gwa city', 'Keren', 'Moenia', 'Otoh Gunga', 'Otoh Langua', 'Theed'], 'Major imports': ['Grain', 'Ore', 'Processed foods', 'TechnologySilk'], 'Major exports': ['Gungan stew', 'Art', 'Cultural itemsGrain', 'Plasma', 'Wine'], 'Affiliation': ['Gungan High Council', 'Royal House of Naboo', 'Galactic Republic', 'Trade Federation', 'Galactic Empire', 'New Republic', 'First Order']}}
paragraph: Naboo was a bountiful planet in the Chommell sector of the Mid Rim, close to the border of the Outer Rim Territories. It was home to the Gungan species and to a population of humans known as the Naboo. Naboo was pushed to the forefront of galactic politics as the birthplace of the Dark Lord of the Sith Sheev Palpatine, who served as its representative in the Senate of the Galactic Republic.

title: Nam Chorios
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'R-6'}, 'Physical information': {'Climate': 'Cold', 'Points of interest': ['Nam Chorios Imperial mining colony', 'Nam Chorios Imperial prison facility']}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
