paragraph: Nkllon was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Expansion Region, positioned at the coordinates L-16 on the Standard Galactic Grid.

title: Noe'ha'on
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region', 'Grid coordinates': 'K-16', 'Trade routes': 'Great Gran Run'}, 'Physical information': {'Primary terrain': 'Jungle'}}
paragraph: Noe'ha'on was a jungle world located in the galaxy's Expansion Region, It was located on the Great Gran Run hyperspace route, connected to Takodana.

title: Noe'ha'on
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region', 'Grid coordinates': 'K-16', 'Trade routes': 'Great Gran Run'}, 'Physical information': {'Primary terrain': 'Jungle'}}
paragraph: Noe'ha'on was a jungle world located in the galaxy's Expansion Region, It was located on the Great Gran Run hyperspace route, connected to Takodana.

title: Nothoiin
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': ['Greater Javin', 'Anoat sector'], 'Moons': '1', 'Grid coordinates': 'K-18'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Primary terrain': ['Forests', 'Rocky']}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Nothoiin', 'Major exports': 'Ur-diamonds', 'Affiliation': ['Noble Court', 'Galactic Empire']}}
paragraph: Nothoiin was a planet in the Anoat sector. It had a moon on which ur-diamonds were mined. During the Iron Blockade, a makeshift medical center on Nothoiin had to resort to smugglers to acquire supplies from Gerrenthum. The planet's native sentients species, the gold-skinned Nothoiins, once ruled the entire Anoat sector.

title: Nouane
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Inner Rim', 'Sector': 'Nouane sector', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-8'}}
paragraph: Nouane was an astronomical object located in the Nouane sector of the galaxy's Inner Rim.

title: Nubia
side_bar: {'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Primary terrain': 'Urban', 'Points of interest': ['Circle Bay', 'Droid museum']}}
paragraph: Nubia was a world home to Industrial Automaton droid factories and Nubian Design Collective shipyards.

title: Obroa-skai
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Inner Rim', 'System': 'Obroa-skai system', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-8'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': ['Obroa-skai College', 'Obroa-skai emergency medevac center']}}
paragraph: Obroa-skai was a planet located in the Obroa-skai system of the galaxy's Inner Rim. It was known mostly for its libraries and medcenters. At the end of the Clone Wars, one of those medcenters bought a fleet of Sephi flyers from Thustra for use during emergency evacuations. Galen Walton Erso served as a teacher at a college on the planet.

title: Ogem
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': ['Mid Rim', 'Western Reaches'], 'Grid coordinates': 'L-17'}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Primary terrain': ['Caves', 'Forests'], 'Fauna': 'Snake'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Onodone'}}
paragraph: Ogem was a planet located in a remote section of the Western Reaches, near the desert planet Jakku. The junk dealer Unkar Plutt sometimes marketed his salvage to spacers from Ogem.

title: Ojom
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Deep Core', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-11'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Besalisk'}}
paragraph: Ojom was a world located in the galaxy's Deep Core that was the homeworld of the Besalisk species. The Chef Dexter Jettster, and Jedi Master Pong Krell were both Besalisks from Ojom.

title: Omwat
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-18'}}
paragraph: Omwat was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Ord Biniir
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'K-5'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': 'Ord Biniir orbital scrapyard'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Ord Biniir was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories, in grid square K-5 on the Standard Galactic Grid. Prior to the Galactic Civil War, the Alliance to Restore the Republic launched a successful assault on Imperial targets there. However the resulting victory did not show the full potency of the rebellion.

title: Ord Canfre
paragraph: Ord Canfre was a location in the galaxy. It was home to the Ord Canfre Institute for Ethics in Art Criticism, which Cepa Bonshu, creator of the anti-Imperial propaganda poster What Will You Do, taught at after retiring from a lengthy communication arts career.

title: Ord Cantrell
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'K-6'}}
paragraph: Ord Cantrell was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Ord Cestus
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'O-6'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': 'Ord Cestus medical station'}}
paragraph: Ord Cestus, also referred to as simply Cestus, was a planet in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. Located in the vicinity of the Perlemian Trade Route, it was situated a considerable distance away from common routes between Geonosis and Coruscant. During the Clone Wars, the Galactic Republic established a medical station near Ord Cestus.

title: Ord Mantell
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Sector': 'Bright Jewel sector', 'System': 'Bright Jewel system', 'Suns': 'Bright Jewel', 'Moons': ['At least 3', 'Quantxi'], 'Grid coordinates': 'L-7', 'Trade routes': "Burke's Trailing"}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Primary terrain': 'Mountain chains'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Mantellian Savrip', 'Immigrated species': ['Bith', 'Falleen', 'Human'], 'Demonym': 'Mantellian', 'Major cities': 'Ord Mantell City', 'Affiliation': ['Black Sun', 'Shadow Collective', 'Galactic Empire']}}
paragraph: Ord Mantell was a planet located in the Bright Jewel system of the galaxy's Mid Rim that was the homeworld of the Mantellian Savrip species. In the waning days of the Galactic Republic, Ord Mantell City housed a base of operations for the Black Sun crime syndicate. It later came under control of the Galactic Empire and became home to an Imperial deepdock.

title: Ord Pardron
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'R-15'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': ['Galactic Empire', 'Alliance to Restore the Republic']}}
paragraph: Ord Pardron was a planet located in the galaxy's Mid Rim that was a safe world for the Alliance to Restore the Republic. A map of the galaxy with a legend listing the various Alliance safe worlds, starfighter hubs at level five or higher, rebel operations sectors and regional headquarters, and shadow planets with deep space caches, included Ord Pardron.

title: Ord Radama
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Orbital position': 'Q-5'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Devlikk'}}
paragraph: Ord Radama was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories that was the homeworld of the Devlikk podracer Wan Sandage.

title: Ord Tiddell
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': ['Alliance to Restore the Republic', 'Mid Rim revolutionaries']}}
paragraph: Ord Tiddell was a planet in the Mid Rim. During the Galactic Civil War between the Galactic Empire and the Alliance to Restore the Republic, Alliance forces, including Lieutenant Caluan Ematt attacked Ord Tiddell as part of the Mid Rim Offensive, an operation by the Alliance and the Mid Rim revolutionaries to take control of the Mid Rim. The operation ended in failure and the Alliance was forced to retreat from Ord Tiddell and many other worlds, including Jeyell, Durkteel, Pothor, Charros IV, and Trasse. Several revolutionaries evacuated with Alliance forces, although many remained on their planets to harass the Empire, who was expected to take quick control over the former Alliance territories.

title: Ord Trasi
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-4'}}
paragraph: Ord Trasi was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Ordo
side_bar: {'Physical information': {'Points of interest': 'Archaic Arsenal of Ordo'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Mandalorians'}}
paragraph: Ordo was a Mandalorian world located within the galaxy. The planet was home to the Archaic Arsenal, which housed an ancient Mandalorian rally master lance.

title: Orelon
side_bar: {'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial'}}
paragraph: Orelon was a terrestrial astronomical object located in the galaxy that was the site of a weapons trade involving the Wookiee smuggler Chewbacca and Big Quince. During the weapons trade on Orelon, Big Quince's Wookiee bodyguard gave Chewbacca the pirate Maz Kanata's Smuggler's Guide. When Chewbacca's partner, Han Solo, learned where he had acquired the Smuggler's Guide months later, Solo recorded an account of the incident in the book.

title: Orinda
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'K-6'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': 'Orinda fuel depot'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Humans', 'Affiliation': 'New Republic'}}
paragraph: Orinda was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim. In the decades after the Galactic Civil War, Orinda was represented in the Galactic Senate by senator Fatil.

title: Orn Kios
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Anoat sector'}}
paragraph: Orn Kios was a planet in the Anoat sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Orondia
side_bar: {'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Points of interest': ['Bounty Emporium', "Koe's", 'Meteor Cafe', 'Orondia Tours', "The Pilot's Lounge"]}}
paragraph: Orondia was a desolate planet in the galaxy. During the Clone Wars, Obi-Wan Kenobi, disguised as Rako Hardeen, Cad Bane, and Moralo Eval were scammed into stopping there when a Bith gave him only enough fuel to reach Orondia, where his brother ran a fueling station.

title: Orvax
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'R-17'}}
paragraph: Orvax was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Oseon
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Centrality', 'Grid coordinates': 'T-8', 'Trade routes': 'Sanity Skip'}}
paragraph: Oseon was an astronomical object located in the Centrality, a sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. It was connected by the Sanity Skip hyperspace route to the planet Kessel and to Junkfort Station by another hyperspace route.

title: Ossus
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Auril sector', 'System': 'Adega system', 'Moons': "At least 1: Ossus's forest moon", 'Grid coordinates': 'R-6', 'Rotation period': '31 standard hours', 'Orbital period': '231 standard days'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': ['Eocho Mountains', 'Great Jedi Library', 'Imhar Canyon', 'Jedi Temple']}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Human', 'Primary language(s)': ['Galactic Basic', 'Ysannan'], 'Government': 'Ysanna tribal government', 'Population': ['3', '750', '000', '99% Ysanna', '1% other'], 'Major cities': 'Knossa', 'Major imports': 'Technology', 'Affiliation': 'Jedi Order'}}
paragraph: Ossus was a planet located in the Auril sector of the Outer Rim Territories that was affiliated with the Jedi Order. Certain scholars surmised it was the location of the first Jedi Temple ever built, although Ahch-To, Coruscant, Jedha, and Tython were also candidates. At the very least, Ossus housed the Great Jedi Library and a temple at some point, from which a mosaic floor was later salvaged and transported to the Order's newer headquarters on Coruscant.

title: Ovise
side_bar: {'General information': {'Location': ['Moddell sector', 'Outer Rim Territories']}}
paragraph: Ovise was a location in the galaxy's Moddell sector.

title: Pakuuni
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'T-6'}}
paragraph: Pakuuni was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Palanhi
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Colonies', 'Grid coordinates': 'K-9', 'Trade routes': 'Shwuy Exchange'}}
paragraph: Palanhi was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Colonies region, along the Shwuy Exchange hyperspace route.

title: Pammant
side_bar: {'Physical information': {'Points of interest': 'Pammant Docks'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Quarren', 'Major exports': 'Starships', 'Affiliation': 'Confederacy of Independent Systems'}}
paragraph: Pammant was home to Pammant Docks, the location where the Invisible Hand, a Providence-class Dreadnought that served as General Grievous' flagship during the Battle of Coruscant, was constructed by the Free Dac Volunteers Engineering Corps, a Quarren starship manufacturer that aligned itself with the Confederacy of Independent Systems during the Clone Wars.

title: Pantolomin
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Core Worlds', 'Grid coordinates': 'K-9'}}
paragraph: Pantolomin was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Core Worlds. It shared its name with the Pantolomin cruiser, a type of luxury cruiser used by Black Sun.

title: Pantora
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region(s)': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Sujimis sector', 'System': 'Pantora system', 'Planet': 'Orto Plutonia'}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Primary terrain': 'Marshes'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Pantoran', 'Government': ['Pantoran Assembly', 'Chairman'], 'Major cities': 'Capital city', 'Affiliation': 'Galactic Republic'}}
paragraph: Pantora was the primary moon in orbit around the planet Orto Plutonia, in the Pantora system, located in the Sujimis sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It was the homeworld of the Pantorans, who were led by the Pantoran Assembly and the Supreme Chairman of Pantora, a post held by Chi Cho, who was later replaced by Baron Notluwiski Papanoida. Pantora was a member of the Galactic Republic and therefore represented in the Galactic Senate. During the Clone Wars, Riyo Chuchi served as senator of Pantora.

title: Paqualis III
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Inner Rim', 'System': 'Paqualis system', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-8', 'Trade routes': 'Hydian Way'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Points of interest': 'Paqualis III outpost'}}
paragraph: Paqualis III, also known as Paqualis, was a terrestrial astronomical object in the Inner Rim, situated along the Hydian Way and positioned at the coordinates L-8 on the Standard Galactic Grid. Following a skirmish with the bounty hunters 4-LOM and Zuckuss, the smuggler Han Solo offered to pilot the pair to an outpost on Paqualis III, near the Bounty Hunters' Guild.

title: Parcelus Minor
paragraph: Parcelus Minor was a location in the galaxy where a retreat occurred during the Imperial Era. The mercenary Saponza claimed to have participated in the retreat.

title: Patitite Pattuna
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim'}, 'Physical information': {'Primary terrain': 'Swamps'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Patitite', 'Primary language(s)': 'Galactic Basic', 'Government': ['Dictatorship', 'Democracy']}}
paragraph: Patitite Pattuna was a planet in the galaxy's Mid Rim, not far from Balnab, that was the homeworld of the tiny Patitite species. R2-D2 and C-3PO crash-landed on the planet after a nearby battle during the Clone Wars. R2-D2 accidentally crushed the planet's despot Hay-Zu, to which there was much rejoicing, and C-3PO introduced the natives to democracy, which prompted a civil war.

title: Pax
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-16', 'Trade routes': 'Hydian Way'}}
paragraph: Pax was an astronomical object located in the Expansion Region, in the grid square N-16 of the Standard Galactic Grid. The hyperspace route known as the Hydian Way linked Pax to the Chardaan system and the location known as ZeHeth, while another route connected it to Kira and Vondarc.

title: Pengalan
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Inner Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'O-8'}}
paragraph: Pengalan was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Inner Rim.

title: Pesfavri
side_bar: {'General information': {'Location': 'Unknown Regions'}, 'Chronological and political information': {'Affiliation': 'Chiss Ascendancy'}}
paragraph: Pesfavri was a location in the Unknown Regions, within the borders of the Chiss Ascendancy. Pirates affiliated with the Lioaoin Regime attacked Chiss freighters shipping off Pesfavri and Schesa.

title: Phaeda
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-6'}}
paragraph: Phaeda was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Phateem
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Inner Rim', 'Sector': 'Nouane sector'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Primary terrain': ['Bamboo forests', 'Mountains'], 'Points of interest': 'Ashlendu Mountains'}}
paragraph: Phateem was an uninhabited planet located in the Nouane sector, near Telerath, covered in bamboo forests and mountains. The Ashlendu Mountains on Phateem contained the Halls of Knowledge, a former Jedi artifact cache. A tournament was held at the Halls of Knowledge, though it was a front for an operation led by Imperial Security Bureau Colonel Sadao Emtri to catch Force-sensitive individuals.

title: Phindar
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Mandalore sector', 'System': 'Phindar system', 'Grid coordinates': 'P-6'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Phindian', 'Affiliation': ['A criminal cartel', 'Galactic Empire']}}
paragraph: Phindar was a planet located in the Phindar system, part of the Mandalore sector in the Outer Rim Territories. The planet, which was home to the Phindian species, was attacked by the Confederacy of Independent Systems during the Clone Wars, and later became affiliated with the Galactic Empire. The planet was later host to a battle during the Galactic Civil War.

title: Pho Ph'eah
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'P-5', 'Trade routes': 'Hydian Way'}}
paragraph: Pho Ph'eah was an astronomical object located within the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories, in the grid square P-5 of the Standard Galactic Grid. It was connected to the planets of Telos and Toprawa by the Hydian Way hyperspace route.

title: Phu
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Colonies', 'Grid coordinates': 'J-13'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Bardottans'}}
paragraph: Phu was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Colonies region of the galaxy that was colonized by the Bardottan species of Bardotta. It was the homeworld of the Bardottan podracer Mars Guo.

title: Pii
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'System': 'Pii system'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': 'Imperial marshaling station Pii'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Pii was a planet in the Pii system, located near the Gulf of Tatooine. It was the location of the Galactic Empire's Imperial marshaling station Pii. Fourteen years before the Battle of Yavin, an Imperial convoy planned to travel there from Desolation Station, via a moon coreward of the Gulf of Tatooine, and then jump to Sentinel Base and Geonosis. These plans were interrupted, however, when the convoy was attacked by a rebel cell run by former Republic Intelligence Captain Berch Teller.

title: Plexis
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Core Worlds'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Zenowai Crime Society'}}
paragraph: Plexis was a relatively small planet located in the Core Worlds region of the galaxy. During the Age of the Empire, it housed a number of spice gangs, all of which were under the authority of the Zenowai Crime Society via an overseer named Shoja Ko.

title: Ploo
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-7'}}
paragraph: Ploo was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Expansion Region.

title: Plooma
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-3'}}
paragraph: Plooma was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories, in the grid square L-3 of the Standard Galactic Grid.

title: Polis Massa
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Subterrel sector', 'System': 'Polis Massa system', 'Grid coordinates': 'K-20'}, 'Physical information': {'Climate': ['Formerly arid', 'now none'], 'Primary terrain': 'Asteroids'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Eellayin', 'Immigrated species': 'Kallidahin', 'Major cities': 'Polis Massa Base', 'Affiliation': ['Archaeological Research Council', 'Alliance to Restore the Republic']}}
paragraph: Polis Massa was an asteroid field located in the Subterrel sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories, far from any major hyperspace lanes. At some point, Polis Massa was a planet located within the system of the same name. The planet was home to a subterranean people called the Eellayin until it was destroyed by a mysterious cataclysm.

title: Pollillus
side_bar: {'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Troig'}}
paragraph: Pollillus was a planet in the galaxy that was the homeworld of the Troig species. The Troig podrace announcer Fodesinbeed Annodue hailed from Pollillus.

title: Polmanar
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Anoat sector'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Trade Spine League'}}
paragraph: Polmanar was a planet located in the Anoat sector of the galaxy. At the time of the Galactic Empire's Iron Blockade of the sector, Polmanar was a base of the Trade Spine League.

title: Prakith
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Deep Core', 'Orbital position': 'K-10'}}
paragraph: Prakith was an astronomical object located within the galaxy's Deep Core. It was connected via hyperspace routes to the worlds Byss and Empress Teta.

title: Pzob
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'T-15'}}
paragraph: Pzob was an astronomical object in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Qat Chrystac
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-16'}}
paragraph: Qat Chrystac was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Expansion Region.

title: Qina
side_bar: {'General information': {'Location': ['Moddell sector', 'Outer Rim Territories']}}
paragraph: Qina was a location in the Moddell sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Before the Battle of Endor in 4 ABY, Qina was part of a map by Corporal Ractivelle of the Stardust unit as part of the Rebel Alliance's preparation for their assault on the second Death Star.

title: Quarzite
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Inner Rim'}, 'Physical information': {'Primary terrain': ['Highly pressurized surface', 'Crystalline caverns'], 'Points of interest': ["Otua Blank's stronghold", 'Quarzite space station', 'Turbolift transport area'], 'Fauna': 'Milodon'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': ['Belugan', 'Kage'], 'Primary language(s)': 'Galactic Basic', 'Government': 'Dictatorship', 'Affiliation': 'Neutral'}}
paragraph: Quarzite was a small planet located in the Inner Rim whose high atmospheric pressure rendered its surface uninhabitable. However, the planet's crystalline caverns were capable of supporting life, and were home to the warring Belugans and Kage. During the Clone Wars, it was ruled by the Belugan dictator Lord Otua Blank. When the Belugans kidnapped the Kage girl Pluma Sodi so that Blank could marry her, Major Rigosso hired a group of bounty hunters to defend a subtram, the primary method of travel on the planet, that would deliver the girl to Lord Blank. The hunters traveled to Quarzite in the Hound's Tooth and took a massive turbolift, which, due to the overwhelming atmospheric pressure, was the only way to reach Quarzite's suface.

title: Quellor
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Colonies', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-12'}}
paragraph: Quellor was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Colonies region.

title: Quermia
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'S-5', 'Trade routes': 'Perlemian Trade Route'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Primary terrain': 'Gardens', 'Surface water': 'Oceans'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Quermian', 'Primary language(s)': 'Quermian', 'Affiliation': ['Galactic Republic', 'Confederacy of Independent Systems', 'Galactic Empire']}}
paragraph: Quermia was a garden planet located in the Outer Rim Territories. It was the namesake of the Quermian species, whose ancestors were settled on Quermia by Arkanian scientists. During the Clone Wars, Quermia was located in Separatist space, isolating it from the Galactic Republic. Although the extensive blockade of Quermia was lifted after the collapse of the Confederacy of Independent Systems, the planet fell under Imperial rule shortly thereafter.

title: Ques
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Hutt Space'}, 'Physical information': {'Climate': 'Humid', 'Primary terrain': ['Forests', 'Glades', 'Swamps'], 'Points of interest': "Teacher's cabin", 'Fauna': ['Axton-tarsier', 'Ferin', 'Slime crab', 'Snarlap']}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Human'}}
paragraph: Ques was a swampy planet in Hutt Space, and its population primarily consisted of scavengers, such as Dec Hansen. The axton-tarsier, the ferin, the slime crab, and the Snarlap were creatures native to Ques. A school named teacher's cabin was located on Ques.

title: Questal
paragraph: Questal was a location that the Imperial Lambda-class shuttle CS-831 was supposed to travel to. Instead, Adea Rite, the aide of Grand Admiral Rae Sloane, rerouted the shuttle to transport naamite batteries to Coruscant.

title: Queyta
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-19'}}
paragraph: Queyta was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Radnor
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'Q-16', 'Trade routes': 'Corellian Run'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Radnor was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim on the Corellian Run.

title: Rago
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'I-7'}}
paragraph: Rago was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim, connected by hyperspace route to Ansion and the Utegetu Nebula.

title: Raithal
side_bar: {'Physical information': {'Points of interest': 'Raithal Academy'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Raithal was an planet that hosted an Imperial Academy several years before the Battle of Yavin.

title: Rakata Prime
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Unknown Regions', 'Grid coordinates': 'G-11'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial'}}
paragraph: Rakata Prime, also known as Lehon, was one of the few navigable worlds located in the Unknown Regions. At some point, the Resistance pilot Venisa Doza visited the planet along with her astromech droid, Torch. The Zabrak pirate Tryki was also once arrested for attempting to board a First Order cruiser near Rakata Prime.

title: Ralltiir
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Core Worlds'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Human', 'Affiliation': 'Alliance to Restore the Republic'}}
paragraph: Ralltiir was a terrestrial planet located in the Core Worlds region. During the Clone Wars, Lieutenant Commander Orson Krennic of the Galactic Republic financed a few weeks of vacation on the planet for the smuggler Has Obitt's former crew, as compensation for replacing them. Ralltiir later served as a Rebel Alliance safe world during the Galactic Civil War. The planet was also the homeworld of the human Imperial-turned-rebel pilot Derek Klivian.

title: Rampa
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Corporate Sector', 'Trade routes': 'Bubble Wink'}}
paragraph: Rampa was a world in the Corporate Sector of the Outer Rim Territories, connected to Panna in the Cronese Mandate by the smugglers' hyperlane Bubble Wink.

title: Randon
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'Q-10', 'Trade routes': ['Pabol Sleheyron', 'Randon Run']}}
paragraph: Randon was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim.

title: Rattatak
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': ['Outer Rim Territories', 'Western Reaches'], 'Moons': 'At least 1', 'Grid coordinates': 'H-16'}, 'Physical information': {'Primary terrain': 'Mountains', 'Points of interest': 'Barterus', 'Fauna': ['Rattataki Trogodile', 'Rattatakian redjacket']}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': ['Dathomirian', 'Human', "Kerch Kushi's species", 'Siniteen', "Voe Atell's species", 'Weequays'], 'Government': 'Warlords', 'Demonym': ['Rattataki', 'Rattatakian'], 'Major cities': 'Rattataki Village', 'Affiliation': 'New Republic'}}
paragraph: Rattatak was a mountainous planet located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. After killing the warlords responsible for the death of Jedi Knight Ky Narec, former Jedi Padawan Asajj Ventress ruled Rattatak until she was found and recruited by former Jedi Master Count Dooku, a Sith Lord.

title: Raydonia
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Moons': '2'}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Climate': 'Temperate', 'Primary terrain': 'Forests'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Human', 'Demonym': 'Raydonian', 'Major cities': 'Raydonian settlement', 'Major imports': 'Supplies', 'Affiliation': 'Unallied'}}
paragraph: Raydonia was a temperate, forested planet located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Red Nebula
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region(s)': 'Wild Space', 'Grid coordinates': 'G-21'}}
paragraph: The Red Nebula was a nebula located in Wild Space, positioned at the coordinates G-21 on the Standard Galactic Grid.

title: Reecee
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Inner Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'J-8'}}
paragraph: Reecee was an astronomical object in the galaxy's Inner Rim.

title: Renatasia
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Centrality', 'Grid coordinates': 'U-8'}}
paragraph: Renatasia was an astronomical object located in the Centrality, a sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Rendili
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Core Worlds', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-11'}}
paragraph: Rendili was a planet located in the galaxy's Core Worlds. It shared its name with the shipbuilding corporation Rendili StarDrive, as well as the company's predecessor, Rendili Hyperworks.

title: Rentor
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Unknown Regions'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Chiss Ascendancy'}}
paragraph: Rentor was a planet of the Chiss Ascendancy, situated near the capital of Csilla. It was the homeworld of at least one branch of the Kivu family, including Kivu'raw'nuru, later known as Mitth'raw'nuruodo.  There was also an academy on the planet which Vurawn attended.

title: Reuss
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'P-18'}}
paragraph: Reuss was an astronomical object in the Outer Rim Territories of the galaxy, linked to Socorro and Spice Terminus by hyperspace routes. It was positioned at the coordinates P-18 on the Standard Galactic Grid.

title: Rhelg
side_bar: {'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Sith'}}
paragraph: Rhelg was a world affiliated with the Sith. In the time of the Galactic Republic, Rhelg was quarantined, along with many other Sith worlds, and its history and Sith affiliation was hidden.

title: Rhen Var
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'R-6'}, 'Physical information': {'Climate': 'Frigid', 'Points of interest': 'Rhen Var Imperial outpost'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Rhen Var was a planet with frigid environments located near the Galidraan system in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. During the galaxy-spanning conflict known as the Clone Wars, the Galactic Republic deployed clone cold assault troopers on the world; troops specifically equipped to deal with cold environments. During the reign of the Galactic Empire, an Imperial outpost was located on Rhen Var. After the stolen Imperial corvette Carrion Spike attacked Imperial facilities in the Galidraan star system, the planet's outpost was considered as one of the potential targets for the corvette by Moff Wilhuff Tarkin. Due to the relative unimportance of the outpost on Rhen Var, Tarkin decided that the Imperial assets on the planet Nam Chorios were a more likely choice for the rebel cell piloting the stolen starship.

title: Rhommamool
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-13', 'Trade routes': 'Corellian Run'}}
paragraph: Rhommamool was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Expansion Region.

title: Riflor
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'J-16'}, 'Physical information': {'Primary terrain': 'Volcanos'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Advozse'}}
paragraph: Riflor was a volcanic planet located in the galaxy's Mid Rim, connected by hyperspace route to Cerea and Lorta. It was home to the Advozse species. On Riflor, volcanic eruptions frequently destroyed Advozsec settlements, so the Advozsec tended to care very little about material goods.

title: Riileb
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Hutt Space', 'Grid coordinates': 'T-12'}}
paragraph: Riileb was an astronomical object located in the Hutt Space sector of the Outer Rim Territories, positioned at the coordinates T-12 on the Standard Galactic Grid.

title: Ring of Kafrene
side_bar: {'General information': {'Location': ['Kafrene asteroid belt', 'Kafrene system', 'Thand sector'], 'Points of interest': 'Section nine'}, 'Chronological and political information': {'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: The Ring of Kafrene, also referred to simply as Kafrene, was a mining colony and deep-space trading post in the Kafrene asteroid belt of the Thand sector. The Alliance to Restore the Republic sent intelligence agent Cassian Andor here prior to the outbreak of the Galactic Civil War. There, Andor learned of the existence of the Death Star.

title: Ringo Vinda
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': 'Ringo Vinda space station'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Humans', 'Demonym': 'Ringo Vindan', 'Affiliation': ['Galactic Republic', 'Confederacy of Independent Systems', 'Galactic Empire']}}
paragraph: Ringo Vinda was a planet located in the galaxy's Mid Rim encircled by a massive civilian graving dock and controlled by the Galactic Republic. It was inhabited by a human cultural group, the Ringo Vindans, who spoke Galactic Basic in a distinctive accent. During the waning decades of the Republic, Jedi Knight Rael Averross hailed from Ringo Vinda.

title: Rinn
side_bar: {'Physical information': {'Climate': 'Frozen', 'Primary terrain': 'Ice'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Human'}}
paragraph: Rinn was an ice planet located in the galaxy. Around 4 BBY, the people of Rinn faced an energy crisis: once their dwindling supply of fuel cells had run out, they would be unable to power the heaters necessary for their survival. This predicament prompted rebel commander Jun Sato to task the Spectres with acquiring more generators.

title: Rintonne
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Sector': 'Lambda sector', 'Grid coordinates': 'P-16'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Galactic Republic'}}
paragraph: Rintonne was a planet located in the Lambda sector of the galaxy's Mid Rim. Rintonne, as well as most of the Andoan Free Colonies, remained loyal to the Galactic Republic during the Clone Wars, despite much of the Lambda sector seceding to the Confederacy of Independent Systems, led by Senator Po Nudo.

title: Rishi
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Abrion sector', 'System': 'Rishi system', 'Moons': '1: Rishi moon', 'Grid coordinates': 'S-15'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Galactic Republic'}}
paragraph: Rishi was a planet in the Rishi system. It had one barren moon. During the Republic Era, Jedi Master Lene Kostana and Padawan Sifo-Dyas discovered the Hand of Skrye on Rishi, and the Master proceeded to teach Dyas a cleansing ritual. During the Clone Wars, the Rishi moon housed the Galactic Republic's Rishi Station.

title: Roche
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'Q-8', 'Trade routes': 'Perlemian Trade Route'}}
paragraph: Roche was a planet located in the galaxy's Mid Rim, in grid square Q-8 on the Standard Galactic Grid, situated between Lantillies and Abhean on the Perlemian Trade Route. It shared its name with the Verpine Roche Hive, a droid manufacturer. During the Clone Wars, a sneak attack on Roche occurred, a battle which the Dressellian smuggler Has Obitt was caught in the middle of.

title: Rodia
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Savareen sector', 'System': 'Tyrius system', 'Grid coordinates': 'R-16'}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Climate': ['Hot', 'Humid'], 'Primary terrain': ['Jungles', 'Swamps', 'Oceans'], 'Points of interest': ['Betu', 'Kay-Tap square', 'Senatorial Palace', 'Toopil'], 'Flora': ['Thinekk tree', 'Kwazel candy', 'Poola blossom'], 'Fauna': ['Birds', 'Frogs', 'Ghest', 'Khardax', 'Kwazel Maw', 'Snakes']}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Rodians', 'Primary language(s)': 'Rodian', 'Government': 'Grand Protector', 'Demonym': 'Rodian', 'Affiliation': ['Galactic Republic', 'Confederacy of Independent Systems', 'Galactic Empire', 'New Republic']}}
paragraph: Rodia was a remote and swampy jungle planet. It was the homeworld of the Rodian species. Cities on Rodia were encased with domed environmental shields that allowed entry and exit for vehicles and vessels.

title: Roon
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': ['Outer Rim Territories', 'Cloak of the Sith'], 'Grid coordinates': 'S-15', 'Trade routes': ["Mumble's Turnaround", 'Triellus Trade Route']}}
paragraph: Roon was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories, in a region called the Cloak of the Sith. It was located on the Triellus Trade Route hyperspace route and the smugglers' route Mumble's Turnaround. The Roon Tours travel agency shared its name with the world.

title: Roona
side_bar: {'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Roonan'}}
paragraph: Roona was the homeworld of the Roonan species.

title: Rorak
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Hutt Space', 'Grid coordinates': 'S-12'}}
paragraph: Rorak was an astronomical object located in the Hutt Space region of the galaxy. It was connected to Ylesia, Nal Hutta and Circumtore, also of Hutt Space, by hyperspace routes. Rorak was located at galactic coordinates S-12.

title: Rothana
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'T-15'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': 'Rothana Imperial Shipyards', 'Fauna': 'Arctic horny whelmer'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Rothana was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. It was home to shipyards controlled by the Galactic Empire. In 14 BBY, ships stationed at Rothana were deployed by the Imperial Navy to other locations that were considered to be potential targets of Berch Teller and his rebel group. The Empire largely abandoned their shipyards in preparation for the Battle of Jakku near the end of the Galactic Civil War, allowing a group of pro-Imperial sympathizers to attempt to steal the craft a year later.

title: Roxuli
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region', 'Grid coordinates': 'I-8'}}
paragraph: Roxuli was an astronomical object in the galaxy's Expansion Region.

title: Rudrig
side_bar: {'General information': {'Points of interest': 'University of Rudrig'}}
paragraph: Rudrig was the location of a university that Lyra Erso studied at in 29 BBY.

title: Rugosa
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region(s)': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'System': 'Rugosa system', 'Grid coordinates': 'O-17'}, 'Physical information': {'Climate': 'Temperate', 'Primary terrain': ['Caverns', 'Coral forests'], 'Fauna': ['Neebray', 'Trident cluster coral', 'Rugosan King coral']}}
paragraph: Rugosa was a temperate moon located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories close to the planet Toydaria. Rugosa's terrain was  once that of vast oceans until they dried up, leaving the moon's surface covered in large forests of coral and rocky cavernous areas. During the Clone Wars, the moon was considered neutral territory, and was chosen as the secret rendezvous point for Jedi Grand Master Yoda to meet with King Katuunko of the Toydarian people to discuss a Toydarian alliance with the Galactic Republic. The meeting was disrupted by the Confederacy of Independent Systems, who hoped to gain the allegiance of the Toydarians themselves, but Katuunko chose to side with the Republic after Yoda defeated a small Separatist force on the moon.

title: Rutan
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-20', 'Trade routes': 'Hydian Way'}}
paragraph: Rutan was an astronomical object in the Outer Rim Territories of the galaxy, situated on the Hydian Way.

title: Ruuria
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'Q-3', 'Trade routes': 'Hydian Way'}, 'Physical information': {'Primary terrain': 'Pink rivers'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Ruurian'}}
paragraph: Ruuria was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories along the Hydian Way that was the homeworld of the Ruurian species. It was noted for having pink rivers, along the banks of which chroma-wings would eat, fly, and mate.

title: Ruusan
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Sector': 'Teraab sector', 'System': 'Ruusan system', 'Moons': ['3', 'including the Ruusan moon'], 'Grid coordinates': 'P-11'}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Points of interest': 'A village'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Human', 'Affiliation': 'Confederacy of Independent Systems'}}
paragraph: Ruusan was a planet located in the Ruusan system within the Teraab sector of the galaxy's Mid Rim that was orbited by three moons. It was positioned at the coordinates P-11 of the Standard Galactic Grid. During the Separatist Crisis, it was aligned with the Confederacy of Independent Systems, and, during the Clone Wars, one of its moons was the location of Skytop Station, a secret Separatist listening post. Ruusan was host to a number of ancient relics, strewn across its many historical battlefields.

title: Ryloth
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': ['Outer Rim Territories', 'Cloak of the Sith'], 'Sector': 'Gaulus sector', 'System': 'Ryloth system', 'Moons': ['At least 3', "Ryloth's largest moon", "Ryloth's outermost moon", "Ryloth's third moon"], 'Grid coordinates': 'R-17', 'Trade routes': ['Corellian Run', "Mumble's Turnaround"]}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Climate': ['Hot', 'humid'], 'Primary terrain': ['Dense jungles', 'Mesas', 'Valleys', 'Volcanoes'], 'Points of interest': ['Bypass Notch', 'Jixuan desert', "Ryloth's northern continent", 'Tann Province', 'Tulara Ravine'], 'Flora': ['Conifer', 'Whiptree'], 'Fauna': ['Blurrg', 'Can-cell', 'Gutkurr', 'Lylek', 'Primates']}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': "Twi'lek", 'Immigrated species': 'Human', 'Primary language(s)': "Twi'leki", 'Government': 'Ryloth government', 'Demonym': 'Rylothian', 'Major cities': ["Kala'uun", 'Lessu', 'Nabat', 'Rhovari'], 'Major exports': ['Ryll', 'Slaves', 'Spice'], 'Affiliation': ['Galactic Republic', 'Confederacy of Independent Systems', 'Techno Union', "Twi'lek Resistance", 'Galactic Empire', 'Free Ryloth Movement']}}
paragraph: Ryloth was a planet in the Ryloth system of the Outer Rim Territories, and the homeworld of the Twi'lek species. Its terrain varied, filled with jungles, mesas, valleys, and volcanoes, and had an atmosphere breathable for Twi'leks and humans alike. A forest covered its equator, filled with dangerous predators. Given the varied and dangerous terrain, Twi'leks lived in caves underground where it was safer.

title: Ryndellia
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'System': 'Ryndellia system'}}
paragraph: Ryndellia was located in the Ryndellia system of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. During the Clone Wars, the Subjugator-class heavy cruiser Malevolence destroyed a convoy of Republic medical frigates near Ryndellia.

title: Ryoone
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'I-17'}}
paragraph: Ryoone was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Saijo
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'K-20'}}
paragraph: Saijo was an astronomical object located in the Outer Rim Territories of the galaxy, positioned at the coordinates K-20 on the Standard Galactic Grid.

title: Saki
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Hutt Space', 'Grid coordinates': 'S-11'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Sakiyan', 'Affiliation': 'Hutt Cartel'}}
paragraph: Saki was a planet located in the Hutt Space region of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories that was conquered by the Hutt Cartel, which was controlled by the Hutts from the neighboring world of Nal Hutta, who turned the native Sakiyans into slaves or vassals.

title: Saleucami
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Suolriep sector', 'System': 'Saleucami system', 'Moons': ['3:', 'Cather', 'Jos', 'Victori'], 'Grid coordinates': 'S-8'}, 'Physical information': {'Climate': ['Arid', 'Temperate'], 'Primary terrain': ['Deserts', 'Swamps'], 'Points of interest': "Cut Lawquane's farmstead", 'Flora': ['Greater cake tree', 'Towering Bith'], 'Fauna': ['Eopie', 'Firefly', 'Nuna', 'Reek', 'Saleucami bat', 'Saleucami buzzard', 'Starklebird']}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': ['Human', "Twi'lek"], 'Affiliation': ['Galactic Republic', 'Commerce Guild', 'Confederacy of Independent Systems', 'Galactic Empire']}}
paragraph: Saleucami was a planet located in the Saleucami system, within the Suolriep sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. Its name meant "oasis". During the Clone Wars, its inhabitants wished to stay out of the conflict, though war would eventually reach the backwater planet. Although Republic forces were able to drive the Separatists from Saleucami, it became the site of an invasion and one of the final battles of the war. Jedi Master Stass Allie was killed on her BARC speeder bike by Commander Neyo at the start of the Great Jedi Purge. It was the homeworld of Sergeant Warda Gojun of the Galactic Empire's 71st GAV Battalion.

title: Salliche
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Core Worlds'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Sallichen', 'Major exports': 'Foodstuff', 'Affiliation': 'Galactic Republic'}}
paragraph: Salliche was an agriworld located in the Core Worlds of the galaxy. It was represented in the Galactic Senate by Senator Bulgeski. It was also once ravaged by Norkronian raiders not long before 42 BBY. Senator Bulgeski asked the Jedi Order to intervene.

title: Sanctuary
side_bar: {'General information': {'Location': 'Outer Rim Territories'}, 'Chronological and political information': {'Affiliation': 'Alliance to Restore the Republic'}}
paragraph: Sanctuary was a location in the Outer Rim Territories that was a safe world of the nascent Alliance to Restore the Republic. A map of the galaxy with a legend listing the various Alliance safe worlds, starfighter hubs at level five or higher, rebel operations sectors and regional headquarters, and shadow planets with deep space caches, included Sanctuary.

title: Sanjin
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Moons': 'Several'}}
paragraph: Sanjin was a planet that hosted several moons. Some time prior to the mission to Vassek's third moon, Jedi Master Neebo traveled to one of these moons to aid refugees.

title: Sanrafsix
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-17'}}
paragraph: Sanrafsix was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Sanyassa
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Moddell sector'}}
paragraph: Sanyassa was a location in the Moddell sector, situated within the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. Due to hyperspace anomalies within the sector, starships were often dumped into the Endor system from Sanyassa.

title: Sarapin
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Core Worlds', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-10'}}
paragraph: Sarapin was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Core Worlds. At some point prior to the attack on the EF76 Nebulon-B escort frigate Hellion's Dare over Jiruus, a fleet battle occurred at Sarapin during which Riot Squadron members Wyl Lark and Sonogari were present, but grounded.

title: Sarka
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'Q-8'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Primary terrain': ['Caves', 'Jungles', 'Mountains', 'Rivers', 'Waterfalls'], 'Points of interest': ['Sarkan gem mine', 'Palace of the Queen of the Sarkans']}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Sarkan', 'Major exports': ['Aqua jewel', 'Corusca gem']}}
paragraph: Sarka was a planet located in the galaxy's Mid Rim, in grid square Q-8 on the Standard Galactic Grid. It was the homeworld of the reptilian Sarkan species. By the time of the Galactic Civil War, Sarka was ruled by Queen Zil.

title: Sarrish
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories'}}
paragraph: Sarrish was a planet where the Battle of Sarrish took place during the Clone Wars. The Galactic Republic lost the battle, and it was considered a devastating loss.

title: Sarvchi
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Unknown Regions'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Chiss', 'Affiliation': 'Chiss Ascendancy'}}
paragraph: Sarvchi was a planet within the territory of the Chiss Ascendancy. A number of Chiss migrated to Sarvchi after the climate of the species' homeworld, Csilla, grew less habitable.

title: Scarif
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': ['Abrion sector', 'Imperial Navy Exclusion Zone'], 'System': 'Scarif system', 'Suns': '1', 'Moons': '0', 'Grid coordinates': 'S-15', 'Trade routes': 'Manda Merchant Run'}, 'Physical information': {'Diameter': ['9', '112 km'], 'Climate': ['Temperate', 'Tropical'], 'Primary terrain': ['Oceans', 'Rocky archipelagos', 'Sandy beaches', 'Verdant jungles', 'Volcanic island chains'], 'Points of interest': ['Aurek-14', 'Death trooper training camp', 'Imperial security complex', 'Scarif orbital shipyard', 'Mines and refineries'], 'Flora': 'Areca nut palm tree', 'Fauna': ['Blixus', '1', '500 known fish species', 'Many colorful birds', 'reptiles', 'and insects']}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Humans', 'Population': ['475', '000'], 'Major exports': ['Starships', 'Supplies for the Death Star'], 'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Scarif was a remote, tropical planet in the Abrion sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Although a small and idyllic world, Scarif played an important part in the Galactic Empire's military-industrial complex, becoming a center for top-secret research beyond inspection distance of the prying eyes of the Imperial Senate. Among the projects stored here was the Death Star battle station, a construction so important the entire planet was covered by a planetary deflector shield that could only be entered via a Shield Gate.

title: Schesa
side_bar: {'General information': {'Location': 'Unknown Regions'}, 'Chronological and political information': {'Affiliation': 'Chiss Ascendancy'}}
paragraph: Schesa was a location in the Unknown Regions, situated near the edge of the Chiss Ascendancy. Pirates connected to the Lioaoin Regime attacked shipping off of Schesa and Pesfavri.

title: Scipio
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Albarrio sector', 'System': 'Albarrio system'}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Climate': 'Frigid', 'Primary terrain': ['Hills', 'Mountains'], 'Points of interest': 'Main Vault fortress'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': ['Human', 'Muun'], 'Affiliation': ['InterGalactic Banking Clan', 'Traxus Division', 'Galactic Republic', 'Confederacy of Independent Systems']}}
paragraph: Scipio was an ice-covered planet located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. It was positioned in the Albarrio system, and was an important world for the InterGalactic Banking Clan.

title: Sedratis
paragraph: Sedratis was a planet located within the galaxy. Sometime during the Clone Wars, a conflict broke out between the Galactic Republic and the Confederacy of Independent Systems on the planet.

title: Sembla
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Mahrusha sector', 'Moons': '4', 'Grid coordinates': 'S-5', 'Trade routes': 'None'}, 'Physical information': {'Primary terrain': ['Shallow seas', 'Volcanic islands'], 'Points of interest': 'Sembla Imperial research base'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Vurk', 'Primary language(s)': 'Semblan', 'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Sembla, formerly known as Utavurk, was a planet located in Mahrusha sector within the Outer Rim Territories. It was the homeworld of the Vurk, including Jedi Master Coleman Trebor. Sembla had four moons, which kept it tidally and tectonically active, and its terrain was made up of shallow seas and volcanic islands. The planet was located far from any major trade routes and as such, was rarely traveled to. However, the Galactic Empire established a research base on the world and also pressed native Vurk as cheap labor in strip-mining operations.

title: Senex
side_bar: {'General information': {'Location': ['Mid Rim', 'Senex-Juvex', 'Senex sector']}, 'Chronological and political information': {'Affiliation': 'Galactic Republic'}}
paragraph: Senex was a location in the galaxy's Mid Rim that was represented by Senator Terr Taneel in the Galactic Senate of the Galactic Republic during the end of the Clone Wars. Taneel was part of the Delegation of 2,000, a group of politicians who sought to counter Supreme Chancellor Palpatine's growing power.

title: Serenno
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'System': 'Serenno system', 'Moons': ['2', 'Mantero'], 'Grid coordinates': 'P-5'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Primary terrain': ['Forests', 'Mountains', 'Plains'], 'Points of interest': ['Castle Serenno', 'Saffia', 'Serenno Spaceport'], 'Fauna': ['Spine-wolf', "Tirra'Taka"]}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Human', 'Primary language(s)': 'Galactic Basic', 'Demonym': 'Serennian', 'Major cities': 'Carannia ', 'Affiliation': ['Sith Empire', 'House Serenno', 'Galactic Republic', 'Sith', 'Confederacy of Independent Systems']}}
paragraph: Serenno was a planet located in the Outer Rim Territories covered in lush forests, mountains and plains. Serenno was named after House Serenno which was the family who ruled it. During the Clone Wars, it was aligned with the Confederacy of Independent Systems, the leader of which was the Serenno-born Count Dooku.

title: Sernpidal
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-3'}}
paragraph: Sernpidal was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Sevarcos
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-19'}, 'Physical information': {'Primary terrain': 'Canyons'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Sevarcos was a planet in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories that was the site of a battle in the months after the Battle of Endor. During the battle, the New Republic successfully liberated at least one spice mine that had been operating on slave labor under the control of the Empire. The area of the spice mine was dry, dusty, and surrounded by canyons, and at least one of the slavemasters was Zygerrian.

title: Sharlissia
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-18'}}
paragraph: Sharlissia was an astronomical object located in the Outer Rim Territories, in the grid square N-18 of the Standard Galactic Grid. A hyperspace routes linked Sharlissia to the celestial body Kabal.

title: Shaum Hii
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-5'}}
paragraph: Shaum Hii was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Shili
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region', 'System': 'Shili system', 'Suns': "Shili's sun", 'Grid coordinates': 'L-8'}, 'Physical information': {'Primary terrain': 'Colorful grasslands'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Togruta'}}
paragraph: Shili was a planet located in the Shili system within the Expansion Region, that was the homeworld of the sentient Togruta species. Because Shili had colorful grasslands, the natives displayed distinctive skin patterns for camouflaging. Jedi Master Shaak Ti and former Padawan Ahsoka Tano of the Jedi Order were Togruta who hailed from this world.

title: Shimia
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'R-17'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Pacithhip'}}
paragraph: Shimia was an astronomical object in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. It was the homeworld of the Pacithhip female Bok Askol.

title: Shola
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'U-14'}}
paragraph: Shola was an astronomical object in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories, positioned at the coordinates U-14 on the Standard Galactic Grid.

title: Shumavar
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-19', 'Trade routes': 'Hydian Way'}}
paragraph: Shumavar was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories, situated along the Hydian Way.

title: Simoom
side_bar: {'Production information': {'Manufacturer': 'Kuat Drive Yards', 'Model': 'Maelstrom-class battle cruiser', 'Class': 'Battle cruiser'}, 'Usage': {'Affiliation': ['Galactic Republic', 'Galactic Empire', 'Alliance to Restore the Republic'], 'Navy': ['Galactic Republic Navy', 'Imperial Navy', 'Alliance Navy']}}
paragraph: The Simoom was a Maelstrom-class battle cruiser that, along with the rest of its class, was in service to the Republic Navy during the Clone Wars between the Galactic Republic and the Confederacy of Independent Systems. After the Republic transitioned into the Galactic Empire, the remaining Maelstrom-class battle cruisers complemented the Imperial Navy until they were either broken up, used as test beds, or mothballed. The Simoom was one of the starships to be mothballed, but was later under the control of the Rebel Alliance, who deployed it as part of the Alliance Navy during the Galactic Civil War against the Empire.

title: Sirpar
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Suns': "1: Sirpar's sun"}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Climate': 'Hot', 'Gravity': 'Heavy', 'Primary terrain': 'Hilly'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Human', 'Affiliation': ['Galactic Empire', 'Arkanis Academy']}}
paragraph: Sirpar was a planet found within the Galactic Empire. It was known for its extremely high gravity compared to that of other human-inhabited planets in the Empire, as well as a dazzlingly intense sun that was so bright that non-natives needed to wear polarized goggles in order to be able to bear it. Generations of humans living on Sirpar had become adapted to the planet, broad in size and possessed of thick layers of muscle. Many of these had become instructors to Imperial cadets. The planet was used as a training forge for cadets of the Arkanis Academy. During the three-day tour, the cadets were granted provisional ranks as they participated in live exercises commanding stormtroopers that had been rotated off active duty.

title: Siskeen
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'R-17'}}
paragraph: Siskeen was an astronomical object in the Outer Rim Territories of the galaxy, positioned at the coordinates R-17 on the Standard Galactic Grid.

title: Skako
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Core Worlds', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-9', 'Trade routes': 'Hydian Way'}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'High-pressure methane', 'Fauna': 'Octuptarra'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Skakoan', 'Primary language(s)': 'Skakoverbal', 'Affiliation': ['Confederacy of Independent Systems', 'Techno Union', 'Galactic Empire']}}
paragraph: Skako was a planet in the Core Worlds region of the galaxy which was the homeworld of the sentient Skakoan species. It had a high-pressure methane atmosphere that was unpleasant or deadly to offworlders. Using the methane and Skako's plentiful metallic resources, the technology-focused Skakoans covered the planet in industry and turned it into an ecumenopolis. For many millenia it remained disconnected from the Galactic Republic due to the Skakoans' xenophobic and isolationist tendencies, but eventually the Skakoan Foreman Wat Tambor of the Techno Union became de facto representative of the world and its people in the Galactic Senate.

title: Skorrupon
side_bar: {'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial'}}
paragraph: Skorrupon was a terrestrial astronomical object where the New Republic pilots Wyl Lark and Kamala encountered a Twi'lek. Several weeks after the Battle of Endor in 4 ABY, Kamala, in a game of "Who? What? Where?" chose the Twi'lek on Skorrupon to be the first to hear in the event of her death.

title: Skye
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'H-19'}}
paragraph: Skye was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Skynara
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'P-19'}}
paragraph: Skynara was an astronomical object located in the Outer Rim Territories, positioned at the coordinates P-19 on the Standard Galactic Grid. Skynara was located on a hyperspace route that branched to Spice Terminus, Suarbi and Vohai.

title: Sleheyron
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Hutt Space', 'Grid coordinates': 'S-10'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Hutt', 'Affiliation': 'Hutt Clan'}}
paragraph: Sleheyron was a planet located in the galaxy's Hutt Space region, in grid square S-10 on the Standard Galactic Grid, that was connected to Kessel, Klatooine, Nimban, and Varl by a hyperspace route. Controlled by the Hutt Clan, it was the homeworld of Hutt crime lord Ziro, who was covered in colorful tattoos indicating his connection to Sleheyron.

title: Sluis Van
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-19', 'Trade routes': 'Rimma Trade Route'}, 'Societal information': {'Major exports': 'Starships', 'Affiliation': ['Outland Regions Security Force', 'Confederacy of Independent Systems']}}
paragraph: Sluis Van was an astronomical object in the southern region of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories, along the Rimma Trade Route. It provided ships to Seswenna's Outland Regions Security Force prior to the Clone Wars. Count Dooku later turned both Sluis Van and Yag'Dhul over to the side of the Confederacy of Independent Systems.

title: Smuggler's Run
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'S-18', 'Trade routes': 'Corellian Run'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Asteroid belt', 'Primary terrain': 'Asteroids'}}
paragraph: The Smuggler's Run was an asteroid belt located in the Outer Rim Territories on the Corellian Run. It was near the planet Wrea. During the Galactic Civil War, TIEs marked with blue stripes, patrolled the Smuggler's Run and intercepted freighters suspected of carrying illicit cargo, with any who didn't submit for boarding inspection obliterated immediately.

title: Sneeve
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'Q-10'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Sneevel'}}
paragraph: Sneeve was an astronomical object in the Mid Rim that served as the homeworld of the Sneevel podracer Boles Roor.

title: Socorro
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'System': 'Gold system', 'Grid coordinates': 'Q-17'}, 'Physical information': {'Primary terrain': 'Deserts', 'Points of interest': ['Socorro asteroid belts', 'Unidentified orbiting defense platform'], 'Fauna': 'Monnok'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Human', 'Demonym': 'Socorran', 'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Socorro was a an astronomical object located in the Gold system within the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. It was the homeworld of Landonis Balthazar Calrissian, former Baron Administrator of Cloud City. It was also the location of asteroid belts with large quantities of doonium ore. The former pirate queen Maz Kanata marked it as a shadowport on a map she included in the book that became known as the Smuggler's Guide.

title: Spice Terminus
side_bar: {'General information': {'Location': 'Outer Rim Territories'}}
paragraph: Spice Terminus was a location in the Outer Rim Territories of the galaxy.

title: Spira
side_bar: {'Physical information': {'Climate': 'Tropical'}}
paragraph: Spira was a tropical world in the galaxy. The Resistance pilot Poe Dameron once took a vacation there, and was reminded of it when tasting a drink at an auction hosted by Nifera Shu on Corellia.

title: Spirana
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Inner Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-13', 'Trade routes': 'Corellian Run'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': ['Santrapei', "Yrica Quell and Chass na Chadic's house"]}}
paragraph: Spirana was an astronomical object in the galaxy's Inner Rim, situated along the Corellian Run.

title: Sriluur
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Hutt Space', 'Grid coordinates': 'S-8'}, 'Physical information': {'Primary terrain': 'Deserts', 'Fauna': 'Sriluurian butterfly'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Weequay', 'Demonym': 'Sriluurian', 'Affiliation': 'Hutt Cartel'}}
paragraph: Sriluur was a desert planet located in the Hutt Space region of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories that was the homeworld of the Weequays, a species whose tough, leathery skin helped them endure its harsh conditions, and the Sriluurian butterfly.

title: Stenos
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'R-5'}}
paragraph: Stenos was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Stobar
side_bar: {'General information': {'Points of interest': ['Stobar spaceport', "Plop Dribble's"]}}
paragraph: Stobar was the location of the Stobar spaceport.

title: Suarbi
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'O-19'}}
paragraph: Suarbi was an astronomical object located in the Outer Rim Territories of the galaxy, and linked to Vohai, Spice Terminus and Svivren. It was positioned at the coordinates O-19 on the Standard Galactic Grid.

title: Subterrel
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Orbital position': 'L-20'}}
paragraph: Subterrel was a planet located beyond the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. At some point before the Clone Wars, Dexter Jettster spent time prospecting on Subterrel.

title: Sullust
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Sullust sector', 'System': 'Sullust system', 'Moons': '1', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-17', 'Trade routes': ['Incisor Sidestep', 'Rimma Trade Route', 'Sanctuary Pipeline']}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Climate': 'Hot', 'Primary terrain': 'Volcanic molten surface', 'Points of interest': ['Abandoned weapons depot', 'Alderaan Enclave', 'Inyusu Tor', 'Inyusu Tor mineral processing facility', 'Mayjein Eruption', 'SoroSuub Centroplex', 'SoroSuub Refinery', 'Sullust Sector Spacefarers Academy'], 'Fauna': ['Ash angel', 'Bat', 'Crab', 'Rockrender', 'Sullustan ash-rabbit', 'Trilobite']}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Sullustan', 'Immigrated species': 'Human', 'Primary language(s)': ['Galactic Basic', 'Sullustese'], 'Population': 'At least one billion', 'Demonym': 'Sullustan', 'Major cities': 'Pinyumb', 'Major exports': ['Starfighters', 'Assault shuttles'], 'Affiliation': ['Galactic Republic', 'Confederacy of Independent Systems', 'Galactic Empire', 'SoroSuub Corporation', 'Alliance to Restore the Republic', 'New Republic']}}
paragraph: Sullust was a planet located in the Sullust system of the Outer Rim Territories that was home to the Sullustan species.

title: Sump
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Orbital position': 'I-18'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Nuknog'}}
paragraph: Sump was an astronomical object in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories that was the homeworld of the Nuknog species.

title: Svivren
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'O-19'}}
paragraph: Svivren was an astronomical object in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Sy Myrth
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'S-7'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Sy Myrthian'}}
paragraph: Sy Myrth was an astronomical object located in the Outer Rim Territories of the galaxy, situated at the coordinates S-7 on the Standard Galactic Grid. It was linked via hyperspace routes to Belderone, Boonta, Centares and Jabiim. Sy Myrth was the homeworld of the Sy Myrthian Brookish Boon.

title: Syvris
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region(s)': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'T-13', 'Trade routes': 'Triellus Trade Route'}}
paragraph: Syvris was a small moon in the Outer Rim Territories region of the galaxy located at galactic coordinates T-13. It was part of the Triellus Trade Route, which connected it to the worlds Dubrava and Arami. Another hyperspace route connected it to the Hutt Space world of Hollastin.

title: Taanab
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Inner Rim', 'System': 'Taanab system', 'Grid coordinates': 'O-8', 'Trade routes': 'Perlemian Trade Route'}, 'Societal information': {'Major exports': 'Foodstuffs'}}
paragraph: Taanab was a planet located in the Taanab system within the galaxy's Inner Rim on the Perlemian Trade Route. The world was home to several agricultural projects which created food used to feed billions of inhabitants of Mid Rim and Outer Rim worlds. The Rebel pilot Wes Janson was born on Taanab.

title: Takodana
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': ['Mid Rim', 'Western Reaches'], 'Sector': 'Tashtor sector', 'System': 'Takodana system', 'Suns': ['1:', "Takodana's sun"], 'Moons': '0', 'Grid coordinates': 'J-16', 'Trade routes': 'Biox Detour', 'Orbital period': '215 days'}, 'Physical information': {'Diameter': ['12', '100 kilometers'], 'Primary terrain': ['Plains', 'Seas', 'Temperate forest'], 'Points of interest': ["Maz Kanata's campsite", 'Takodana Castle', 'Nymeve Lake'], 'Fauna': ['Birds', 'Chicken', 'Convor', 'Flurrg']}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': ['Artiodac', 'Frigosian', 'Human', 'Volpai'], 'Population': 'Less than 1 million', 'Demonym': 'Takodanan', 'Major cities': 'Andui', 'Affiliation': 'Neutral'}}
paragraph: Takodana was a planet located in the Mid Rim, though it fell in the southwestern region of the galaxy known as the Western Reaches.

title: Talay
side_bar: {'General information': {'Location': 'Mid Rim', 'Points of interest': 'Tak Base'}, 'Chronological and political information': {'Affiliation': 'Alliance to Restore the Republic'}}
paragraph: Talay was a location in the galaxy that served as an Alliance to Restore the Republic regional headquarters and operations sector during the early rebellion against the Galactic Empire. Talay would be included in a map of the galaxy that listed safe worlds, starfighter hubs at level five or higher, regional headquarters and operations sectors, and deep space caches. Ord Pardron, an Alliance safe world, was nearby.

title: Taloraan
paragraph: Taloraan was a location in the galaxy, home to the Wind Raiders. While living as a hermit on the planet Pasaana, Lando Calrissian wore a Taloraan Wind Raider's helmet.

title: Tammuz-an
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'T-14'}, 'Societal information': {'Government': 'Monarchy', 'Affiliation': 'Tammuz-an royalty'}}
paragraph: Tammuz-an was a planet located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. Shortly after the end of the Clone Wars, the Tammuz-an royalty purchased a batch of R-22 prototypes from Kuat Systems Engineering designers for their planetary defense fleet, after the Galactic Empire rejected the ship for mass production. Tammuz-an was responsible for nicknaming the R-22 as "Spearheads" after their resemblance to local spears.

title: Tangrene
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'O-4'}}
paragraph: Tangrene was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories, connected via hyperspace route to Edusa.

title: Targon
side_bar: {'Biological classification': {'Classification': 'Cat'}, 'Physical characteristics': {'Hair color': ['Red', 'Yellow']}}
paragraph: Targons were a species of giant cats that possessed thick fur and tufted ears. Despite being a predator species, they had low-level empathic abilities. Lina Soh, Chancellor of the Galactic Republic during the High Republic Era, owned two pet targons, Matari and Voru, who accompanied her wherever she went.

title: Taris
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-7'}, 'Physical information': {'Primary terrain': ['Urban', 'Vines and fungae'], 'Points of interest': 'Talinn district', 'Flora': ['Three fingered vine', 'Slime-slick fungus'], 'Fauna': 'Assassin-spider'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': ['Human', 'Kubaz'], 'Primary language(s)': 'Galactic Standard', 'Demonym': 'Tarisian', 'Affiliation': ['Galactic Empire', 'New Republic']}}
paragraph: Taris was a polluted urban planet located in the Outer Rim. Although Taris was a heavily populated ecumenopolis, much of the surface itself was polluted with wrecked starships and dense, overgrown swamps. Makeshift tenements made of shipping containers and crashed starships stacked on top of one another, while yellow smog drifted in the atmosphere. The elite of the planet dwelled in nicer skyscrapers.

title: Tarsunt
side_bar: {'Biological classification': {'Designation': 'Sentien'}, 'Physical characteristics': {'Skin color': ['Gray', 'Purple', 'Yellow'], 'Hair color': ['Brown', 'White'], 'Eye color': 'Black', 'Distinctions': ['Thick fur', 'long pelts', 'paws']}, 'Sociocultural characteristics': {'Homeworld': 'Tarsunt'}}
paragraph:
The Tarsunt were a species of furry sentients. They had long pelts of fur.
One member of this species was the engineer Brill, who aided the Alliance to Restore the Republic in the Battle of Endor. Another was Lanever Villecham, who served as Chancellor of the New Republic 30 years after the Battle of Endor. Blik ran a gladiatorial arena where droids fought each other. Another member of the tarsunt species was senator Colandrus.

title: Taskeed
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'S-7'}}
paragraph: Taskeed was an astronomical object located in the Outer Rim Territories of the galaxy. Linked to Jabiim and Dennogra by hyperspace routes, it was positioned at the coordinates S-7 on the Standard Galactic Grid.
