'Water'], 'Major exports': ['Dilarium oil', 'Silicax oxalate', 'Slaves'], 'Affiliation': ['Hutt Clan', "Jabba Desilijic Tiure's criminal empire", 'Galactic Empire']}}
paragraph: Tatooine was a sparsely inhabited circumbinary desert planet located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. It was the homeworld of Anakin and Luke Skywalker, who would go on to shape galactic history. Part of a binary star system, the planet was oppressed by scorching suns, resulting in the world lacking the necessary surface water to sustain large populations. As a result, many residents of the planet instead drew water from the atmosphere via moisture farms. The planet also had little surface vegetation.

title: Taul
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Moons': 'At least 3'}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Toxic', 'Primary terrain': ['Acidic', 'Deserts', 'Rocky'], 'Fauna': ['Can-cell', 'Spice spider', 'Starfish', 'Thidaxx']}}
paragraph: Taul was an acidic planet in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories, inhabitated by several dangerous creatures, such as the steel-eating spice spiders.

title: Telerath
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Inner Rim', 'Sector': 'Nouane sector', 'System': 'Telerath system', 'Trade routes': 'Vaathkree Trade Corridor'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Primary terrain': 'Islands', 'Points of interest': 'Manala'}}
paragraph: Telerath was a planet located in the Nouane sector of the Inner Rim. It was allegedly a resort world but had problems with gang violence. Disputes on Telerath were settled through sword combat, in a convention known as Sword Law. In a cantina on Telerath, the bounty hunter Jango Fett and his son, Boba, met with fellow hunters Neelda, Rinn, and Tiver, who Fett had hired for an upcoming mission.

title: Telos
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'Q-4', 'Trade routes': 'Hydian Way'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Telos was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories, along the Hydian Way. During the campaign at Salient, an Imperial battle group was stationed at Telos under the command of Admiral Utu. Moff Wilhuff Tarkin requested that Utu dispatch whatever vessels she could spare from Telos to Salient, and was later informed by a commander that Utu hoped to send two Star Destroyers.

title: Telti
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Inner Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-10'}}
paragraph: Telti was an astronomical object in the galaxy's Inner Rim.

title: Tepasi
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Core Worlds', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-9'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Human'}}
paragraph: Tepasi was a planet located in the galaxy's Core Worlds that was the homeworld of General Cassio Tagge, a member of the Galactic Empire during the Galactic Civil War who was born into nobility and privilege. It shared its name with Tepasi taffy.

title: Terminus
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Kallea sector', 'Grid coordinates': 'K-20', 'Trade routes': ['Corellian Trade Spine', 'Hydian Way']}}
paragraph: Terminus was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories, and was the intersection of the Corellian Trade Spine and the Hydian Way. The corridor was known to be infested with pirates, including the Ohnaka Gang. Around 3 ABY, the Spirit of Jedha dropped out of hyperspace, and was trapped there.

title: Teth
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Wild Space', 'Sector': 'Baxel sector', 'System': 'Teth system', 'Moons': '2', 'Grid coordinates': 'U-12'}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Primary terrain': ['Jungle lowlands', 'Tall mesas'], 'Points of interest': ["B'omarr Order Monastery", "Grakkus' safe house", 'Hutt palace of Teth', "Tomb of Ziro the Hutt's father"], 'Fauna': 'Can-cell'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Hutt', 'Affiliation': ["B'omarr Order", 'Hutt Clan', 'Confederacy of Independent Systems']}}
paragraph: Teth was a jungle planet located in Wild Space. At some point, the world was inhabited by the B'omarr Order. However, by the time of the Clone Wars, their castles were abandoned, though some would be converted by the Hutts into formidable strongholds. Some distance from the B'omarr monastries and the Tomb of Ziro the Hutt's father, an area of mysterious rock formations could be found on the surface of Teth.

title: Thakwaa
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'I-19'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Points of interest': 'Red Isles', 'Flora': 'Plants', 'Fauna': 'Flies'}}
paragraph: Thakwaa was a terrestrial astronomical object located in the Outer Rim Territories and positioned at the coordinates I-19 on the Standard Galactic Grid. The Red Isles was a location on Thakwaa, where the Rebel Alliance pilot Nath Tensent and his astromech droid T5 had to spend a night some time prior to the Battle of Endor, fought in 4 ABY. For protection against flies, T5 convinced Tensent to create an ointment from plant stems, which had a side effect of causing rashes. According to Tensent, nothing interesting occurred during his time on Thakwaa, and the two departed several days later.

title: The Red Twins
side_bar: {'General information': {'Location': 'Mid Rim'}}
paragraph: The Red Twins was a location in the galaxy's Mid Rim.

title: The Redoubt
side_bar: {'General information': {'Location': 'Wild Space'}}
paragraph: The Redoubt was an astronomical object located in Wild Space, near the Utegetu Nebula. It held the coordinates H-7 on the Standard Galactic Grid.

title: The Ring
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region(s)': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Anoat sector'}}
paragraph: The Ring was an astronomical object found within the Anoat sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. It was situated relatively close to the planets Gerrenthum and Nothoiin.

title: The Wheel
side_bar: {'Production information': {'Class': 'Space station'}, 'Location information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'System': 'Besh Gorgon system'}, 'Usage': {'Owner(s)': 'Jaspara', 'Points of interest': ['Cosmo Lounge', 'Middle Ring', 'Third level', 'Upper Ring']}}
paragraph: The Wheel, also known as space station BDT-0978, was a space station located in the Besh Gorgon system of the galaxy's Mid Rim.

title: Thearterra
side_bar: {'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Points of interest': 'Thearterra mining field'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Chiss Ascendancy'}}
paragraph: Thearterra was a terrestrial astronomical object of the Chiss Ascendancy. A mining field was operated on Thearterra, and was sought over by both the Mitth and Ufsa families.

title: Thila
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'Q-4'}}
paragraph: Thila was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Thisspias
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region', 'Grid coordinates': 'O-8'}, 'Physical information': {'Climate': 'Temperate', 'Primary terrain': 'Rocky', 'Fauna': ['Cygnat', 'Thissp mouse', 'Ystervark']}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Thisspiasian', 'Primary language(s)': 'Thisspiasian', 'Government': 'Blood Monarchy', 'Affiliation': ['Galactic Republic', 'Galactic Empire']}}
paragraph: Thisspias was a rocky, temperate planet located in the galaxy's Expansion Region. It was the homeworld of the Thisspiasian species, including the Jedi Master Oppo Rancisis. The planet had been a member of the Galactic Republic for a very long time, and was also the site of many important battles, particularly during the Great Manifest Period.

title: Thonner
side_bar: {'General information': {'Location': ['Moddell sector', 'Outer Rim Territories']}}
paragraph: Thonner was a location in the galaxy's Moddell sector.

title: Thule
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Sector': 'Esstran sector'}}
paragraph: Thule was a location in the Esstran sector of the galaxy.

title: Thustra
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region', 'System': 'Thustra system', 'Grid coordinates': 'O-7'}}
paragraph: Thustra was a planet located in the Thustra system of the Expansion Region. Sephi flyers came from here.

title: Thyferra
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Inner Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-14', 'Trade routes': 'Rimma Trade Route'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Vratix', 'Affiliation': 'First Order'}}
paragraph: Thyferra was a planet located in the galaxy's Inner Rim, on the Rimma Trade Route. It was the homeworld of the Vratix species. Arvel Crynyd piloted Z-95 Headhunters for a bacta cartel on the world. Following the Battle of Exegol in 35 ABY, Thyferra was in open rebellion against the First Order.

title: Tibrin
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Sector': 'Hadar sector', 'Suns': '3', 'Moons': 'At least 1', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-18'}, 'Physical information': {'Primary terrain': 'Oceans', 'Fauna': ['Fire-coral', 'Saberfish']}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Ishi Tib', 'Primary language(s)': 'Ishi Tibrin', 'Government': 'Tibrin government', 'Major cities': 'Tibrina ', 'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Tibrin was a aquatic planet covered in phosphorescent seas with towering coral reefs as tall as the sky located on the edge of the Hadar sector, in a trinary star system, within the galaxy's Mid Rim. It was the homeworld of the Ishi Tib species.

title: Tierfon
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': 'Tierfon launch base'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Human', 'Affiliation': 'Alliance to Restore the Republic'}}
paragraph: Tierfon was a planet in the Mid Rim that was considered a Rebel Alliance starfighter hub that was at least a level five during the early rebellion against the Galactic Empire. Tierfon was included in a map of the galaxy that listed safe worlds, starfighter hubs at level five or higher, regional headquarters and operations sectors, and deep space caches. The map was later included in The Rebel Files

title: Tinoon
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Anoat sector'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Tinoon was a planet located in the Anoat sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Months into the blockade of the sector by the Galactic Empire, a Rebel cargo filled with foodstuffs and armor was impounded at the Tinoon spaceport.

title: Tinta
side_bar: {'Production information': {'Type': 'Toy', 'Owners': 'Jyn Erso', 'Locations': ['Erso homestead', "Lah'mu"]}}
paragraph: Tinta first appeared as a prop in the film Rogue One: A Star Wars Story, which was released in North America on December 16, 2016. The prop was not identified in the film, but received a name in the Star Wars: Rogue One: The Ultimate Visual Guide, which was written by Pablo Hidalgo and released alongside the film.

title: Tirahnn
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Inner Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-8', 'Trade routes': 'Perlemian Trade Route'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Tirahnn was an Imperial astronomical object located in the galaxy's Inner Rim along the Perlemian Trade Route. A thug working for the Gray Syndicate, while examining Merei Spanjaf, mentioned having seen someone with a hidden transmitter once during a gang war on Tirahnn. The thug, trying to scare her, suggested opening her skull to check.

title: Togoria
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'P-9'}}
paragraph: Togoria was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim.

title: Tokmia
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Anoat sector'}, 'Societal information': {'Major exports': 'Crystals', 'Affiliation': 'Figg Excavations'}}
paragraph: Tokmia was a planet located in the Anoat sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. Figg Excavations mined the world for crystals, though they eventually abandoned it, leaving behind some crystals guarded by a still-active security system.

title: Toola
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'S-5'}, 'Physical information': {'Climate': 'Frigid', 'Fauna': 'Mastmot'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Whiphid'}}
paragraph: Toola was a frigid planet located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories that was the homeworld of both the sentient Whiphid species and massive beast of burden known as mastmots. The Galactic Republic's clone cold assault troopers served on this frozen world during the Clone Wars and Jedi Master Quinlan Vos mistakenly believed it home to a Separatist supply base. J'Quille, a male Whiphid who worked as a bounty hunter, hailed from Toola.

title: Toong'l
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'T-7'}}
paragraph: Toong'l was an astronomical object located in the Outer Rim Territories of the galaxy, positioned at the coordinates T-7 on the Standard Galactic Grid.

title: Toprawa
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': ['Outer Rim Territories', 'New Territories'], 'Grid coordinates': 'P-5', 'Trade routes': 'Hydian Way'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': 'Sila Kott flight school'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Humans'}}
paragraph: Toprawa was a planet located in the regions known as the Outer Rim Territories and the New Territories, in the grid square P-5 of the Standard Galactic Grid. It was connected to the locations Feriae Junction and Pho Ph'eah by the Hydian Way hyperspace route.

title: Tosste
side_bar: {'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Tosste was a location within the Galactic Empire. In describing early Imperial history in his Strategy and Tactics class at the officer's academy on the planet Arkanis, Colonel Julyan taught his students that it was on Tosste that Admiral Terrinald Screed and the Imperial Navy smashed the Iska pirates that they had driven from Fanha.

title: Toydaria
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Sector': 'Hutt Space', 'System': 'Toydaria system', 'Grid coordinates': 'R-11', 'Trade routes': 'Shag Pabol', 'Rotation period': '21 standard hours', 'Orbital period': '184 standard days'}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Foggy', 'Climate': 'Temperate', 'Primary terrain': ['Forests', 'Mountains', 'Swamps'], 'Points of interest': ['Church of Toydaria', 'Leleen River', 'Royal Detention Center', 'Toydarian Royal Palace', 'Windswept Lakes'], 'Flora': ['Algae', 'Annra plant', "N'Omis flower"]}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Toydarian', 'Primary language(s)': ['Galactic Basic', 'Toydarian', 'Huttese'], 'Government': 'Fuedal monarchy', 'Population': ['11 million', '79% Toydarian', '18% Hutt', '3% other'], 'Major cities': ['Arnel', 'Riar', 'Royal City', 'Toydor'], 'Major imports': ['Consumables', 'technology'], 'Major exports': ['Consumables', 'labor'], 'Affiliation': ['Hutt Clan', 'Galactic Republic']}}
paragraph: Toydaria was the homeworld of the Toydarian species, located in Hutt Space.

title: Trandosha
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Sector': 'Mytaranor sector', 'System': 'Kashyyyk system', 'Suns': '1', 'Moons': 'Wasskah', 'Grid coordinates': 'P-9'}, 'Physical information': {'Climate': 'Temperate', 'Primary terrain': ['Forests', 'Jungles', 'Plains'], 'Points of interest': 'The Scorch', 'Fauna': ['Doshian jellyfish', 'Trandoshan hunting hound']}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Trandoshans', 'Demonym': ['Doshian', 'Trandoshan'], 'Affiliation': 'Galactic Republic'}}
paragraph: Trandosha, also known simply as Dosh, was an arboreal planet located in the galaxy's Mid Rim and the homeworld of the Trandoshan species. It was orbited by Wasskah, a verdant moon, and was positioned in the same star system as Kashyyyk, the homeworld of the Trandoshans' fierce rivals, the Wookiees. The feared Trandoshan bounty hunter Bossk hailed from Trandosha.

title: Trasse
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': ['Alliance to Restore the Republic', 'Mid Rim revolutionaries']}}
paragraph: Trasse was a planet in the Mid Rim. During the Galactic Civil War between the Galactic Empire and the Alliance to Restore the Republic, the Alliance was forced to retreat from its failed Mid Rim Offensive, an operation by the Alliance and the Mid Rim revolutionaries to take control of the Mid Rim. The Alliance was forced to retreat from many worlds including Jeyell, Durkteel, Ord Tiddell, Charros IV, and Pothor. Several revolutionaries evacuated with Alliance forces, although many decided to remain on their planets to harass the Empire.

title: Trenwyth
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'I-16'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Flesh-eating daggerworm'}}
paragraph: Trenwyth was an astronomical object located in the the galaxy's Mid Rim that was the homeworld of flesh-eating daggerworms, a species of parasitic worm that could infest happabores.

title: Trian
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'R-3'}}
paragraph: Trian was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Triffis
paragraph: Triffis was a planet within the galaxy. It was the homeworld of the Triffian podracer Ebe E. Endocott.

title: Trigalis
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'P-17'}}
paragraph: Trigalis was an astronomical object located in the Outer Rim Territories of the galaxy, connected to Farstine and Vergesso by hyperspace routes, and positioned at the coordinates P-17 on the Standard Galactic Grid.

title: Trindello
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Moddell sector', 'System': 'Trindello system'}}
paragraph: Trindello was an astronomical object located in the Trindello system of the Outer Rim Territories' Moddell sector.

title: Triton
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-18', 'Trade routes': 'Rimma Trade Route'}}
paragraph: Triton was an astronomical object in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories, situated on the Rimma Trade Route.

title: Trogan
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'R-7'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': 'Trogan Imperial outpost'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Trogan was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. It housed an Imperial outpost and was located close to the Galidraan system. When the Imperial corvette Carrion Spike was stolen and attacked Galidraan Station, Moff Wilhuff Tarkin requested a list of all nearby Imperial resources the ship might next attack; Trogan and its outpost were amongst those included in the list given to him.

title: Troiken
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'S-5'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Primary terrain': 'Forests'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Xexto', 'Immigrated species': 'Gozzo', 'Affiliation': 'Pyke Syndicate'}}
paragraph: Troiken was a planet located in the Outer Rim Territories region of the galaxy that was the homeworld of the Xexto species. It was also home to raw spice mining operations, controlled by the Pyke Syndicate.

title: Tshindral
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Trade routes': 'Rimma Trade Route'}}
paragraph: Tshindral was one of a number of locations on the Rimma Trade Route that housed manufacturing facilities, spacedocks, and shipping lanes. In 3 ABY, the Rebel Alliance's 61st Mobile Infantry attacked numerous targets along the trade route. The Imperial Captain Tabor Seitaron, who was tracking the rebels, predicted Tshindral as one of their next possible targets, alongside the planets Sullust and Malastare. He prepared Tshindral and the other two locations for an attack, and the 61st ultimately targeted Sullust.

title: Tund
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Centrality', 'System': 'Tund system', 'Grid coordinates': 'U-8'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Toong'}}
paragraph: Tund was a hidden planet located in the mysterious Tund system, within the Centrality sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories, in grid square U-8 on the Standard Galactic Grid. It was the homeworld of the Toong species and became home to Ben Quadinaros, a Toong Podracer pilot that claimed to be from the Tund system.

title: Turkana
side_bar: {'General information': {'Location': 'Outer Rim Territories'}, 'Chronological and political information': {'Affiliation': 'Alliance to Restore the Republic'}}
paragraph: Turkana was a location in the galaxy that served as an Alliance to Restore the Republic regional headquarters and operations sector during the early rebellion against the Galactic Empire. Turkana was included in a map of the galaxy that listed safe worlds, starfighter hubs at level five or higher, regional headquarters and operations sectors, and deep space caches.

title: Tynna
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-14'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Tynnan', 'Affiliation': ['Confederacy of Independent Systems', 'Galactic Republic', 'Galactic Empire']}}
paragraph: Tynna was a planet located in the galaxy's Expansion Region. During the Clone Wars, Tynna was occupied by the Separatists. Republic High Command sent at least one commando squad to the planet to coordinate with local freedom fighters, an operation that was somewhat successful. By the closing actions of the Clone Wars, it was represented in the Galactic Senate by Senator Streamdrinker. During the early stages of the Galactic Empire's reign, Streamdrinker represented the planet in the Imperial Senate until they were arrested by Imperial Intelligence one day after the creation of the Empire.

title: Tythe
paragraph: Tythe was a location in the galaxy where Count Dooku avoided defeat on at least one occasion.

title: Tython
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Deep Core', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-10'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Primary terrain': 'Mountains', 'Points of interest': ['Ancient temple ruins', 'Martyrium of Frozen Tears', 'Meridional Ice Cap'], 'Fauna': 'Butterfly'}, 'Societal information': {'Demonym': 'Tythonian', 'Affiliation': 'Jedi Order'}}
paragraph: Tython was a terrestrial planet located in the galaxy's Deep Core region that was shrouded in myth. The Martyrium of Frozen Tears built by Jedi there, and some Jedi scholars made the case that Tython was the site of the Jedi Order's first temple. During the Galactic Civil War, Doctor Chelli Lona Aphra led Darth Vader to Tython's Meridional Ice Cap to mislead him as to the location of the Rebel Alliance's main base, which was actually on the Outer Rim planet Hoth.

title: Uba
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Sector': 'Barsa sector', 'System': 'Uba system', 'Grid coordinates': 'J-6'}}
paragraph: Uba was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim.

title: Ubrikkia
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'Q-10'}}
paragraph: Ubrikkia was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim.

title: Ukio
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Abrion sector', 'Grid coordinates': 'S-15'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Ukian', 'Major exports': 'Foodstuffs', 'Affiliation': ['Galactic Republic', 'Confederacy of Independent Systems']}}
paragraph: Ukio was an agrarian planet located in the Abrion sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories, connected by hyperlane to Rishi and Molavar. Its native inhabitants were the Ukians. During the last decades of the Galactic Republic, Ukio acted as a breadbasket of the Core Worlds. However, during the Secessionist Movement, the Ukians began to resent the Republic for not reciprocating enough. Eventually, Ukio joined the Confederacy of Independent Systems.

title: Ulmatra
paragraph: Ulmatra was an astronomical object located in the galaxy that was connected to Randa, in the Kessel sector, by hyperspace route. It was also where the Hutt crime lord Durga was based.

title: Ultaar
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'R-8'}}
paragraph: Ultaar was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim.

title: Umbara
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region', 'Sector': 'Ghost Nebula', 'System': 'Umbara system', 'Moons': "At least 2: Umbara's outermost moon", 'Grid coordinates': 'P-10'}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Primary terrain': 'Rolling landscapes with overgrown plant life', 'Points of interest': ['Sector delta', 'Umbaran airbase'], 'Flora': ["Death's embrace", 'Zabrak spine'], 'Fauna': ['Banshee', 'Vixus']}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Umbaran', 'Primary language(s)': 'Umbaran', 'Government': 'Umbaran government', 'Major cities': 'Umbaran capital', 'Major exports': 'Doonium', 'Affiliation': ['Galactic Republic', 'Confederacy of Independent Systems', 'Galactic Empire']}}
paragraph: Umbara, known as the "Shadow World" due to the lack of sunlight on its surface, was a planet located within the Expansion Region. The planet was also an exporter of doonium, a metal utilized in the construction of starships. During the Clone Wars, the planet was initially part of the Galactic Republic before seceding to join the Confederacy of Independent Systems. It proceeded to host one of the larger battles of the Clone Wars. After the fall of the Republic, the planet fell under the power of the Galactic Empire. During the Imperial Era, Captain Thrawn suppressed an uprising on Umbara that had been engineered by the shadowy insurgent leader Nevil Cygni.

title: Umgul
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-16'}}
paragraph: Umgul was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim.

title: Uogo'cor
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'Q-10'}}
paragraph: Uogo'cor was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim.

title: Uquine
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Colonies'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Human'}}
paragraph: Uquine was a placid planet located in the galaxy's Colonies region. The agricultural scientist Tepha Leonis gave birth to her second child, Zare Leonis on the planet, although the Leonis family left the world, living in a number of locations including the space station Hosk Station and the planet Lothal. Uquine was also the homeworld of the rebel pilot Col Takbright. Before he left Uquine, Takbright watched in agitation as the Galactic Empire spread across the galaxy devouring worlds for ore and killing those who opposed them. After realizing he couldn't spend another day on his homeworld doing nothing, he left Uquine with credits, a duffel bag, and a vow to avenge those that had been wronged by the Empire.

title: UR-1060
side_bar: {'General information': {'Location': ['Moddell sector', 'Outer Rim Territories']}}
paragraph: UR-1060 was a location in the Moddell sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Before the Battle of Endor in 4 ABY, UR-1060 was part of a map by Corporal Ractivelle of the Stardust unit as part of the Rebel Alliance's preparation for their assault on the second Death Star.

title: UR-2650
side_bar: {'General information': {'Location': ['Moddell sector', 'Outer Rim Territories']}}
paragraph: UR-2650 was a location in the Moddell sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Before the Battle of Endor in 4 ABY, UR-2650 was featured in a map of the Moddell sector by Corporal Ractivelle of the Stardust unit as part of the Rebel Alliance's preparation for their assault on the second Death Star.

title: UR-3741
side_bar: {'General information': {'Location': ['Moddell sector', 'Outer Rim Territories']}}
paragraph: UR-3741 was a location in the Moddell sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Before the Battle of Endor in 4 ABY, UR-3741 was part of a map by Corporal Ractivelle of the Stardust unit as part of the Rebel Alliance's preparation for their attack on the second Death Star.

title: UR-8827
side_bar: {'General information': {'Location': ['Moddell sector', 'Outer Rim Territories']}}
paragraph: UR-8827 was a location in the Moddell sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Before the Battle of Endor in 4 ABY, UR-8827 was part of a map by Corporal Ractivelle of the Stardust unit as part of the Rebel Alliance's preparation for their assault on the second Death Star.

title: UR-9353
side_bar: {'General information': {'Location': ['Moddell sector', 'Outer Rim Territories']}}
paragraph: UR-9353 was a location in the Moddell sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Before the Battle of Endor in 4 ABY, UR-9353 was part of a map by Corporal Ractivelle of the Stardust unit as part of the Rebel Alliance's preparation for their assault on the second Death Star.

title: Urce
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-6'}}
paragraph: Urce was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim.

title: Urdur
side_bar: {'General information': {'Location': ['Outer Rim Territories', 'Corporate Sector'], 'Points of interest': 'Outlaw garage'}}
paragraph: Urdur was a location within the Outer Rim Territories' Corporate Sector. The former pirate Queen Maz Kanata marked it as the site of an outlaw garage on a map she included in the book that would become known as the Smuggler's Guide.

title: Usk
paragraph: The letter  was the twenty-ninth letter of the Aurebesh alphabet. It was pronounced "Usk", and equaled the High Galactic character U.

title: Utapau
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Tarabba sector', 'System': 'Utapau system', 'Suns': '1: Utapau', 'Moons': '9', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-19', 'Distance from Core': ['51', '000 light years'], 'Rotation period': '17 standard hours', 'Orbital period': '351 standard days'}, 'Physical information': {'Diameter': ['12', '900 kilometers'], 'Climate': 'Temperate', 'Primary terrain': ['Desert', 'Plains', 'Large sinkholes', 'Rocky'], 'Surface water': '0.9%', 'Points of interest': ['Shrapnel Field', 'Sinkhole Crassnah', 'Taqual racing pit'], 'Flora': ['Cave-molds', 'Ocean-kelp'], 'Fauna': ['Dactillion', 'Filth beetle', 'Ginntho', 'Jamel', 'Nos monster', 'Resputi-seal', 'Rock-vulture', 'Utapaun flying squid', 'Utapau plains quadruped', 'Varactyl']}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': ["Pau'an", 'Utai'], 'Immigrated species': ['Amani', 'Sugi'], 'Primary language(s)': ['Amani', 'Galactic Basic', 'Utapese', 'Utai'], 'Government': 'Utapaun Committee', 'Population': ['95 million:', '65% Utai', "30% Pau'an", '5% other'], 'Demonym': 'Utapaun', 'Major cities': ['Pau City'], 'Major imports': ['Foodstuffs', 'technology'], 'Major exports': ['Chemicals', 'Ore', 'Minerals', 'Salts', 'Starships'], 'Affiliation': ['Techno Union', 'Confederacy of Independent Systems', 'Galactic Empire']}}
paragraph: Utapau was a remote and rocky planet in the Outer Rim Territories' Utapau system that was covered with enormous sinkholes. Its native inhabitants were the Pau'ans and the Utai, though tribes of Amani also immigrated to the world. It was the location of the Battle of Utapau during the Clone Wars.

title: Utegetu Nebula
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region(s)': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'I-8'}}
paragraph: The Utegetu Nebula was a nebula located in the galaxy's Mid Rim.

title: Uviuy Exen
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Colonies', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-9', 'Trade routes': ['Hydian Way', 'Shwuy Exchange']}}
paragraph: Uviuy Exen was an astronomical object located in the Colonies region of the galaxy, along the Hydian Way and Shwuy Exchange hyperspace routes.

title: Uyter
side_bar: {'Physical information': {'Points of interest': ['Imperial Academy of Uyter', 'Riverbreaker']}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Human', 'Major cities': 'Central City ', 'Affiliation': ['Galactic Empire', 'New Republic']}}
paragraph: Uyter was a planet in the galaxy known mostly for its agriculture and farming of crops and foodstuffs. During the Imperial Era, the Galactic Empire established an Imperial Academy in Uyter's capital city, Central City. Around the time of the Battle of Scarif, Uyter was represented in the Imperial Senate by Senator Nower Jebel. Just a few months after the pivotal Battle of Endor, the Alliance to Restore the Republic invaded Uyter and liberated the Imperial Academy from the Empire. Thirty years later, Uyter was a member world in the New Republic, where it was represented by Nahani Gillen in the Galactic Senate.

title: Vaathkree
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'S-8'}}
paragraph: Vaathkree was an astronomical object located in the Outer Rim Territories of the galaxy, positioned at the coordinates S-8 on the Standard Galactic Grid.

title: Vakkar
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Colonies', 'Grid coordinates': 'K-9', 'Trade routes': 'Shwuy Exchange'}}
paragraph: Vakkar was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Colonies region, along the Shwuy Exchange hyperspace route.

title: Valc
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Wild Space', 'Grid coordinates': 'J-4'}}
paragraph: Valc was an astronomical object located in Wild Space.

title: Valgauth
paragraph: Valgauth was a location in the galaxy. Its human inhabitants, the Valgauthians, had a reputation as berserkers when boarding starships. As such, a Valgauthian was regarded as a valuable addition to any pirate crew.

title: Vandelhelm
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-15', 'Trade routes': 'Rimma Trade Route'}}
paragraph: Vandelhelm was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Expansion Region, along the Rimma Trade Route.

title: Vandyne
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'O-5'}}
paragraph: Vandyne was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Vanqor
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'System': 'Vanqor system'}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Climate': 'Temperate', 'Primary terrain': ['Caves', 'Crystalline formations', 'Rocky'], 'Points of interest': 'Vanqor listening post', 'Fauna': 'Gundark'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Mirialan', 'Affiliation': 'Confederacy of Independent Systems'}}
paragraph: Vanqor was a rocky crystalline planet located in the Vanqor system of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories that was the homeworld of the gundark species. During the Clone Wars, the Confederacy of Independent Systems established a listening post on this world.

title: Varl
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Hutt Space', 'Grid coordinates': 'S-11'}}
paragraph: Varl was an astronomical object located in the Outer Rim Territories of the galaxy, within Hutt Space. It was connected to Saki and Nal Hutta by hyperspace routes, and positioned at the coordinates S-11 on the Standard Galactic Grid.

title: Vasha
side_bar: {'General information': {'Location': ['Moddell sector', 'Outer Rim Territories']}}
paragraph: Vasha was a location in the galaxy's Moddell sector.

title: Vassek
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'System': 'Vassek system', 'Moons': 'At least 3; including Vassek 3'}}
paragraph: Vassek was a planet in the Vassek system of the Outer Rim Territories. It had at least three moons, one of which was used by Separatist General Grievous as the location of his home base during the Clone Wars.

title: Vaynai
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'S-4'}}
paragraph: Vaynai was an astronomical object in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Velmor
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'P-7'}}
paragraph: Velmor was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim.

title: Velusia
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'System': 'Velusia system'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': 'Kolo-ha', 'Fauna': 'Chomong'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Velusian', 'Affiliation': 'New Republic'}}
paragraph: Velusia was a planet located in the Velusia system and the homeworld of the Velusian species, which occupied most of the planet except the volcanic atoll of Kolo-ha. In 5 ABY, members of the New Republic, including Chancellor Mon Mothma and Leia Organa, traveled to Velusia to negotiate the surrender of Grand Vizier Mas Amedda. Velusia was also home to the chomong, a species of sea creatures. The fossilized corpses of the chomong created a ring of shimmering sediment off the coast of Kolo-ha.

title: Vena
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region', 'Grid coordinates': 'P-9'}}
paragraph: Vena was an astronomical object located in the Expansion Region of the galaxy.

title: Vendaxa
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region', 'Suns': 'At least 1', 'Grid coordinates': 'O-14'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Primary terrain': ['Forests', 'Plains', 'Water'], 'Fauna': ['Acklay', 'Lemnai', 'Vendaxan land squid']}, 'Societal information': {'Demonym': 'Vendaxan'}}
paragraph: Vendaxa was a fertile planet located in the Expansion Region of the galaxy. It was the homeworld of the acklay, a non-sentient species of crustaceans that inhabited the planet's lush plains.

title: Ventooine
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'P-3'}}
paragraph: Ventooine was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Vergesso
side_bar: {'General information': {'Location': 'Outer Rim Territories'}, 'Chronological and political information': {'Affiliation': 'Alliance to Restore the Republic'}}
paragraph:
Vergesso was an asteroid in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. The former pirate Queen Maz Kanata marked it as a shadowport on a map that she included in the book that became known as the Smuggler's Guide.
During the early rebellion against the Galactic Empire, after being rejected for help by the Grand Hutt Council and the Bounty Hunters' Guild in fighting the Galactic Empire, the Alliance to Restore the Republic considered a possible alliance with the Mining Guild, and at the time, the Rebel Alliance maintained an investigation of Mining Guild operations on Vergesso.

title: Veron
side_bar: {'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Gwerax-hai'}}
paragraph: Veron was a terrestrial astronomical object where the species known as Gwerax-hai were captured, typically using net-throwers. The Rebel Alliance's 61st Mobile Infantry held an open recruiting drive on Veron sometime by the year 0 BBY. At the recruiting drive, the bounty hunter Brand joined the infantry company in an attempt to get close enough to Captain Micha Evon to assassinate him for his bounty. Lying about her identity, the bounty hunter smuggled her kit onto the 61st's CR90 corvette, the Thunderstrike.

title: Vestar
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-20'}}
paragraph: Vestar was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Vex
side_bar: {'General information': {'Location': ['Moddell sector', 'Outer Rim Territories']}}
paragraph: Vex was a location in the galaxy's Moddell sector.

title: Vicondor
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'J-7'}}
paragraph: Vicondor was an astronomical object located in the Mid Rim of the galaxy, connected to Vortex and Dorin by hyperspace routes. It was situated at the coordinates J-7 on the Standard Galactic Grid.

title: Vinsoth
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-5'}}
paragraph: Vinsoth was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. At some point, the Chevin Jol Bengim encountered slavers and slave camps on Vinsoth, although he later moved to the planet Jakku.

title: Virgillia
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'System': 'Virgillia system', 'Grid coordinates': 'I-18'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'New Republic'}}
paragraph: Virgillia was an astronomical object located in the Virgillia system of the Outer Rim Territories, positioned at the coordinates I-18 on the Standard Galactic Grid.

title: Virujansi
side_bar: {'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Humans', 'Government': ['Virujansi council', 'Imperial governorship'], 'Affiliation': ['Galactic Empire', 'New Republic']}}
paragraph: Virujansi was a planet in the galaxy. It was ruled by the Virujansi council, supported by the Virujansi Rarified Air Cavalry until the Galactic Empire arrived and replaced the council's rule with an Imperial governor. The members of the Air Cavalry were given the opportunity to join the Imperial Navy, but some pilots like Antoc Merrick and Garven Dreis, instead chose to join the Alliance to Restore the Republic during the Galactic Civil War.

title: Vjun
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'Q-6', 'Trade routes': 'Salin Corridor'}}
paragraph: Vjun was a planet located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories in grid square Q-6 on the Standard Galactic Grid, situated between Lucazec and Phindar along the Salin Corridor hyperspace route. It was home to the famous tailors who wove Count Dooku's elegant cloak.

title: Vohai
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'O-18'}}
paragraph: Vohai was an astronomical object in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Vondarc
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-16', 'Trade routes': 'Rimma Trade Route'}}
paragraph: Vondarc was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim, along the Rimma Trade Route.

title: Vortex
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-8'}}
paragraph: Vortex was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim. It was connected to Vicondor via hyperspace routes.

title: Vulpter
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Deep Core', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-10'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': 'Arakyd Industries data storehouse'}}
paragraph: Vulpter was a planet located in the galaxy's Deep Core that was the homeworld of the Vulptereen podracer Dud Bolt. The KX-series security droid K-2SO was constructed on Vulpter, as were many of the Galactic Empire's probe droids.

title: Vurdon Ka
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Inner Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-9', 'Trade routes': 'Perlemian Trade Route'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Vuvrian'}}
paragraph: Vurdon Ka was a planet located within the galaxy's Inner Rim that was the homeworld of the Vuvrian species. It was located close to one end of the Perlemian Trade Route, which connected it to the planets Castell and Chazwa.

title: Wayland
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-7'}}
paragraph: Wayland was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim. ZO-E3 heard that Emperor Palpatine supposedly had a huge storehouse of treasures on Wayland.

title: Wetyin's Colony
side_bar: {'Location information': {'Planet': 'Yavin 4', 'Points of interest': 'Dameron homestead'}}
paragraph: Wetyin's Colony was the main settlement on the moon Yavin 4 that was established when settlers traveled from the planet Setor to become farmers. In the months after the Battle of Endor, when Shara Bey and Kes Dameron settled in a new home there after completing their service in the Alliance to Restore the Republic. Having their own home had been their dream after being separated from one another, as well as their son, Poe, for much of the Galactic Civil War. Upon moving into their new home, the couple planted one of two remaining fragments of a Great Tree that had once dwelled in the heart of the Jedi Temple, after Bey and Luke Skywalker recovered them from the Galactic Empire.

title: Wobani
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Sector': 'Bryx sector', 'System': 'Wobani system', 'Grid coordinates': 'R-8'}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Climate': 'Temperate', 'Primary terrain': ['Hills', 'Mud plains', 'Rock formations'], 'Points of interest': ['Imperial Detention Center & Labor Camp LEG-817', 'Imperial headquarters', 'Wobani Penitentiary']}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': ['Galactic Empire', 'New Republic']}}
paragraph: Wobani was a temperate planet partially hidden by a swirling dust cloud, located in the Wobani system, in the Bryx sector of the galaxy's Mid Rim. During the Imperial Era, the planet was used by the Galactic Empire as a site for labor and prison camps.

title: Woostri
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-16', 'Trade routes': 'Rimma Trade Route'}}
paragraph: Woostri was an astronomical object in the galaxy's Expansion Region, situated along the Rimma Trade Route.

title: Wrea
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'S-18'}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Climate': 'Cold', 'Primary terrain': ['Islands', 'Oceans'], 'Points of interest': "Saw Gerrera's Wrea outpost"}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Wrean', 'Immigrated species': ['Human', 'Togruta', "Twi'lek"], 'Affiliation': 'Partisans'}}
paragraph: Wrea was a planet in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories that was mostly covered in oceans, with little land masses scattered over the surface. It was the homeworld of the aquatic Wrean species. During the Clone Wars, it hosted a comm tower. Wrea was notoriously difficult to reach, because of the Smuggler's Run asteroid belt nearby. It was for this reason that freedom fighter Saw Gerrera established a base for his Partisans insurgent group here during the reign of the Galactic Empire.

title: Wroona
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Inner Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-15', 'Trade routes': 'Rimma Trade Route'}}
paragraph: Wroona was an astronomical object in the galaxy's Inner Rim, on the Rimma Trade Route.

title: Xa Fel
side_bar: {'General information': {'Points of interest': 'Shipyard'}, 'Chronological and political information': {'Affiliation': 'Galactic Empire'}}
paragraph: Xa Fel was a location in the galaxy that housed a shipyard. During the Galactic Civil War, the shipyard of Xa Fel served the Galactic Empire; however, the New Republic fought to gain control of it in 5 ABY.

title: Xagobah
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-18'}, 'Physical information': {'Primary terrain': 'Canyons'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Xamster', 'Affiliation': ['Galactic Empire', 'Imperial-Royalist coalition']}}
paragraph: Xagobah was an astronomical object in the Outer Rim Territories which produced war resources for the Galactic Empire during the Galactic Civil War. The Rebel Alliance's 61st Mobile Infantry fought the Empire there as part of a campaign in 3 ABY. In 5 ABY, New Republic forces led by General Ria undertook a campaign against an Imperial-Royalist coalition at the astronomical body.

title: Yabol Opa
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Colonies', 'Grid coordinates': 'M-9', 'Trade routes': 'Perlemian Trade Route'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': 'University of Yabol Opa'}}
paragraph: Yabol Opa was a planet located in the galaxy's Colonies region, along the Perlemian Trade Route. It was home to the University of Yabol Opa, whose Grand Warden Solokin Sakellar owned a lodge on Coruscant.

title: Yag'Dhul
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Inner Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-14', 'Trade routes': ['Corellian Trade Spine', 'Rimma Trade Route']}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Givin', 'Affiliation': 'Confederacy of Independent Systems'}}
paragraph: Yag'Dhul was a world located in the galaxy's Inner Rim that was the homeworld of the sentient Givin species. Its environment was so harsh that their organs were sealed away from the atmosphere and they could survive for a short while in vacuum. Yag'Dhul was located at the intersection of the Corellian Trade Spine and the Rimma Trade Route. During the Separatist Crisis, it joined the Confederacy of Independent Systems. Along with Sluis Van, Yag'Dhul made up part of a southern sphere of Separatist worlds, to which Count Dooku unsuccessfully attempted to add Eriadu.

title: Yaga Minor
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'K-5'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': 'Yaga Minor shipyards'}}
paragraph: Yaga Minor was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. In 14 BBY, an incident occurred at the Yaga Minor shipyards, which was reported to Darth Vader by Captain Luitt of the Star Destroyer Perilous.

title: Yinchorr
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Expansion Region', 'Grid coordinates': 'L-8'}}
paragraph: Yinchorr was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Expansion Region, located in grid square L-8 on the Standard Galactic Grid. Following the Battle of Endor, the New Republic was involved in a battle on Yinchorr that devolved in to a siege situation.

title: Ylesia
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Hutt Space', 'Grid coordinates': 'Ð¢-12'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Fauna': 'Reek'}}
paragraph: Ylesia was a terrestrial planet in the Outer Rim Territories section of Hutt Space that, along with the Codian Moon, was the homeworld of the reek species. It was located within the Hutt Space region of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories and was connected to Teth and Rorak by hyperspace routes. The former pirate Queen Maz Kanata marked it as a point of interest on a map she included in the book that would become known as the Smuggler's Guide.

title: Yout
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Moons': ['At least 12', 'Twelfth moon of Yout']}}
paragraph: Yout was a planet with at least twelve moons. In 22 BBY, the assassin droid KRONOS-327, employee of crime lord Ziro the Hutt, returned to Ziro's Palace on the planet Coruscant after an unsuccessful mission to the twelfth moon of Yout. When KRONOS-327 reported the failure to Ziro, the Hutt sentenced the droid to be scrapped.

title: Zaddja
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'System': 'Zaddja system', 'Grid coordinates': 'H-15'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Primary terrain': 'Archipelagoes', 'Surface water': 'Oceans'}}
paragraph: Zaddja was a terrestrial astronomical object located in the Zaddja system of the Outer Rim Territories, situated at the coordinates H-15 on the Standard Galactic Grid. Its surface consisted of oceans broken up by archipelagoes of white sand beaches. At night, the beaches were covered by water from the high tides; as such, the inhabitants of Zaddja lived on flying skiffs. A hyperspace route connected Zaddja to Gannaria, a planet in the Trilon sector.

title: Zaloriis
paragraph: Zaloriis was a location in the galaxy, inhabited by Zalorians. During the Imperial Era, when the galaxy was dominated by the Galactic Empire, and prior to the Battle of Hoth in the year 3 ABY, a campaign occurred on Zaloriis between the Zalorians and the Empire. The human male Maximilian Veers demonstrated his cunning and courage in the battle, one of several conflicts that led to his eventual promotion to the rank of general in the Imperial Army.

title: Zanbar
side_bar: {'Physical information': {'Climate': 'Temperate', 'Primary terrain': ['Plateaus', 'Swamps'], 'Points of interest': 'Zanbar Death Watch camp', 'Fauna': ['Anooba', 'Momong']}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Human', 'Affiliation': ['Death Watch', 'Shadow Collective']}}
paragraph: Zanbar was a temperate swamp moon covered with massive rocky plateaus. During the Clone Wars, the Mandalorian splinter group Death Watch established a temporary camp on its surface, which continued to be used after Death Watch allied with Maul to form the Shadow Collective. Zanbar was later the site of a battle between the Shadow Collective and the Confederacy of Independent Systems.

title: Zardossa Stix
side_bar: {'Physical information': {'Primary terrain': 'Desert', 'Points of interest': 'Temple of Malmourral', 'Fauna': ['Dalgo', 'Eopie', 'Gundark', 'Tooka']}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': ['Aqualish', 'Bardottan', 'Gossam', 'Gotal', 'Human', 'Ithorian', "Kerch Kushi's species", 'Khramboan', 'Nimbanel', 'Quarren', 'Rodian', 'Sakiyan', 'Siniteen', "Twi'lek", 'Unidentified tentacle-faced species', "Voe Atell's species", 'Weequay', 'Zygerrian'], 'Primary language(s)': ['Galactic Basic', 'Gossam'], 'Major cities': 'Zardossa Stix Port', 'Affiliation': 'Frangawl Cult'}}
paragraph: Zardossa Stix was a moon with a desert climate, located near Bardotta. It had a spaceport village which Mace Windu and Jar Jar Binks visited while tracking the Frangawl Cult that had kidnapped the Queen of Bardotta, Julia. The moon also featured a pyramid called the Temple of Malmourral, which was used by the Frangawl Cult, as well as their leader, Mother Talzin, as part of a ceremony to drain the Living Force from members of the Dagoyan Order.

title: ZeHeth
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'N-16', 'Trade routes': 'Hydian Way'}}
paragraph: ZeHeth was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim that was situated along the Hydian Way.

title: Zeltros
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Inner Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'O-10'}, 'Physical information': {'Class': 'Terrestrial', 'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Primary terrain': 'Oceans'}}
paragraph: Zeltros was an astronomical object in the galaxy's Inner Rim that had oceans and beaches with tropical trees. Following a massacre aboard the Sorca Retreat, the rogue archaeologist Doctor Chelli Aphra traveled to Zeltros to take a break from her recent misadventures. While relaxing at a beach, being served a Dantooine ice-twist by a service droid, she was confronted by Tukan, who had been tracking her since she killed one of his affiliates, Dukan. Defiant of his attempt to arrest her, Aphra shot him with a blaster she had been concealing. This aggravated Tukan's accomplices, who drew their own blasters on her.

title: Zerm
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Kessel sector', 'Trade routes': 'Kessel Run'}}
paragraph: Zerm was an astronomical object located in the Kessel sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Zeta
side_bar: {'Production information': {'Manufacturer': ['Structgalactis', 'Inc.'], 'Model': 'Z7 series', 'Class': 'Construction droid'}, 'Technical specifications': {'Height': '3 meters', 'Gender': 'Feminine programming', 'Equipment': ['Frictionless omnidirectional treads', 'Symmetric arms with various attachments']}}
paragraph: Zeta was a Z7 series construction droid who was part of a crew tasked to build a settlement on Cro-Akon. When the construction site was raided by slavers, Zeta sacrificed herself to allow fellow droid Z5-TXT to escape with the other droids and organic workers. Zeta was taken to work at a mining complex on the Unknown Regions planet known as the Deep, where Lady Eekee modified Zeta with an override chip to turn her into an enforcer droid, which forced her to enjoy the suffering of other droids while also being aware of the change in her programming. The mine was infiltrated by Luke Skywalker, who intended to rescue the astromech droid R2-D2. Zeta unwillingly attempted to stop the subsequent uprising, and Skywalker removed the override chip, repairing Zeta's circuits. With Zeta's knowledge of a flaw in the override chips, Skywalker freed the other enforcers, and the droids escaped the Deep, overthrowing the organic beings who ran the operation. Zeta's story later became known to G2-X, a droid aboard the starship Wayward Current.

title: Zhanox
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Anoat sector', 'System': 'Zhanox system', 'Grid coordinates': 'K-18', 'Trade routes': 'Ison Trade Corridor'}, 'Physical information': {'Points of interest': 'Mining outposts', 'Fauna': 'Nexu'}, 'Societal information': {'Immigrated species': 'Ugnaught', 'Major exports': 'Ore'}}
paragraph: Zhanox was a mining world located in the Anoat sector of the galaxy. Ugnaught miners were known to work there, although they feared the presence of spiny nexus. During the Iron Blockade, one Zhanox mining outpost requested specific off-world supplies to be delivered by a young smuggler.

title: Zhar
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'P-17'}}
paragraph: Zhar was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

title: Ziost
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Grid coordinates': 'R-4'}, 'Societal information': {'Affiliation': 'Sith'}}
paragraph: Ziost was a world located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories that was affiliated with the Sith. Along with the likes of Malachor, Jaguada, and Rhelg, it was quarantined during the time of the Galactic Republic. Ziost was the original site of an ancient Sith ritual altar that was present in the Grand Republic Medical Facility on Coruscant in 19 BBY. Much like the planets Moraband, Exegol, and Asog, Ziost maintained a fertile climate until the arrival of the Sith.

title: Zolan
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Mid Rim', 'Grid coordinates': 'P-16'}, 'Physical information': {'Climate': 'Warm', 'Fauna': 'Monzu'}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Clawdite', 'Primary language(s)': 'Clawdite'}}
paragraph: Zolan was a warm and arid planet located in the galaxy's Mid Rim, near the Corellian Run. At some point, during the development of Zolan's native Clawdite species, a spike in solar activity bathed the planet in radiation. The Clawdite's ability to modify their skin color and body shape, similar to the predatory monzu also native to the world, resulted from this spike in solar activity, and many of the other native species developed different ways to survive. However, many other species were unable to cope and went extinct.

title: Zonama Sekot
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Unknown Regions'}}
paragraph: Zonama Sekot was an astronomical object located in the Unknown Regions. It was situated in an otherwise empty and unexplored area westward of the desert world Jakku, which was located in the Western Reaches of the Inner Rim.

title: Zorbia
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Sector': 'Moddell sector'}}
paragraph: Zorbia was a location in the Moddell sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. Because of hyperspace anomalies located within the sector, starships at Zorbia were occasionally dumped into the Endor system.

title: Zygerria
side_bar: {'Astrographical information': {'Region': 'Outer Rim Territories', 'Suns': '1', 'Moons': 'At least 1', 'Grid coordinates': 'S-4'}, 'Physical information': {'Atmosphere': 'Breathable', 'Climate': 'Temperate', 'Primary terrain': ['Plains', 'Mesas', 'Highlands', 'Rocky'], 'Points of interest': 'Royal Palace', 'Flora': 'Slave Shade', 'Fauna': ['Blurrg', 'Bogwing', 'Brezak']}, 'Societal information': {'Native species': 'Zygerrian', 'Primary language(s)': 'Galactic Basic', 'Government': 'Queen of Zygerria', 'Major imports': 'Sentient beings', 'Major exports': 'Slaves', 'Affiliation': ['Zygerrian Slave Empire', 'Confederacy of Independent Systems']}}
paragraph: Zygerria was a planet located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories that was the homeworld of the Zygerrian species.
